{"product_id": "33230", "page": 12, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-31", "text": "I loved AC2 on the PS3, and I thought I would pick it up on the PC. While it's better than I remember, worth a solid 9/10 (-1 for poor control and handling), I do NOT recommend getting this mainly because Sequence 12 and 13 are SOOOOO boring and literally add nothing to the main story. It's a HUGE let down,that grinds the story to a halt, and acts as pure filler, adding nothing at all that is fun, new or interesting.\nI would recommend getting the orinigal AC2 and then adding the DLC you want. That way, when you get bogged by the irrelevant \"Battle of Forli\" and \"Bonfire of the Vanities\" DLCs, you can uninstall/refund it and move on.", "hours": 18.0, "user_id": "76561198067198869", "username": "Monkey Mouth", "products": 109, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 12, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-31", "text": "No matter how many years passes by, AC 2 is one of the best AC games out there. In terms of story and progression that is... Jumping from one end to the other is fun (but frustrating). The best espects of this game is its concept of height. Even to this day, AC 2 still gives me the scare whenever I am jumping across platforms on high places, like the level in the massive church (I don't know what it was called).\nNow to the problems of this game!\n1. Parkour is stiff but manageable. If you think before jumping and climbing, especially on those dugeons.\n2. Combat is as easy as counting A,B,C. Maybe a bit too easy.\n3. 100% completing this game isn't that hard, but you will feel like it is a waste of time. Basically, the collectables are not worth the damn.", "hours": 19.4, "user_id": "76561198190279638", "username": "LeeJin970417", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
