{"product_id": "33230", "page": 13, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "Well, this is not a very good game (for me). Almost boring, the story just so goddamn short, even I can complete 3 sequence in 1 hour. And the most disturbing of all of this is, well, Auditore Cape bug. I'm stuck at the cinematic scene, and I can't go anywhere. And you know what? They (Ubisoft) tells me to just restart the goddamn savefile! They have no idea to fix this bug lol\nVery boring, short, and buggy. -10/10 would never play this game again.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "bubblegum", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "Though the original console version of AC II is a fantastic game, this is practically unplayable on PC.\nI've found it virtually impossible to get past a really early point (training with your uncle) due to controls not doing what they should (can't lock onto an enemy). I've tried various different controllers (including steam controller) as well as mouse & keyboard and no single configuration has let me lock onto targets; thus, I'm unable to progress in the storyline. It seems to be a common issue as I've found a lot of similar complaints when trying to find a fix, but no helpful solution yet.\nTL;DR: Don't buy on PC, get it on console.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Sam", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "It's a good game. I've played it on the PS3 and it was fun, but my problem is the freaking Uplay crap. Why the hell do I need that? I don't care! I just want to play. It's stupid that I have to make an account to play.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198190605861", "username": "4LPH4-0N3", "products": 21, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "I got a controller especially for this game because it's just too hard to learn to play when all tips on how to do stuff are given in controller format rather than keyboard. Once you get a controller it's lots of fun, it's easy to get into (and easy to fall off buildings), sometimes super frustrating but it's very forgiving to let you try again. I especially enjoyed the stealth  missions, although it can be frustrating to get detected over and over. The tombs were you find the seals are difficult but interesting, and a very welcome break from the outside city area, because after a while it just seems weird to always be outside. I liked that the hardest challenges didn't involve overpowered monsters but just your own skill and a ticking clock. I loved the way you can try different vehicles, they all handle differently and keep things interesting. The npc's get in the way but they're sassy and it's fun to steal their boat. I'm close to the finish on this one but looking to get the Brotherhood edition to conclude the story, that should tell you enough.", "hours": 60.6, "user_id": "76561198142078007", "username": "afrael", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-27", "text": "Great Game. Love it.", "hours": 42.9, "user_id": "76561198174726893", "username": "lynxanne", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "A pretty solid game. Stealth wise it's a bit shallow and Desmond's section of the plot is by far the worst part about it.  Not the pinnacle of greatness, but Ezio alone made it enjoyable to play. It was good enough to make me want to finish it, so that's worth something, I guess. If you want to play just one AssCreed, go for this one.", "hours": 24.8, "user_id": "76561198255326810", "username": "Jalter (TF2SP)", "products": 66, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "The AC series is easily in my favorite series of all time.\nWhile they change the controls a bit (mostly menu navigation) between AC2 and ACB&R, it's still largely the same game. You're an Assassin (the capital is important!), one of a long line of agents sworn to fight the Templars.\nOut of the Ezio trilogy, I would place AC2 as my favorite so far. ACB added lifts and more story, which was lovely. ACR (so far) has added more about Subject 16 and his place in everything, which is fascinating. AC2, though, seems to have a lot more material. The storyline was long, deep, and ended in a way I couldn't have predicted. Upgrading Monteriggoni paid for itself, the bredth of emotion was sustained throughout the game, and the comments in the database kept me laughing.", "hours": 53.8, "user_id": "76561198162527903", "username": "Ae3qe27u", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "I like it so much because of the storyline that is interesting; for all the people this is the best Assassin's Creed, but for me I think that is not like what I expected in the launch trailer. I would have wanted it more interactive and more wide.", "hours": 32.3, "user_id": "76561198327920618", "username": "mario", "products": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "dont work", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Shiny Alolan", "products": 51, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "In my opinion, the best AC title to date (sorry Origins, I love you very much but ACII's still on top). The graphics may be outdated for some more nit-picky players, and AC1 actually has better graphics (at least, in my opinion), but ACII still manages to be an incredibly immersive experience. Its main locations (Firenze, Venezia, Forl\u00ec, Monteriggioni and San Gimignano) have their own characteristic aura and their own charms and even soundtrack. Firenze is passionate, colorful and vibrant. Venezia is colorful but at the same time it retains a \"dreamy\" feel to it. Forl\u00ec is gloomy and humid. Monteriggioni feels like home, not only because it is the headquarters of the Assassin Order, but because it's warm and welcoming. San Gimignano is a small but busy medieval city, and feels imponent. I have personally been to Firenze and Venezia before playing the game and I'm being serious when I say that the game brought me back to those cities.\nStory-wise, it's very compelling. There was no moment in which I felt like the story was dragging out. And unlike other AC titles, ACII is a game that lets you become attached to the secondary characters. They have their own story and character development.\nIt surely is not as good as Brotherhood graphically or gameplay-wise (in Brotherhood you have many more combat and weapons options), however I do think that ACII is the best game out of the two. Brotherhood has far more side content (also very much varied), but the main story is just not as compelling as ACII's.\nACII is a classic, not only for Assassin's Creed fans, but for any gamer who enjoys a great game. If you haven't played it yet, do give it a try. If you're too scared of spending money on something you're not sure you're going to like (like me), watch a gameplay or two on Youtube, and see if you'd like to take on the experience yourself. I did it that way and found so many things on my own that those gameplays had never shown. It was totally worth it.", "hours": 106.6, "username": "Mari", "products": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 14, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "What an absolute crazy insane update from the first AC.\nThis game has such a huge update, the fighting is better / blending is better / different clothes / different weapons / different missions / alot of great characters. This is an absolute must play for AC fans.  The story is absolutely amazing and you are totally getting into it and fast. I love the different missions, you get to disguise as an enemy / you gotta join an carnaval to get a gold mask / you go FLY and SO. MUCH. MORE.\nBuy it already. I got this game for 3 EURO.... 3 EURO!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "hours": 25.7, "username": "Fiascotje", "products": 553, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 15, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-26", "text": "Pros\nGood storyline probably one of the best in AC.\nGraphics aren't awful\nAble to run well on most computers\nAmazing combat.\nCons\nThe controls are a mess, in most games controls don't bother me I usually just use the default controls. But AC2's controls where that bad I had to customise them to make it a bit playable and comfortable.\nOverall AC2 is one of the best games I've played, it is okay on PC but I would get it on console. However nothing will make me say that AC2 isn't a brilliant game... even when the controls are awful\n7/10", "hours": 16.3, "username": "Finn", "products": 53, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
