{"product_id": "33230", "page": 30, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "If Tenchu Stealth Assassin and Grand Theft Auto had a baby and bought it a Matrix onsie, this would be the outcome.\nYou need to learn how to become an Assassin and you only have a couple of days to do it! So they load you up into the memories of a 15th century Florentine noble man who you guessed it, learnt to become an Assassin. In a Matrix type state you 'become' Ezio Auditore.\nGame play is set up in a similar way to how Grand Theft Auto is -  you can free travel around beautiful Renaissance Italian cities and in those cities along side the main story are tasks / races / fights etc that you complete when and if you want -you just head to the map marker.\nThe graphics still compete with newer games and play is smooth and glitch free. Beautiful backdrops and story rich with a great soundtrack. In short, this game is frickin awesome. Buy this game... Then cancel all your plans and call in sick to work.\nP.S. If you open the game and your controller isn't registering, all you have to do is download new drivers and copy them into the steam game folder. This link shows you how to do it =)", "hours": 82.3, "user_id": "76561198310540345", "username": "batfinx", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 30, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "fastastic", "hours": 40.2, "user_id": "76561197995551101", "username": "KingJoe3rd", "products": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "This game is still compatible with Mac devices, from snow leopard and above. Startup varies for different Mac devices. Most of the time, you won't be able to see the setup and launcher window as it will be either invisible, black or white. When the startup and setup screen appears, the buttons won't be visible but still work, similar to having your brightness on the lowest setting, you wont be able to see anything but will still be able to click and do normal functions. Setting up Assasins Creed 2 will be very annoying and will take a lot of time, random clicking and raging.\nYou will need a Ubiplay account to log into Assasins Creed 2, Ubiplay accounts are only creatable on windows devices so you will need a windows devive to create a Ubiplay account which you use to log in on the invisible log in page.\nThe \"Start\" button is on the bottom right of the screen after you have logged in.\nHope this is helpful, gl & hf", "hours": 23.8, "username": "1983 Was Better", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "shity game", "hours": 21.9, "username": "William7566", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "Elaborating on the promise and fixing the faults of the original,\nis still, to this day, the greatest game in the franchise, featuring an interesting and entertaining cast of characters whose adventures are a joy to experience through the lens of the game's great and polished mechanics.", "hours": 28.0, "username": "TemplarHedgehog", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-18", "text": "I LOVE THE GAME THE STORY TOO SOO GOOD TRY IT!!!", "hours": 38.5, "user_id": "76561198202566034", "username": "Pingu", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-18", "text": "I know that people have said this is \"the best of the series\" (a couple of years ago when I purchased it), but it's one of THE WORST console ports - ever. I didn't realise? know? at the time. If you play PC and have/use/like a controller - you're good to go - if you're an actual PC player - mouse and kbd - No No No - it's unplayable - with a myriad array of keyboard mappings attempting to \"recreate\" a controller.\nWish I could get a refund. R I P", "hours": 1.4, "username": "freyjaFX", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-17", "text": "Its Good. The story is ok, the gameplay is amazing, and the open world is huge. The only downside is the pc controls (who thought they where a good idea anyway?) and the graphics (this is more understandable as it was made in 2009).", "hours": 26.1, "user_id": "76561198049713559", "username": "andrewsudworth", "products": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-16", "text": "Best game ever. I wish they made more games like these.\nFighting techniques could have been a bit diverse but its fine since it came 8 years back.\nThere needs to be a remastered version of this.", "hours": 28.3, "username": "Alta\u00efr", "products": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-15", "text": "Assassins Creed II may well be the best of the series. I have been a fan of this series since the first game and between my PC version and the Xbox 360 version, I have logged close to a thousand hours on this game. Graphically, it is not the prettiest to look at by today's standards.\nHowever, it has an amazingly compelling storyline that will leave the player enthralled. The game world has so much to do and collect, you'll not be able to put it down.", "hours": 41.5, "user_id": "76561198283540129", "username": "NerdyScot473", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-15", "text": "Surely the best Assassins Creed game in the series, it has the best main character: Ezio is just very charismatic, interesting and you feel with him. The story is also pretty good, just end rather aprubt. The control mechanics are also the best in the series, and just lets you really cntroll the character and doesnt let him climb ever single wall there is around except the one you want to climb ( I'm looking at you Black Flag). Just sometimes the perspective changes a bit weird. The graphics surpisingly aged pretty well and Florence and all the old italian cities still look beautiful. Really recommend the game, go and buy it.", "hours": 36.6, "username": "SaltyUrs", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 31, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-15", "text": "It's beautiful.\nThe storyline, the injustice, the redemption, the enchanting 15th century Renaissance Italian backdrop, all together provide an immersive and moving experience. The best Assassin's Creed game with the best Assassin ever to live. Ezio Auditore captivates us with his charisma, his good humoured nature, his sense of justice (though that takes a while).\nI played the game for 2 hours(officially). I was in a trance for 3 weeks.\nBuy it. You'll remember AC2 forever.", "hours": 9.0, "username": "The White Wolf #TheFRag", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
