{"product_id": "33230", "page": 35, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-05", "text": "The story is decent, and the parkour truly is very fun... for the first few hours. After a while you begin to realize that the core game is a total grind-fest of boring copy-pasted escort quests in copy-pasted locations. Playing Assassins Creed is a bit like clam diving, except the ocean is made of bullsh*t: you can find some truly good stuff in here, but only if you comb through the copypasted crap. Personally, I'm happy I experienced this franchise, but I can't say it's good, nor would I say it's worth the time.", "hours": 10.4, "user_id": "76561198087951038", "username": "Misanthrope", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 35, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-05", "text": "Absolutely amazing game - entertaining story, characters and increadibly beautiful Florence and Venezia :) It took me almost 100 hours to finish the game because everything  was so breathtaking ; here I met Leonardo da Vinci and Machiavelli  - I used Leonardo's flying machine and participated in the Carnival di Venezia :) I should mention that I played the game in 2015 for the first time and it impressed me so much even after a few years after it's launch. Unforgettable experience. Thank you for this amazing piece of gaming art!", "hours": 99.5, "username": "Pszcz\u00f3\u0142kaMakaronowa", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
