{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "Solid entry in AC franchise. Its heavy debated as the best game of the series but if your like me and prefer a game encourages exploration well AC 4 takes that title easily. Never mind that. The game has a solid story, Ezio is defintely the best Assassin compared to the other AC protaganist. Free running is fine but can be frusturating at times compared to newer titles and the graphics, well they didnt age that well, especially that strange brown tinge to everything eww.", "hours": 23.9, "user_id": "76561198100898836", "username": "Disastah!", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "The best Assassin's creed game. It is an enjoyable play, but no more. It is nothing really special, and is rubish compared to games such as Tomb raider(2013) or Skyrim. Still worth playing though. - Problem is, once  you've already played a few assassin's creed games, you will get fed up of this one very quickly, as all the games have pretty much the same storyline, and playin as an assassin gets very annoying very quickly.\nTHIS IS A GOOD GAME, BUT:\nIT IS DESIGNED FOR PLAYING ON A CONSOLE< NOT ON PC, AND  AS A RESULT IT IS  EXTREMELY DIFFICULT YO PERFORM SOME OF THE PARKOUR SEQUENCES! furthermore, the tutorial stages in the game tell you how to play the game on a console, so you will have to waste some time reading the controls on the main menu. UBISOFT NEED TO UPDATE THIS GAME FOR PC!", "hours": 22.2, "user_id": "76561198273645312", "username": "BenMin0", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "This is my first ever Assassin's Creed game, and turns out it has gave me one of the best experience in gaming.\nFinished this game after the game is already 7 years old, and it doesn't feel old at all. Amazing graphics, soundtracks are pretty good too.\nThe background of the Italian renaissaince added a lot of charm to it as this is one of the historical event I like.\nThe main story is just awesome, and the ending was a twist for me, at least.\nAssassin's Creed 2 is rich of content, assassins tomb, hired mission, historical details, memory glyphs etc.\nEven though steam does not have any acheivements for it, I still spend a lot of time finding and unlocking everything in the game, just to enjoy more of those unlockables.\nCool platforming, combats is very fun and you could kill your targets with any style you like, but some of them have some serious requirements that cannot mess up.\nThe game doesn't require money grinding at all, unless you want more survivability at early game.\nEasily one of the best assassin games i've ever play, and highly recommended to everyone out there.\n9.5/10", "hours": 32.8, "username": "P\u03ac\u0438D\u00e1_\ud800\udf00dd\u0457ct\u0451D", "products": 272, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "Although I'm recommending it I have some strong criticism towards this game.\nThe whole thing with the Animus and Desmond and everything is really weird and unecessary.\nAlthough the climbing and free-runnig is fun, it is painfully obnoxious when your character does the complete opposite of what you wanted, and it is rage inducing.\nTowards the end I saw a lot of fille rmissions which were honestly boring, pointless and underwhelming.\nI get the point of the game being fight or flight but sometimes there is too many people around and it is not fun.\nI enjoyed this game but it could be a lot better.", "hours": 23.5, "username": "Majin Greed", "products": 765, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "It's a little better than the first game, but I still wasn't wild about it. The action could definitely be more fun and, for that matter, challenging.", "hours": 44.4, "username": "The Universal Void", "products": 1056, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "Assassin's Creed II was way better than its predecessor; scenery looks beautiful and musics are awesome! The ability to buy things is a great increase and side missions are better. The game made me even want to start learning Italian! I fell in love with Rosa and my heart broke when Ezio and Rosa didn't become a couple. I recommend this game warmly, even if I got upset for Rosa.", "hours": 75.4, "username": "Lone Wolf", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 37, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-10-24", "text": "Having played most of the AC games, I can hand on heart say that AC2 is still the best of them all. Sure, later games added a little more in the way of actions, abilities and gadgets, bigger worlds to explore and even seas to sail, but it was AC2 that truly defined the series. This is the one AC game where, far and above all the others, everything just comes together perfectly - story, setting, characters, gadgets, actions, mechanics, graphics...And the music? A sheer delight to listen to. AC2 is a masterpiece so beautifully captivating from is humble beginning to its awesome conclusion, you'd swear the hand of Da Vinci himself had been involved in its creation.", "hours": 39.0, "user_id": "76561198008254365", "username": "Septimus", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
