{"product_id": "33230", "page": 47, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-19", "text": "I want to like this game, and I do for the most part, so that's why I'm giving it a thumbs up... overall, it's a great game and I love the series (I own all of them) but I don't know what it is. I guess it just boils down to the missions and story are just too repetitive and always on the verge of putting me to sleep...\nThis game in a nutshell (for me): \"Oh.. we need to kill this dude... oh wait, this dude needs to die now... oh, and then there's his mean uncle, too. Kill him next... let's see... I guess you can kill this next guy, he's kinda a jerk. -shrugs-\"", "hours": 51.1, "username": "WingFlux", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 47, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-09-19", "text": "This is the beginning of where Assassin's Creed really comes into it's own. Defintely worth playing.\nFirst of all, they began by adding the essential stealth kill mechanics, such as haystack kills, ledge kills, and drop kills, and then expect you to use them to kill without being seen.\nSecond, unlike the first game, a crowd of guards can be a real pain, especially once they start mixing in brutes.\nLastly, the controls feel a lot better, though you won't be able to escape jumping off into space now and then. Still an improvement over the first game. And to top it off, water no longer is an instant death for you (though it still kills your enemies), so thumbs up to that.\nGraphics are what you'd expect from a game of that age, but they didn't kill the mood for me. Sound quality wasn't anything I noticed as either good or bad.\nAll in all, a good game worth playing.", "hours": 74.7, "user_id": "76561197970289054", "username": "Wildfire [VoM]", "products": 586, "early_access": false}
