{"product_id": "33230", "page": 56, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-19", "text": "So i played the first Assassin's Creed game for several hours before it got boring and that's when my friend told me to play AC2.  When I first loaded the game I did not realized how big the map would be.  The story is amazing to play through and I watched as Ezio grew to be a great Assassin.  It took me several days before I finished the game because I was exploring the map and the viewpoints and doing side missions.  I just enjoy this game a lot better than AC 1 because there is a lot more to explore and I find the setting of the game to be beautiful.", "hours": 30.5, "username": "melancholy", "products": 1380, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
