{"product_id": "33230", "page": 56, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-19", "text": "I had lots and lots of fun playing this game. It's not perfect, but what is?\nPROS\n- Ezio's journey. I cared about what happened, even if the story wasn't such a revelation to me personally.\n- It worked like a charm on Win10 with my controller. No technical problems at all, no Uplay problems either.\n- It has tons of fun stuff to do. Very differentiated quests (mostly killing, but fun!).\n- YMMV on this, but it's an easy game. I don't like to stress too much over games, and it was ok for me.\n- Collecting things makes sense, they are relevant to the story.\n- Double air assassinations never get old.\nCONS\n- Towards the end, the story took over and the gameplay was a bit mechanical.\n- Too many timed quests (and close shave at that) for my taste. If I wanted to constantly worry about the clock ticking, I would be a track athlete.\n- Video- audio was not synchronized in many of the cut scenes.\n- Guards can be annoyingly stupid, blind and deaf.\n- Ezio has a ladder fetish. No, really, just walk by them and he gets an urge to climb.\n- Jumps and reaches have game logic. 2 meters away, if the game needs it? No problem. 40 cm if the developers didn't want it that way? Nope.\nThis was my first AC game, and now I'm itching to play all of them.\nP.S. English with an accent= character speaks his native language, will never be not hilariously funny to the rest of us.", "hours": 60.7, "username": "Gia_P11", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-18", "text": "Hands down the best in the series. Perfect story, gameplay, missions etc.", "hours": 48.9, "username": "Isaiah's In HD", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-17", "text": "Brings me back to when I played these games when I was younger. Overall pretty gud story as it made you feel like you were really immersed with the character. Fun movement while combat seems a bit too easy.", "hours": 35.6, "username": "lil tit", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-17", "text": "Ezio Auditore is an assassin avenging the wrongeful execution of his family, in Italy Ezio hunts down templars with the help of Leonardo Da Vinci who builds his weapons and his uncle Mario who helps him train.  10/10 would kill templars again", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198342220205", "username": "WhiterDruid", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-17", "text": "This is one of those well made games and one that actually ignited the franchise (if as of lately kinda becoming in stagant stage I'm feeling about it without a established modern protagonist) and this is first of third games starring Ezio in of his grand adventure. This one entails a bloody rampage on a Templar conspiratory.\nAs for the game itself, the story is well done and actually gave you two Heroes, Desmond (Modern) and Ezio (Past), and it follow up with from the last game Assassin's Creed 1 with a intro narration to tell you what happened so far (marks for that) and a escape from facility that is ran by people who kidnapped you and kicked off the story for the franchise as well as to birth of our beloved hero whose humble rich style life is shattered later by machinations of a conspiratory. Throughout the game you'll visit different cities with different information on different locations, buildings at the time of late 15th century, and both fictional and actual real people.\nBesides from the amazing adventure and good graphics at the time of actual release, game does offer you some side activities that actually would either contribute to the story (graphs' puzzles come to mind), serves mostly to enlarge your pocket to ensure you can get better armor, weapons, ranged ammunition, and smelling salts to restore your lost health, or get you a amazing armor set while doing the side activites that involve Assassins' Seals. Later on in the game, you can get involved rebuilding a villia that seen better days has passed and look run down and murky that later, with investment, repay you later and build up its intrastructure as well unlocking new areas to explore as florins ticks in at treasure box.\nAll in all, this game is perfect for those who want to be introduced to the franchises, if anyone chose not to do the very first game, and beloved Ezio series and Desmond's misadventure. Also, do not be fool by my amount of hours as I finished this game quite a few times on Playstation 3 game console as well its sequels.", "hours": 29.5, "username": "Grimstock", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-16", "text": "Huge improvement over the first game, which was repetitive and got boring very quickly. I spent nearly 40 hours playing this one and it had a variety of tasks and missions, more interesting areas, characters and plot. It's also a great looking game, especially for its time.", "hours": 37.5, "username": "PurpleCheshire", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-14", "text": "It's aight", "hours": 21.4, "username": "Emrys", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-14", "text": "Assassin's creed 2 is BAE <3 I loved this game alot ! The missions were interesting, the carachters were well made and just the combat overall was great i recommend this game to anyone who like assassin's creed and hasnt played this 10/10 <3", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Clementine", "products": 174, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-14", "text": "After spending more than 70 hours, i think this game is great, soundtrack is good and story is amazing, i feel that it worth to buy and play it.", "hours": 85.2, "user_id": "76561198363590821", "username": "ximangocloc_040573", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-14", "text": "Nice game", "hours": 25.7, "user_id": "76561198359369591", "username": "Jeager88", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 57, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-13", "text": "ACII is way better than the first game, but its still just not very fun to me.  The story is good and all, but the game just lacks something to keep me playing.  I made it almost to sequence 6 so I did give the game a good chance.  I'm playing with a keyboard and mouse which I don't recommend.  A controller would be way better.", "hours": 12.5, "user_id": "76561198093363183", "username": "Smackm0nk3y", "products": 464, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-13", "text": "Great gameplay, great story, doesn't get boring quickly- what else you might want from a game?", "hours": 24.1, "user_id": "76561198140713257", "username": "Solarwhale", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-13", "text": "The best series of games I've seen. All parts are great. Is clearly explains each time and era. The best!", "hours": 40.4, "username": "\ub808\uc624\ub2c8\ub2e4\uc2a4 1\uc138 Society.gg", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-12", "text": "Definitely my favorite entry in the Assassin's Creed series. If not for future desmond's irrelevant side-plot the game would be perfect. Ezio is probably one of the most likeable characters i've ever seen in a game of this genre, you feel the desire to take the story to it's completion and the game is long enough to make you feel satisfied.", "hours": 19.8, "username": "Se\u00f1or Mirak", "products": 342, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "10|10", "hours": 34.4, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198096243555", "username": "TvT csgofast.com cs.money", "products": 139, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "When AC I made a huge success, Ubisoft obviously wouldn't miss the opportunity to make a sequel. And it's amazing how much work they did to make AC II an awesome game. They made everything better, gameplay, story, the map. Just forgeting the fact that Ezio wear a Assassin suit all the time and no one cares, the game is perfect.", "hours": 15.1, "username": "John Winchester", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "Best game", "hours": 23.2, "username": "Cryomancer", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "Fun game with fluid parkour action and fighting. The ending was quite disappointing though.", "hours": 35.7, "username": "Negationix", "products": 1131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed II picks up right where the original Assassin's Creed left off (so play the first game before this one). The dual storyline continues to be interesting. ACII improves on every single aspect of it's predecessor. The story is more engaging, the gameplay has been refined to near-perfection (within the scope of the game engine), and the characters have more interesting personalities. Ezio is a charasmatic and likable protagonist that clearly grows over the years that the game covers (without sacrificing all the reasons why he's so likable).", "hours": 27.5, "username": "IronicRobot", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-10", "text": "Ma franchise", "hours": 27.5, "username": "ChrisTudy", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 58, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-10", "text": "Ezio Auditore da Firenze (hope I spelt that right) what a great character.  Many cities to explore. Classic Ubisoft tower climbing and radar vision (eagle vision). Controlls on PC great (still recommend using controller).\nCombat can be a bit weird at times and the parkour isnt as good as it used to be compared to newer assassins creed games.", "hours": 25.7, "username": "Hellinc2001", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-09", "text": "imo, the best ac game of the ezio collection. smooth fluid movement throughout the cities with no wonky controls. if you're wanting an ac game, I suggest this one over any other.", "hours": 50.7, "username": "stink", "products": 157, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-09", "text": "One of my favourite games of all time and the best AC game Ubisoft ever made.", "hours": 64.1, "user_id": "76561198076001874", "username": "The_Wolf_1989", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "A must-play Assassin's Creed.\nIt blew me away. Me and many others.\nOne of the greatest gaming experiences I've had in terms of story, character development, and gameplay.\nBest AC game of all time\nIf you're gonna play an Assassin's Creed title, start with this one.\nMy only complaint is that I can't wipe my memory to experience this masterpiece again.", "hours": 132.8, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198127618858", "username": "EpicFires", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "I've been told that the AC2 trilogy is the best in the series... I'm 118min into the game and I feel like I haven't even seend 1% of what it has to offer.", "hours": 2.0, "username": "Seijaku.kun", "products": 437, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "All in all, a pretty good game. The story can be pretty disjointed and missions are somewhat lackluster, especially near the end of the game, but the overall experience is enjoyable. The graphics hold up even this many years afterwards, and the parkour gameplay is still wonderful. Not a great stealth game either, but fun nevertheless.", "hours": 17.5, "username": "chipbloch", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "I wanted to put a review here -- if it were on a star system I'd give it like 3 stars instead of a \"do not recommend\".\nThe reason I'm saying \"do not recommend\" is not because it's a bad game -- I've heard only positive things about the game. However, if they're going to say it runs on mac, it should run on mac. And I just want to chime in with the many voices warning that it doesn't.", "hours": 5.6, "username": "Mito", "products": 638, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "AMAZING STORY", "hours": 47.4, "username": "Odar", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "Impressive game!!!\nEven though the game isn't really perfect (I mean sometimes you may meet some problems like feeling not good when you were operating the character, being annoyed by some mysterious BUG, or something you unexpect to see when you were enjoying your game), you can still be attracted by its story, the legendary of EZIO, and the pieces of EDEN. I've never been to Italy before, but the game gives me a brief concept of the country with long history. Don't miss this game, it's worthy for you to take a look!!!", "hours": 55.4, "username": "BlanFFeng", "products": 16, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "This game is one of the best maybe the best game in the series .\nIt's just great go play it .", "hours": 71.6, "username": "DuckTape666", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 59, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "Probably the best Assassin's Creed game.", "hours": 29.3, "username": "Caseilla", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "This game is one of the best maybe the best game in the series .\nIt's just great go play it .", "hours": 71.6, "username": "DuckTape666", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "Probably the best Assassin's Creed game.", "hours": 29.3, "username": "Caseilla", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "A classic, the only assassin's creed with an incredible story. For today's standards, the gameplay isn't very smooth and intuitive, but that's a very minor setback considering all the others aspects are done almost perfectly.", "hours": 19.0, "username": "BlackSymmetry", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "By far the best AC game. Good progression and great story.", "hours": 29.7, "username": "Spike_BOT", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "When this game released I almost couldn't believe how amazing it was! I enjoyed the gameplay as much as the storyline. The soundtrack composed by Jasper Kyd is unbelievable, it places you in 15th century Italy, while still keeping a small piece of modern musical influence creating a masterpiece in my opinion!\nEight years later it's just as good as I remember!!!\nLove the history lessons too\nLittle issue with the ubisoft launcher", "hours": 6.9, "user_id": "76561198161040921", "username": "Starborn", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "i'm more of an\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665man", "hours": 22.2, "username": "GOM", "products": 173, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "The introduction into the Ezio Auditore story arc, the best of the series in my opinion and also the one that establishes it as the flagship IP of Ubisoft. It vastly improves on the first game, but you can already tell that it's going to steer towards collecting\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665on the map to keep the player \"engaged\". Well, it worked for me.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "bob loblaw", "products": 551, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "The Best Assassin's Creed. Then Brotherhood and Black Flag.", "hours": 9.6, "username": "CarlPole", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "Not a single AC game sucks. So amazing.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "link1987", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 60, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-05", "text": "I'm not recommending this game just to warn people who might get the white screen error. If you have a laptop chances are that it might not work on it. In my case it didnt work. Im pretty sure i would have loved this game if i actually got a chance to play it. I've played it in the past and it was a load of fun.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "shooter3234", "products": 31, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-05", "text": "7 years old game but still great. Smooth gameplay, rich story.\nAnd... I never fall to death ;)", "hours": 61.5, "user_id": "76561198066617015", "username": "NEgg", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "The continuation Desmond Miles's story, where through the Animus, he becomes Ezio Auditore da Firenze during the height of the Renaissance in Italy. The gameplay is quite similar to the first Assassin's Creed with quite a lot of upgrades including a Villa where you may generate money to purchase items for the missions. The optional missions also includes collecting tons of stuff throughout the map(s) and solving puzzles which is quite fun for those who are interested in a challenge.\nThe free-run controls however, are still the same to the original Assassin's Creed which is quite frustrating at times, but you'll get used to it eventually. The story at times do not make sense and have plot holes due to the fact the time span is throughout several years. Overall, Assassin's Creed 2 is a good game to play.", "hours": 28.1, "username": "Hybrid_Dragon", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "You Flew Ezio,You Flew. -Leonardo da Vinci", "hours": 28.4, "username": "\ud83c\udf41Yoo Bro\ud83c\udf41", "products": 57, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "This is probably the high point for the series. The gameplay of the original game is polished and expanded upon, but the series hasn't started milking itself dry yet. If you can stand to give Ubisoft money, this is worth a buy.", "hours": 48.9, "username": "Bread Destroyer", "products": 823, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "I've played the game for almost 15 hours now and I love the story and the design but there's one thing bothering me very much. I've never raged that much of an AC game ever before. I really hate it that, for example, when you enter the Family Grave at the Villa, you need to parkour your way to the end. Seems fun right? Well, the game just turns the camera right at the moment you want to jump, so that the chance is very big that you jump against a wall and fall all the way down and need to start over again. And than you're down there, and the timer is going on, second time, you make the first jump but at the second it turns AGAIN. So you fall down again. And that for like 30 times. Oh, and overall I really hate the freerun system in this AC, never hated it so much in any other AC, and I've played 5 or 6 of them.  Despite that, I really reconmend playing this game.", "hours": 17.0, "user_id": "76561198259232190", "username": "PlatVoetGezicht", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "The story is AMAZING and the gameplay is prety smoth.", "hours": 41.2, "user_id": "76561198351848714", "username": "Calin", "products": 18, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "One of the best Assassins Creed Games i must say!!!\nWell a little bit bugs but hey! Take a look at Syndicade when it first came out\nWould give it 9.7 of 10", "hours": 45.5, "user_id": "76561198167359875", "username": "ErKis csgolive.com", "products": 26, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "The number of mechanics this game improves upon is vast compared to the original. There is a vast amount of weapons to experience, and play with. The main charater is memoriable, the side characters are enjoyable to listen to, and the game captures the beauty of Italy very well. The music is solid, but not memoriable. This iteration of AC adds a lot of little things that AC1 was missing to keep the side quest from getting too boring. However, the game screams that it was meant for a controller.", "hours": 23.4, "username": "Ivory Fox Boy", "products": 313, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-03", "text": "\u6253\u5f00\u542f\u52a8\u5668\u4e4b\u540e\u5c31\u51fa\u73b0\u767d\u5c4f\uff0c\u4f60\u8fd9\u8ba9\u6211\u600e\u4e48\u73a9", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Sean_zsy", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 61, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-03", "text": "I love this game!!! It has challenged me in a way no other game has. As the challenges get more and more frustrating, the wins get so much sweeter. The storyline is fun to follow and the characters are amazing to play as/ get to know. I would definiteely recommend this game!!!", "hours": 6.4, "user_id": "76561198161433158", "username": "whichwitchdoctor", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-03", "text": "Amazingly fun and interesting game!!!", "hours": 35.4, "username": "Lion-Pride", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-03", "text": "This game is so fine in my opinion is the besc in AC series!\n10/10", "hours": 22.1, "username": "Decu", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "7 years and still want to play it again. This is my TOP 1 game ever. 10/10", "hours": 35.4, "username": "SCRAPPER", "products": 1341, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "The best of AC franchise", "hours": 12.2, "username": "Dean Dean", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "Really wanted to try and get into the series the right way, but I cannot even run the game. The game will freeze trying to get into an animus at the very beginning. I've run the game in compatability mode for windows 7, vista, and XP, but no luck. I have tried everything.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "rezoLute", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "It has been 7 years since I have played this game (originally on the XBOX 360). I decided to pick up all of the AC games to play through them all on PC before Origins came out.\nAll I can say is I can't believe I forgot how great this game is. Seriously. This is a game that, if came out today, would still easily be a best seller. The story is well done, the game world is just incredible and vast, and it feels so alive!\nIf you are looking to get lost in a game over the summer then I highly advise this game, especially if you haven't played it! It is a must for every game collection! I would also say that the price it is during the Summer Sale is pretty much a steal as well!", "hours": 22.0, "username": "TheForFeeF", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "An amazing story following Desmond Miles and his ancestor, Ezio Auditore Da Firenze. This game is the second chapter to Desmond's adventure of the hunt for the pieces of eden and the 'temple'. Following to the escape of the Abstergo Industries, Desmond and Lucy manage to escape to a warehouse where the other modern assassins are hanging out. With the new and updated Animus, as Rebecca explains, \"Animus 2.0\", Desmond is set to explore his italian ancestor in the late 1400's to learn from him. In Assassin's Creed 2, Ezio, the protagonist, is a charming young man with desire for revenge. After the occurance of his father and two brothers death, Ezio builds a strong hatred towards the ones he thought were friends. With his father's Assassin robes and a note written to him about the world of Assassins and their goals, Ezio begins  his quest to hunt down every man responsible for the execution of his father. With those responsible dead, Ezio learns more and more of his enemies and the reason behind everything that ever was and ever will be.\nI suggest playing this game first if you want to play his trilogy, as there are 3 games to Ezio's life.", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Gogsley", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 62, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "7 years later,still one of my favorite games.\n10/10", "hours": 60.4, "user_id": "76561198020424270", "username": "A$AP", "products": 143, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
