{"product_id": "33230", "page": 79, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-22", "text": "My favorite AC game to date.\nHas a great atmosphere and Renaissance Italy is a gorgeous setting.\nDespite it being an old game and having some flaws, it is still playable and enjoyable.\nThe story was also very nice - amazing, combined with the rest of the trilogy as you see Ezio's transition from a child with a quest for vengeance to a fully grown man trying to uncover the secrets of the Master Assassin Alta\u03car.\nA memorable game and a must have for fans of the franchise.", "hours": 30.0, "username": "Lefter", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
