{"product_id": "33230", "page": 83, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-09", "text": "Historically deep and very interesting plot, full of conspiracy theories.\nBig, open, beautiful cities with lots of things to discover.\nVery fun main objectives which introduces new mechanics and fun \"toys\" :).\nGood character development.\nLots of collectibles which are actually rewarding.\nNew economy. You can purchase equipment and more.\nGraphics are also pretty good for it's age.\nVERY easy combat and stupid AI.\nControls sometimes become frustrating and let you to make an unintended move such as jumping down a building or killing a civilian etc. But you get used to it as you play.\nUbisoft managed to fix almost every problem with the first game and uncovered the true potential of the Assassin's Creed series. ACII is the true representative of the series; it is a masterpiece of it's time.", "hours": 23.8, "username": "Sir Legar", "products": 546, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 83, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-09", "text": "Assassin\u2019s Creed\u00ae 2 is the follow-up to the title that became the fastest-selling new IP in video game history. The highly anticipated title features a new hero, Ezio Auditore da Firenze, a young Italian noble, and a new era, the Renaissance.\nAwesome game with nice cinematics and roleplay. good graphics with a wide depth. Story mode that will take u far back in the future.", "hours": 97.1, "username": "Davva", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
