{"product_id": "33230", "page": 86, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-29", "text": "Such and Amazing game, I mean AMAZINGGGGGG.\nFirst things first, it felt so good running around with the ambient music, it totally gave life to the diferrent cities. Everytime you came back to a city to do something you feel a strong noastalgic feeling, even if only 30 minutes passed. 9/10 Soundtrack.\nI don't usually complete the entire it of the game, sidequests I will most likely leave them undone but the main story, ohhhh ohhh that is such a golden point of the game. Just gold, its intense and combined with the beautiful scenery and music your gonna call sick to work the next day. Well I don't have that option but it was 3 days, sleeping,  working, playing, eating something in between to keep yourself alive and playing again.\nEzio and desmond are such a good characters for you to follow along, that makes the game be worth it.\nThat ending, that twist, that feeling it leaves you \"I need moreeeeeeeee\". So good!!", "hours": 21.5, "user_id": "76561198293380406", "username": "MaLGooee", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 86, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-29", "text": "Pros:\n1. Blast to the past if you are an old assassin's creed fan\n2. One of the best AC games available because the Assassin is amazing\n3. Easily controlled\nCons:\n1. None\n2. None\n3. None\n4. There isnt supposed to be a number 4", "hours": 6.2, "username": "Eclitops", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 86, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-03-29", "text": "I bought this to play on an early 2015 Macbook Pro Retina running MacOS Sierra, and had some pretty big problems right out the box.\nUbisoft requires you to play this game through their UPlay launcher. This launcher shows nothing but a white box to me. It is still possible to log in but you have to move your cursor around until you find a text input field, hope it's the username field, enter your username, then hit TAB to enter your password. If this works, the launcher will bring up another white box and you have to blindly click around until you (hopefully) hit play in the bottom right corner.\nOnce the game starts, you may only be able to see half the screen, as it will be shifted halfway up your monitor. If you get the correct half of the screen, or if you know which keyboard keys to press, you may be able to get into graphics options and change the resolution. This sometimes fixes your problem, but at this point I figured it would be better to quit and get a refund from Steam, so I don't have any info on the gameplay.\nUbisoft has seriously pooped the bed on this one. If you have a Mac and you're thinking of testing your luck, just remember that you can request a refund from Steam within two weeks of purchase as long as you have fewer than 2 hours of playtime.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561198322134420", "username": "tomasgotchi", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 86, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-29", "text": "BUT NOT IF YOU DONT HAVE A MID END PC", "hours": 1.4, "compensation": "Product received for free", "user_id": "76561198323380278", "username": "eliottnaeslund", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 86, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-29", "text": "I recommend the game, just not on PC.\nThe game itself is fun, but is barely able to run on a rig that's more than capable of running modern games on high settings.  No option of tweaking graphics options other than what's in the game. Some people are able to get 60fps consistently whereas I'm having trouble getting 20 at any point in the game.\nI'm hearing horror stories about the next few AC titles, so I'll probably not buy them and waste my money on a 20fps experience. It's a sad day for the PC MasterRace.", "hours": 28.5, "username": "Purge", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
