{"product_id": "33230", "page": 101, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-30", "text": "This game is very good. It's challenging I'll admit but the game manages to mix that with fun and atmosphere. My only problem is the unnecessary missions that add nothing to the story and how the control symbols aren't normal keyboard keys, but instead are weird symbols that have no correlation to the action being done.\nOverall, I recommend you get this game if you like puzzles and a great story.", "hours": 25.3, "user_id": "76561198088038722", "username": "GALAXY_", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 101, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-29", "text": "I love this game, I did a speedrun pretty much and completed it in just under 7 hours. It is a huge improvment on the original Assassin's Creed because it has some depth to the story line and isn't just Kill and Repeat. I played this game for the first time on a PS3 a few years ago and instantly enjoyed the freerun style so when I signed up to steam and quite recently bought it, it is almost impossible for me to give it a negative review. I feel like the people who don't enjoy this series have either picked up the wrong genre or are not willing to sit down and put a good few hours into a game. 11/10 would play again.", "hours": 6.2, "username": "WHG | Trxsta", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 101, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-29", "text": "Fantastic \"stealth\" action-adventure video game. The story is probably the best and least stupid it has been in the series, but however hasn't aged perfectly. I would say Assassin's Creed IV Black Flag is better to a very certain extent. This game, atmospherically, nails it. Italy is beautiful (aged by today's standards) and traversing it is really fun. I played this first in 2012 on PS3, but after playing a game as fluid as Assassin's Creed Unity, I certainly wish for the new traversing mechanics. This one feels somewhat stiff. Combat is crap for the most part. The game is VERY easy too, and combat is more of an annoyance than anything. Music is really good. Characters and voice acting are both great.\n8/10", "hours": 20.7, "username": "Rocketman \u262d", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
