{"product_id": "33230", "page": 102, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-26", "text": "Honestly, I mediocre game for me. I get the hype and I understand that this game deserves to be considered one of the best games made, but honestly I didn't enjoy it that much. Overall, I would still recommend this game, because I realize that many of my friends love it, and other may have a better time with their experience. But I honestly found flaws with the parkour system, because often times, it just doesn't work out for me, and I find myself constantly jumping off roofs and high buildings automatically, leading to my demise, or a restart of the mission. Also, I feel that the combat system just doesn't offer what an average gamer would want: simple, efficient, and easy when combatting crowds of guards. But overall, really great storyline, great character designs, and very in-depth feel to the game. 7/10", "hours": 26.2, "username": "Crayon Shin Chan", "products": 109, "early_access": false}
