{"product_id": "33230", "page": 103, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "This was my first AC game, so I came in with almost no expectation. Through the first like 15 hours, the game kept blowing me away with cool gadgets, excellent combat system and a great cast of characters. However, I felt that the mission were getting very repetitive and the lines were getting a bit cliche. Overall, I think that you should definitely give this one a go first if you are interested in AC simply because of the story and the visual itself( I thought that the game has aged exceptionally well).", "hours": 35.5, "user_id": "76561198330512416", "username": "hungtinhphuong01", "products": 40, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 103, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "Never played any AC before besides Brotherhood a few years ago on Xbox 360, saw this on sale, picked it up and had so much fun, honestly from beginning to end, I always involved and intrigued and while I did get frustrated at times, once I finally figured out how to solve a riddle or go undetected, it was so much fun, one of the best campaigns I've ever played and definitly recommend, Ezio is such a fun character to follow. 10/10 Recommend.", "hours": 20.8, "username": "RK^", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
