{"product_id": "33230", "page": 103, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-20", "text": "For me, Assassins Creed II stands as the peak of the entire series.\nIt is a quantum leap from the clunky previous game, bringing all the immersive environments and great story telling, and combining it with a slick and fluid combat system.\nThe plot is excellent, although it does lose pace somewhat in the later stages of the game as there are large time jumps, but the DLC goes go some way to remedy this.\nThe free-running mechanics are simple and easy to use, and make you feel like an absolute master of the art within minutes. If I had one small complaint - less timed free running puzzles please?\nIf you only ever play one game in the AC collection - make it this one.", "hours": 72.8, "user_id": "76561198077914319", "username": "WantedEye", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
