{"product_id": "33230", "page": 121, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-21", "text": "I cannot recommend for one simple reason - they botched up the mouse movement.. The mouse feels very wonky when trying to play this game, for the brief time I was trying to tweak and play I really felt like I had to fight it... it seems like a great deal of mouse acceleration and unfortunately there is absolutely NOTHING you can do to remedy this if you want to play with keyboard and mouse. Outside of this it looks fine, and should be perfectly playable with a controller. But not having good functionality with a mouse in a PC game is an instant no for me here, especially when the first game had it working perfectly fine.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198088034397", "username": "Beast", "products": 115, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 121, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-21", "text": "Well this game is probably the best game in the AC series (personally though I prefer syndicate). It had a compelling backstory for our protagonist (No spoilers!). It featured many historical figures such as Leonardo da Vinci, Niccol\u00f2 Machiavelli, Caterina Sforza etc. The parkour is the best it\u2019s even been. The melee combat is a bit just like mashing 2 toys together sometimes for my liking. Overall the best AC game!\nTl: DR\nPros\n*Great parkour\n*Good story\n*Features famous people and their history\n*A really cool tomb system (basically like the new tomb raider games)\nCons\n*Occasional bugs in combat\n*Made by Ubisoft (I\u2019m hoping Watch Dogs 2 (When I get it) will redeem Ubisoft in my eyes)\nI\u2019m giving it a\u2026.\n8.75/10\nP.S If you are planning to start playing some of the AC series, start with AC2.", "hours": 23.2, "username": "JediJimbo1", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
