{"product_id": "33230", "page": 132, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-26", "text": "I bought this game a couple years ago, having not really payed much attention to the series before. After playing it for a couple hours, I bought the previous game, and the next two as well. Needless to say, I was impressed. I've never played any other game like Assassins Creed before, and it's really a unique franchise, even if there's little variety between each instalment.\nGameplay wise, this game has very few flaws. There's almost no glitches, and the combat, while not as easy/smooth as later games, has no problems.\nThe story is one of the best of the series, though I haven't played most of the new instalments to fully compare.\nI recommend this game to anyone curious about the series. While the first game is alright, I think that this game gives a better introduction into the gameplay/style of this series.", "hours": 119.9, "user_id": "76561198158572731", "username": "jimmydartist", "products": 223, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 132, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-26", "text": "Ciao fans!\nGreetings fans!", "hours": 32.8, "username": "Ajit pai", "products": 245, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 132, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-26", "text": "omg a classic so much love xoxo luv u ezio", "hours": 19.0, "username": "Quinn", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 132, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-26", "text": "Okay, to bw honest I bought this on accident thinking it was with the older Ezio. However, I cannot complain about this accident... infact, I'm thrilled that I accidently recieved this! The story is unbelieveably addictive, the time our protagonist is in is mind blowing, and the system is incredible!\nTo be honest, I never enjoyed any side quests... but, the game makes me want to tackle anything that they throw at me!\nI mean, I can't be bias... but in my opinion I see nothing wrong with this game... well, except how we must download a silly launcher and must translate the buttons/moves... but this earned my 9.5/10! I would recommend this game if you are curious about Ezio and a great open parkour game", "hours": 6.9, "username": "Detare", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
