{"product_id": "33230", "page": 138, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-24", "text": "To begin with this game is one of my all time favorites. The grafics and gameplay lack a little in comparison to newer games. The story on the other hand is one of the most intense and is beautifully supported by the amazing soundtrack. Ezios transition from a spoiled know-it-all to a stone cold killer is brutal and fascinating at the same time. To anyone who for some reason has not played it yet and likes the renaissance italian setting, marvelous OST and intense fights, should definitely check this one out.", "hours": 11.6, "user_id": "76561198028528537", "username": "<sob> nomad", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 138, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-24", "text": "This was the first Assassin's Creed game that I played.  I got it on sale for $9.99. Totally worth the amount I paid. I've played this game for 72 hours and I have not even finished all of the side quests and missions. This game was a big success to me, despite the fact that it launches through Uplay. I would recommend this game for it's story and length of gameplay. (If you take your time and not rush through missions.) :)", "hours": 75.8, "user_id": "76561198077260307", "username": "CogWorkOwl", "products": 115, "early_access": false}
