{"product_id": "33230", "page": 140, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-23", "text": "This game, in my opinion, perfects the Assassin's Creed formula. The story is really engaging, and I absolutely love the depiction of Renaissance Italy. The assassinations themselves felt fun and challenging to play out. There are a huge variety of weapons available in the game, letting you carry out missions in different ways. The side activity of renovating a village is also a lot of fun - it is cool to see the area change over time as you acquire more wealth. The game may be old, but it still feels fresh and fun to play.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Moarliek", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
