{"product_id": "33230", "page": 141, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-23", "text": "Pros\n-Good story\n-Most compelling protagonist in the series\n-Huge feature additions compared to AC1\n-Get to make Leonardo da Vinci do tedious busy work\n-\"It's a-me, Mario\"\nCons\n-Present day storyline is cringey, especially in hindsight after seeing its conclusion in AC3\n-Can't make Desmond and Shaun fight to the death\nConclusion\nMissing some features that became vital later in the series, but still the best AC storyline and a huge improvement over its predecessor in every way. Also, muh nostalgia. 9/10", "hours": 69.3, "username": "\u0f44\u0f44\u0f0b\u0f54\u0f53\u0f74\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f0d", "products": 272, "early_access": false}
