{"product_id": "33230", "page": 146, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-28", "text": "One of my friends is a huge fan of the Assassin's Creed franchise and he made me buy the game during Steam Summer sale and play it. And I've to say, I'm glad he made me do it.\nThe story was awesome. Kept me hooked for 50hrs - That says something. And the ending was really amazing! Totally worth the 50hrs.\nWhat really impressed me is how they've tried to blend historical and biblical events in the story and puzzles. (Also, some greek legends.)\nReminds me of Dan Brown books. Especially the glyphs. Many times while solving the glyphs I felt I would've appreciated them more if I had more knowlegde about the mentioned events.\nBut that didn't affect the overall gameplay experience though. Since the glyphs is just an optional side mission. Which unlocks\n- which again, took me by surprise :)\nPS. I've already decided to buy\nand\nthis winter sale.", "hours": 49.6, "user_id": "76561198183290835", "username": "masquerade", "products": 185, "early_access": false}
