{"product_id": "33230", "page": 147, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-22", "text": "This is where I started playing the Assassin's Creed franchise and I fell in love with this game. Although a few yeas old the graphics are still pretty impressive. This is probably the best Assassin's Creed game. It implements puzzles and killing. Pretty weird combination but they perfected it. (Except for the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t \"assassinate without being detected\" \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t.)", "hours": 65.6, "username": "lil jizz", "products": 95, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-21", "text": "I picked this up in 2013, didn't play it until about a month ago...\nThis game is incredible, while not the graphical quality of a next gen game it certainly had me hooked.\nI never really was into assassin's creed when it first came out, but boy am i glad i had picked this up in a sale.\nThis is the godfather of all assassin's creed games, with a storyline that actually made me gasp, fun gameplay and cool content.\ntl;dr grab dis its good", "hours": 55.3, "username": "Dan Greene", "products": 216, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-21", "text": "One of the classics, brilliant.", "hours": 41.7, "username": "^ \ud835\udd04\ud835\udd31\ud835\udd2f\ud835\udd26\ud835\udd29\ud835\udd29\ud835\udd1e ^", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-21", "text": "Story seemed to be interesting, but my god those controls.  Even after plugging a controller in, I felt I was fighting the input manager more than I was any challange the game presented.  Exceedingly frustrating and with so many better alternatives out there, I cannot recommend.", "hours": 2.4, "username": "Capashin", "products": 443, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-20", "text": "By far one of my favorites games. I grew up in Italy so seeing all the Italian scenery gave me a sense of nostalgia I enjoyed throughout the gameplay.\nThe soundtrack is brilliant; the graphics amazing, all things considered; and although not extremely challenging, the battles are enjoyable. The plot is very interesting and the characters encountered even more so (I freaking ADORE Leonardo).\nSide effects of playing this for too long: Makes you wanna learn parkour.", "hours": 66.0, "username": "shiraiphoenix", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-19", "text": "I played this when it first came out on PS3 and loved it. Just bought it and tried to play it today and Uplay wont let me log in. It's a fantastic game, but the cancer that is Uplay will not let me enjoy it.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Saihchotic", "products": 490, "early_access": false}
