{"product_id": "33230", "page": 148, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-15", "text": "In my opinion, this is the best AC game of the series. It provided a nice story, with nice graphics that do not require a hefty PC to run.\nI love this game every time I play it.", "hours": 28.1, "username": "Colonel Chris", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 149, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-12", "text": "The best game in the franchise. I love pretty much everything about it. It\u2019s got my favourite videogame soundtrack of all time and one of the best video game locations ever with Venice and Florence.  The attention to detail and a realistic recreation of those cities during that time period really help to make the game world feel real. Ezio is one of my favourite video game protagonists, he is very likable and watching him grow as a person throughout the game was beautifully done, just amazing character development. The story is gripping from start to finish, you really get invested in it. The parkour and combat is brilliant of course as well as all the other small gameplay touches. I just love the game it\u2019s really a work of art.\n10/10 (Masterpiece)", "hours": 20.2, "username": "David0vi\u0107", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 149, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-12", "text": "bought this once before. Ubisoft refused to work properly", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Brick", "products": 73, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 149, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-12", "text": "Pros:\n- Fantastic story which consists of great character development and purpose, making it intriguing and interesting.\n- Good gameplay (although the combat could have been better if the combo kill was added in this game rather than ACB, doing so could possibly make the combat to easy, therefore one could say that AC2's more challenging gameplay is better).\n- Decent open world consisting of multiple cities and challenges (for those seeking to acheive full game completion).\n- Great time period.\n- Ezio has charisma, charm, intelligence, skill etc... A VERY likable character and by far the best Assassin, in my opinion.\nCons:\n- The combat and general game mechanics system isn't as developed as that of ACB or ACR, and is still very plain and simple. But then again, this is hardly a con, what else could we have expected from Ubisoft when this game came out?\n- I'm Italian, and the voice acting is quite cringy at times. The accents are stereotypical and their pronounciation of Italian words is also pretty bad at times.\nIn short, this game is an absolute masterpiece. Wherever it lacks in graphics or game play, it makes up for in story.\nRating: 9.5/10.", "hours": 105.0, "username": "DSprite", "products": 110, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 149, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-10", "text": "Ezio for life love the game I think I'm getting the ezio collection \ud83d\udc4d\ud83d\udc4c", "hours": 4.3, "user_id": "76561198294252465", "username": "alek.guerrero9943", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
