{"product_id": "33230", "page": 153, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-17", "text": "Still the best Assassin's Creed, and I've played most of them.  When I think about what made this game so special, I think about these five reasons:\n1.  Ezio & story.  Ezio is by far the strongest lead character the series has ever had, and the story is engaging right from the start all the way until the mindblowing ending.  Other characters are great as well.\n2.  Glyphs. These cryptic puzzles are scattered all around the cities, hidden from plain sight but revealed using your special vision.  They're fascinating, creepy as hell, and addictive.  And each one you find contributes towards an important piece of information in the story.  It's glaring that they scrapped these in later AC installments.\n3.  Music.  Jesper Kyd created the soundtrack and it's nothing short of stellar.  YouTube it if you don't believe me.\n4.  Challenge and pacing.  Progression and difficulty feel just right.\n5.  You get to\n.\nThis isn't just the best Assassin's Creed, it's a fantastic and memorable game on its own right; so enjoyable that it made AC1 feel like a tech demo in comparison.  If you could only play one Assassin's Creed, play this one.", "hours": 5.5, "username": "Dapper Tardigrade", "products": 600, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 154, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-17", "text": "Very old memories returning <3", "hours": 0.9, "username": "No Dope | csgopositive.com", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 154, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-17", "text": "So, now I've played the game for roughly 100 hours, 100%'ed it twice hehe. And I gotta say, the story was mind-blowing towards the end of the game. For the price this would be a 9/10. Before playing through this I also played trough the first Assassins Creed game, might have 100%'ed it, but still, every change they made from that game to this game was beatiful. I even got surprised when I found out I could fight with only the hidden blade, not like in the first one.\n9/10", "hours": 99.0, "username": "Slump", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 154, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-16", "text": "This is the first AC game I've played - had a lot of fun with it. Good story. The open world approach suits this game very well, although the side missions do end up being a little repetitive after a while. As some others have said, it's a bit of a lazy port, and there are a few occasions when you curse the camera, as it gets locked into a more dramatic angle unexpectedly and certain tricky moments, causing you to fluff up otherwise easy moves. It's also apparent in the menus, which are a pain to navigate with a mouse. But overall worthwhile. It hasn't convinced me that jumping into haystacks from tall buildings is a good idea yet, though...!\nEdit: After playing later titles, the clunky menu navigation is presumably by choice... quite a chore to navigate.", "hours": 49.8, "user_id": "76561198006611232", "username": "Martocticvs", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
