{"product_id": "33230", "page": 155, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-09", "text": "after first part, all i had were tons of questions, that had \" the f-c-u-k\" in it, like \"what the..., why the..., how... what... \" etc.\nSecond chapter gave some answers.\nbut that's not the point.\nyou kno, there's a game you love, which is\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665really. everyone has that - one of favs, but generally and honestly -\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\ni wouldn't say that AC2 is\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 It could've been better.\nbut it is one of my favourites.\nnuff said.\n10 \"Insieme per la vittoria\" out of 10.", "hours": 40.7, "username": "bo77om", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 155, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-09", "text": "One word I can describe to this game: Fun\nThe story picked up where Assassin's Creed left off. The combat system is much better than last time, enemy HPs are now shown, you can explore more cities, detection meter is balanced (unlike the first game), enemies can now counter-attack making the game more challenging, chests are scattered all over, enemies search the area first before giving up, and citizens are more reactive to unusual activities.\nThe negative side is controls. You can easily lose control or make actions that you never meant (such as jumping to your death without pressing jump).\nOverall, the game well-balanced, calm in Venice, has a good story, and definitely fun to kill those templars.", "hours": 27.4, "username": "ridon428", "products": 559, "early_access": false}
