{"product_id": "33230", "page": 156, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-06", "text": "It's another Assasins Creed game, this time, something.", "hours": 27.7, "user_id": "76561197970701643", "username": "Liam Neeson Punching Wolves", "products": 1160, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 156, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-06", "text": "This is the game Assassin's Creed should have been. It's smooth, quick, fun, and has a genuinely likeable and human character. He's not as interesting as he might be, but neither are actual people. Whether shooting close to reality without consideration for whether reality is, itself, interesting can be called a good thing is a question that has been at the heart of literary analysis for generations, but for those who come in for the gameplay, which is excellent, the story will certainly not detract from it overmuch, and for those who come in for story, well... hopefully you'll stay for the gameplay.", "hours": 38.5, "username": "Areus", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 156, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-06", "text": "Quality bugs found in the game.\nPause game to go for dinner\nReturn back to see archers spawning.\nTouch archer\nGame crashes\nHighly recommended to people who loves to craash their games.", "hours": 39.7, "user_id": "76561198006810279", "username": "Fakkong", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 156, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-06", "text": "Shortly:\nPros\n- Good story\n- Italy atmosphere, wonderful\n- Garrison and its upgrading\n- Parkour (obviously)\n- Traveling through the cities\nCons:\n- Sometimes the camera act wierd, but it could be my fault :)\n- Ubisoft game manager and some troubles with it\nRecommend it.", "hours": 10.4, "user_id": "76561198018523777", "username": "Dorreah", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 156, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-05", "text": "One of the best AC games. AC2 was a truly involving single player storyline, with Ezio's character definitely appealing to the player. Graphics are of course dated & the mechanics are nothing special, but the story in itself makes the game definitely worth buying.\nProbably best using a controller for this one.\n9/10", "hours": 29.5, "username": "tomfordgt", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
