{"product_id": "33230", "page": 167, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-06", "text": "it has a couple bugs and uplay blows, but it has a nice story. hard to get used to the mechanics because i played newer games, where things like ledge grabbing are much more refined. the graphics have aged well, the enivonments are beautiful. 3/5.", "hours": 25.2, "username": "fraggered", "products": 1448, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 167, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-06", "text": "The best game in what still is the finest trilogy of games I've ever had the pleasure of playing. Beautiful storytelling, incorporating various historical figures of the time, such as Caterina Sforza, Niccolo Machiavelli and Leonardo Da Vinci. All whilst being captivated by some of the most sensational scenery of Renaissance Italy.\nYou can also fly the famous Da Vinci Flying Machine to kick guards off of buildings.\n10/10 - Would Da Vinci Kick again.", "hours": 9.7, "user_id": "76561198008714804", "username": "McCheesebiscuit", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 167, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-06", "text": "Didn't expect the game to be as good as it was. The stpry was fun and kept me playing till the end. The DLC parts were kinds of boring and consisted of repeated action. Since i got the delux edition, there was no way to skip it, but you are not missing anything from the DLC. Core game is good though, i just find the controlls to get a bit annoying at times.", "hours": 35.9, "user_id": "76561198141784246", "username": "MrZouron", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 167, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-06", "text": "A diamond in Assassin's Creed franchise", "hours": 19.0, "user_id": "76561198115718083", "username": "navas94", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "This is the second to best AC game, no doubt... 9.8/10.0\n- Florence, Venice, Toscana, Vennetto... this game is a feast for explorers\n- The story is brilliant\n- The diversity of activities brings a lot of alternative things to do\n- The music is great\nCriticism (if any)\n- AC Brotherhood is the part II of this game, but if you add them, the score break records\n- It really has no other issues, it's just AC IV Black Flag is slightly bigger/better", "hours": 26.4, "user_id": "76561198109858979", "username": "Kalimonde", "products": 145, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "Buy a controller for this... Also \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 U play.", "hours": 8.2, "user_id": "76561198149599629", "username": "Derp", "products": 88, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "Es el que mas me encanta de todos <3", "hours": 23.1, "user_id": "76561198074252988", "username": "Kiyomi", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "there are many improvements all over the board, and plenty of new mechanics and necessary changes from the first title in the series. Assassin\u2019s Creed II is a solid title, and the first of a trilogy ( AC II, Brotherhood, Revelations ) that is considered by many the best story arc in the whole series. It is a highly regarded title in the series, especially if you follow up with the next two games in succession.", "hours": 26.3, "username": "Borba", "products": 3226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "Ok game, main quest needs spice.", "hours": 21.7, "user_id": "76561198030712944", "username": "jepeli", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-04", "text": "An improvement on the original in almost every way. Still a little too long, and the cities, although massive, look a little copy and paste. Nevertheless a great game with a compelling story and fun free running antics!", "hours": 31.9, "username": "Foreverseeking", "products": 1604, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-04", "text": "By far the best game in the series and still worth a play in 2016.\nGreat missions, with only a few boring (but short) fillers sparingly thrown in.\nGreat plot and interesting characters.\nSO MUCH TO DO: Tonnes of great side missions, TONNES of collectables and Tonnes of side objectives.\nAll of these fold seamlessly into the game, just feels like one massive sandbox with great progression.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "The Hacker Known As 4Chan", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-04", "text": "I've played all the Assassin's Creed up to Unity, and let me just say that this game is very much worth it, I'd get it even if it was 50$ or more, because that's how much it's worth. Assassin's Creed II doesn't just give you an amazing impact on both story and gameplay, but it also sharpens your mind. That's if you're like me and try to become a true Assassin and plan your attacks and improvise to the environment like a true Assassin. I see Assassin's Creed as a really violent jigsaw puzzle, the way how you plan to take down your enemy without being seen. I've been introduced to Assassin's Creed in the most uncommon way. I started out on Assassin's Creed II: Discorvery for the Nintendo DS. After the 2D climbing and assassinations, I merged onto Assassin's Creed III, not knowing anything at all. I'll admit I wasn't too good at the game due to me being very young and not caring about anything. But over time I learned to master all the essentials making all my Assassinations and plans much easier, Assassin's Creed 1 and 2 REALLY helped with that. I HIGHLY reccommend this game to all who wish to become a true Assassin, and to have a blast of their lives.\nFinal Verdict: 8.7/10 Very good game. Worth replaying.", "hours": 8.3, "username": "Kawaii Cheezburger", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-04", "text": "Good game but the last sequence was just too easy. I got the feeling that they made that last part of the game just like if they were making the final of a movie. You just sit and watch what's happening. But it's a very interesting story and the scenarios are just amazing. I love Italy and I need to visit Florence and Venice so badly. Can't wait to have Brotherhood installed to explore Rome!", "hours": 71.4, "username": "miNa", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 168, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-04", "text": "that moment when you listen to the lute suit guys for the first time and realize...their singing a song about you...also ITSA ME MARIO! well played ubisoft well played...", "hours": 24.4, "username": "Gravity", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "Double plus good", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Sajuuk-Khar", "products": 406, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "I originally illegally downloaded this game and played it, but bought it on steam to support the developers. I've heard a lot of people say that Assassin's Creed II is their favorite, I don't know that this is my favorite, but it is definitely a solid entry into the series. If you're wanting to start playing the Assassin's Creed series, I think you should skip the first one (it's not very good and is very repetitive), and just start with this one.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198044339289", "username": "Davidc145", "products": 849, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "Easily the best game in the series.\nWhereas the first game felt dull and repetative, Assasin's Creed picks up the pace with everything. The music, the atmosphere, the characters and especially Ezio are magnificient.\nIf you are thinking about buying an Assassin's Creed game, this is the one you want. If you are a completist like me, you'll get a bit more out of the games in sense of story and background, however that is not necessary at all.", "hours": 68.6, "user_id": "76561198011944356", "username": "Verzada", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-03", "text": "This game is for everyone who enjoys stealth- and assassingames with great stories.\nIt is better than all its descendants, the last whole game with the unique puppeteer control and the ultimate Assassins-Creed feeling to it. Maybe with the exceptions of Assassins Creed Revelations and Brotherhood, but those are more like DLCs.\nI can only recommend it, especially to those people, who started with a later version of the series and are terribly disappointed:\nYes, the franchise was \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed, but it was awesome once!\nGIVE IT A CHANCE!", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Marekatt", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-07-02", "text": "i want a refund of my 9.99 because I cant even get my game to lauch someone help or STEAM give me a refund", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561198285475624", "username": "Lobster500", "products": 9, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 169, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-02", "text": "Well compared to the first installment... This is absolutely fantastic. Awesome plot. No glitches so far< Thank God for that>.\n7 Sequences completed and still very much addicted to it!.", "hours": 53.4, "user_id": "76561198236637926", "username": "El' Panda", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
