{"product_id": "33230", "page": 170, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "I got this as a gift and it's a very awesome game. Trully recommend it for the thrill of fighting.", "hours": 5.5, "user_id": "76561198091049415", "username": "Miel", "products": 31, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 170, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2, does everything a sequel needs to do. it added to the gameplay, expanded the story in multiple directions and created a highly memorable character in the form of Ezio Auditore da Firenze.\nIt also lead to such apparent popularity that Ubisoft decided to flog the series into oblivion thereafter with yearly sequels including 2 spin-offs to Ezio's particular story (which where still decent if formulaic).\nThe inclusion of multiplayer as well as an on-the-go manual and historical checkbook, and puzzle minigames made the game enjoyable not only by increasing the rich wealth of historical lore but adding much needed breaks from running over rooftops, causing tiles to crash to the streets below...\nThis and Brotherhood (it's first sequel and second part of Ezio's trilogy) are the best of the Assassin's Creed series, partly because the game was still fresh and partly because the setting of Renaissance Italy was one of the most fascinating areas of history to explore.\nHighly recommend - will likely become a Classic.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "Deisophia", "products": 631, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 170, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "If you play any stealth games, assassin's creed 2 is definitely one of the best (if not the best) of the series.\nhighly recommend for anyone that likes stealth/assassination games", "hours": 34.7, "username": "Noobie_2", "products": 265, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 170, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "This game is the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 for such an old game the landscapes and settings are much more beautiful than even current gen games. Whilst the missions can get repetitive, it's still fun to just unwind, explore, climb buildings and collect random\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to make your mansion look cooler. The story is A+ and very satisfying as you further unravel the corruption behind the Italian government right down to it's core, dealing with each enemy at the end of each chapter that resolves one sequence and kickstarts the next.", "hours": 53.0, "username": "luca", "products": 98, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 170, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "A good game, nice storyline and a lot of different things to do (when you're done with the story).\nYou can also collect different sorts of items so that makes the game extra challenging and adds new goals to it.", "hours": 50.9, "user_id": "76561198177867918", "username": "frox6216", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
