{"product_id": "33230", "page": 173, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-23", "text": "This game will keep you busy for hours. Even longer if you go for the feathers and other side quests or just like parkour. If you've ever wanted to throw people off of tall buildings and then watch as people crowd around the body in both amazement and shock, this is your game. If you've never wanted to do any of that, then what's wrong with you? Kidding. Seriously, get this game, you won't regret it.\n9/10", "hours": 58.9, "username": "Take A Bow", "products": 248, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 173, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-23", "text": "There are a few problems i have with the game\n1: The \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t i had to go through to get the damn thing to start (I ended up refunding and re-buying it to get a different code which fixed the startup problem)\n2: The camrea angles, i know that third person games tend to have camera angles that are rather inconvienient but wat i'm talking about are the \"fixed\" camera angles such as in the Assassin's tombs or the Templar's hideouts. I find them very annoying and they will chang how the controls work depending on the angle\naside from those two things i found the game really enjoyable and would reccomend playing it and if you'd like a little challenge going through out the game: only get supplies like smoke bombs, medicine, throwing knives, Etc. from looting dead enemies.\nall in all, I'd rate the game 7.5/10", "hours": 66.7, "username": "Wise", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
