{"product_id": "33230", "page": 177, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-05", "text": "At the risk of sounding edgy all of these Ubisoft games are pure autism and I have no idea why anyone would play these. The story is boring, that characters flat, and nothing holds my interest.", "hours": 9.0, "user_id": "76561198036797969", "username": "SliQster", "products": 85, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 177, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-04", "text": "As the first part of the \"Ezio Trilogy\" its one of my favourite parts. It may be buggy sometimes (like climbing) but its pretty good besides that. The Graphics r pretty good for 2009 and its fun roaming around. It also provides a fantastic first part of the Ezio Story.\n+good Story\n+good graphics for 2009\n+good engine\n+Ezio\n-cant use my deluxe bonus key :(\n-rare bugs\n11/10 would buy again", "hours": 41.1, "username": "Lasse", "products": 88, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 177, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-03", "text": "Really enjoyed playing this game\n+ pretty scenery, didn't matter that the game is old (so not so up to date graphics)\n+ story line and voice acting (okey okey, I do love the italian accent)\n+ side \"tasks\" (don't focus only to story line, just enjoy the cities and do some treasure hunting, assassin contracts etc. every now and then)\n- Had difficulties to get the game working because of Ubisoft service error. Problem was quickly solved with their customer service. The Uplay that came with game was old and needed to download a new one.\n- Controlling character was awful with mouse and keyboard, would say that get any controller to connect to PC (incase don't have one yet) as it makes it much easier to perform the actions.", "hours": 39.8, "user_id": "76561198038823747", "username": "Nebs", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
