{"product_id": "33230", "page": 179, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 still holds out as a personal favourite game.\nThe story is rather captivating and the gameplay is fairly smooth and very enjoyable.\nUnlike newer Assasin's Creed games this one does not suffer from a lot of the glitches, bugs, and major repetitve nature of many modern games.\nThe game does not have a massive replay factor as it is a linear game however I would recommend that the game is worth playing through at least once, and that it is worth buying for at least a single playthrough.", "hours": 21.4, "username": "Psychowire", "products": 267, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 179, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-26", "text": "They took what's best in Assassin's creed, improved it and made a sequal out of it.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Hanzo", "products": 539, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 179, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-26", "text": "We'll never forget that foreshadowing exchange between Ezio and his older brother, Federico, after the two completed a rooftop race: \"It is a good life we lead, brother,\" Federico says, to which Ezio replies \"The best. May it never change.\" A heart-wrenching audio track quiets in the background as the two share their appreciations. \"And may it never change us,\" Frederico responds. Then stuff got dark. Ultimately landing AC2 a spot on our list of 100 best games ever made. It took simulated stalking, breathtaking scaling and parkour stunting to all new heights.", "hours": 81.1, "username": "Leia Organa", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 179, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-24", "text": "the 3rd party DRM kills your accessibility.\ni bought this and can't access it or any other game that i have that is a ubisoft title that uses ubiplay.\nthe whole 3rd party DRM has killed my relationship with ubisoft, who i have been buying stuff from since their beginnings.\ndigital rights management, when it takes all access from the user for no wrong doing is no right at all, thats a wrong.\nbuying a game through a second party to be made accessible or non-accessible by a third party is not really legal is it?\nim not buying it through UBI, steam is supplying it through them but my dealings are with steam, and though i have paid i still can't access my own games, not just this one, ANY that use uplay, so let me point out that i will NOT be making ANY purchases of games that use uplay because i can't access my account, barring further sales from the sellers end, real logical..\nbuyer beware.", "hours": 8.3, "username": "capricorn1971ad \u00ae \u067f", "products": 182, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
