{"product_id": "33230", "page": 186, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-04-15", "text": "Most people consider this game THE BEST assassin's creed game ever, but personally I think it's really dated and arduous.\nPros:\n-The maps are large, are well designed and represent florence ver well.\n-Looks very pretty, especially for a 2009 game.\n-Fun traversal and climbing/parkour. Can be fiddly at times though.\nCons:\n-The protagonist Ezio in my opinion is really bland and boring.\n-The story is decent enough but is told through awfully voice acted cutscenes which you can't skip without mods.\n-Combat consists of button mashing until your \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing thumb falls off.\n-No controller support (unless your instal malware infested drivers).\n-Uplay...", "hours": 13.7, "user_id": "76561198122867779", "username": "Fungal Infection", "products": 102, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 186, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-04-13", "text": "As usual, this will be a short one. AC:2 is definately the best in the series. If you have played and enjoyed any of the other ones, you'll probably love the second of the series. The game is pretty, has a pretty solid story, really excellent mechanics, and just improves on everything in the first one. Basically, this game is all that a sequal should be; it took the first game, kept the same concept, then improved everything. Really fun, and just really well executed.", "hours": 46.9, "username": "Reeze The Vampire", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
