{"product_id": "33230", "page": 189, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-04-04", "text": "For me this was the true start of the Assassin's Creed franchise, with the original game being more of a proof of concept. I very much enjoyed the improvements over its predecessor and it set the scene for the next two titles with some pretty strong storytelling. Now that i have mentioned the story let me say that the whole animus/current day storyline does tie the games together with a bit more meaning they were (to me at least) completely throw away and i believe i would have enjoyed them all the same without\ntl;dr  -  better than the first, with even better to come\n7/10 - would requiescat in pace again", "hours": 2.5, "username": "The Jabba", "products": 900, "early_access": false}
