{"product_id": "33230", "page": 193, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-19", "text": "Far better and superior to first game. Ezio is just more sympathetic character to play with and renaissance Italy - Florence and Venice are one of the best places you can visit in video game (and also in reality too). The idea to have list of people to kill to get revenge for death of your family and slowly remove the names from the list (and from their lives) is satisfactory experience. Nicely combines real history and characters with made up stuff from the video game.", "hours": 32.7, "user_id": "76561198012833532", "username": "Awesomo 2000", "products": 435, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 193, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-19", "text": "I am suprised how Assasin\u00b4s creed is really nice game. Gameplay is really smooth, main story is nicely done. What i do not like is side quests,doing same things again and again is not my hobby. Sometimes i have trouble with control,but its maybe i am not used to games like this.Enviroment of the game is beautiful,Italy is very detailed..maybe i will use assasins creed as turistic guide when i will be there:)I like how the game adds new things,weapons and so during the gameplay,so you dont get bored.\npros\n-evniroment\n-smooth gameplay\n-story\n-graphic\n-skills and equipment progression\n-main character is charismatic\ncons\n-controls\n-side quest\n-13session\n-sometimes AI", "hours": 32.2, "user_id": "76561198162204620", "username": "LeMinhLam", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
