{"product_id": "33230", "page": 195, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-13", "text": "probabilmente il migliore della saga\npresenta una campagna single player longeva e divertente,una vasta quantit\u00e0 di armi rispetto ai capitoli pi\u00f9 moderni,una mappa piuttosto ampia ed un protagonista tra i migliori della serie per quanto riguarda i lati negativi ,il combat system troppo semplice ed i comandi per mouse e tastiera scomodi ma questo problema puo essere risolto settando i tasti ed infine il free running si presenta troppo automatico e spesso causer\u00e0 incomodi come cadere da un palazzo che stiamo cercando di scalare.\nvoto 9/10", "hours": 26.4, "user_id": "76561198119381893", "username": "VigilanteIV", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 195, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-12", "text": "I will not recommend this game because it is bad - because obviously it isn\u00b4t, in fact, it is by far the best game in the series and I loved when I got it some years go; I will not recommend this game because of Uplay, because you simply have to install Uplay in order to play it (it\u00b4s just that simple, guys...); I will not recommend this game because the controls might seem weird for mouse and keyboard.\nThe reason I will not recommend this game it is because it has performance problems. For a game of 2010, me playing on a PC bought in late 2014, it is pathethic that I have to deal with imense stuttering over and over again. It does not the make unplayable, but it makes it boring having to deal with it every 10 seconds, or even less. Supposedly, you have to roll back your graphics card in order to fix it, but I would you do that, just to play 1 game??? And it appears this performance issues does not only occur in this game of the series...\nUbisoft just throws the game on Steam, not giving a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665about this issues. Shame on them!", "hours": 25.8, "username": "Zlazoj Sivek", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 195, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-12", "text": "If you're a fan of the series, then get it.\nThe gameplay throughout this series is naturally very similar. That isn't a bad thing for me, but I know it puts some off. If you want to try one of the games as a standalone or a first purchase, I suggest Black Flag.\nVisuals a little dated, story is cool and/but a lot of cutscenes.\nWould cautiously recommend/10", "hours": 65.2, "username": "Gaz", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
