{"product_id": "33230", "page": 205, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-06", "text": "I have played every Assassin's Creed game from 1 to syndicate and i never get bored from this game it is simplay the best Assassin's Creed game in the Assassin's Creed series. Also you don't need AC1 to play this game because in my opinion this is where the story actually begins.", "hours": 49.8, "user_id": "76561198265056396", "username": "Mr Shade", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 205, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-06", "text": "If you ever wondered why Assassins Creed games seem to be astronomically popular despite being the same re-hashed content with a cling-thin story, it's becuase they're still riding on the good will of this game and the next two.\nAssassin's Creed used to be about mystique in the \"real world\" revealed through progression in the \"virtual world\", with a whole lot of face-stabbing thrown in the mix. Ezio as a main character was extremely engaging and relatable. I remember how much fan discussion there used to be about the historical relevance of the Pieces of Eden, and many a fan theory came about as to how they were responsible for things like Hitler's rise to power, Einstein and Edison's genius, etc.\nThey just don't make Assassins Creed games like these anymore.", "hours": 42.3, "username": "DoctorJohn", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
