{"product_id": "33230", "page": 211, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-12", "text": "This game is fantastic. For me is best that super-cool kills stunts jumps parkour etc.\nSome of objectives are bit hard and you must go 4-5 times trought them. It's good because of many and many upgrades weapons armor and gun that shoot too !!! Lots of parkour. And you have your own city (villa) and you do upgrades here and every 20 minutes you recieve some cash. I strongly recommend it. Its fantastic :)", "hours": 138.2, "user_id": "76561198145033145", "username": "Tracer farmskins.com CSGO64.com", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 211, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "One of the best Ubisoft Montreal creations, and indeed the best adventure game of all time on pc in my opinion. Has decent variety of activities, good plot, amazing characters. An overall win, despite mediocre graphics.\nIt's really sad for me to watch once marvellous series to become so expensive, but soulless games, that come out faster than cat gives birth. I wish one day Ubi will understand, that you don't need to produce games faster than light, to be succesful publisher and developer. Just look at the Rockstar North...", "hours": 11.4, "user_id": "76561198129380421", "username": "JayBlue", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 211, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "The first solid AC game. I loved AC1 sure but AC2 just completely overshadowed it. The features made it a one great experience that after playing it I never felt like going back. The only other steps forward in AC were the Brotherhood and Black Flag. But this one will always be in my mind for introducing Ezio and most importantly Cristina. The story, great characters and gameplay make it an absolute classic.", "hours": 49.8, "username": "sir_laser", "products": 770, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 211, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "Love it, the only thing I didn't like is that you can't replay memories. I was pretty set on being able to go back and re-do stuff so i finished the game and got pretty bummed out when i realized that wasn't an option. That just shows i wanted to play more of it tho, it's a great game", "hours": 111.1, "username": "Marita", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 211, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-11", "text": "In order to overcome the issue with Uplay being \"unavailable\", download and install the latest version from the Uplay website.", "hours": 71.2, "user_id": "76561198261849261", "username": "Trog", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "Played this game on 360 and loved it. Picked it up during steam sale and haven't been able to because whenever I plug in my xbox one controller the camera won't stop rotating, Anyone know how to fix this?\nSeems like this issue shouldn't happen :/", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561198123465644", "username": "Brolacca", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "I think I would've enjoyed it if I could actually get in the game. Thanks\n, Uplay.", "hours": 1.1, "user_id": "76561198055051968", "username": "Filtered", "products": 148, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "I got this game about a month ago, and I have yet to play it due to Ubisoft being \"unavailable\" for the past few weeks. My computer has all of the required  parts to run the game. Does anyone know what is going on? Have any of you guys had the same problem and know how to fix it? I need help.", "hours": 75.7, "user_id": "76561198107062690", "username": "Horizon", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "I'll start with my bad experiences and go for the good later. Like having puding after a meal.\nThe Bad\nI still think that the game should've had an official steam release so we can get rewards and so forth but its not the worst thing about the game. My worst experience about this game is the fact that in some cases the screen is forced at a certain angle I suppose to better view where to go and what to do. What I dont like about that is my keys change. Left isnt left anymore and back isnt back anymore. So if your after the fast paced parkour, this game on PC will frustrate you lets say a 5% of the time. Another thing that annoyed me about the game is the rooftops running, Again with the fast paced parkour. Its as if Ezio is a fearless idiot, by the time I can see he wont make it and leave the keys it tends to be too late. So he bravely flies off of the edge of a building hoping for the best results and usually dont get the best part of it. So again, if your after the fast paced stuff, not a good idea.\nNow for the good review part.\nAgain, like Assasins Creed 1, I think the game has a good basis. The finishing and graphics of the game is well done. I like the fact that the collectables in the game has meaning and rewards. I think the story is well thaught of and if you take your time and plan ahead you will have Many, MANY hours of fun. All in all I think its brilliant.", "hours": 41.4, "user_id": "76561198053831612", "username": "Morphios", "products": 168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "Today I have to agree with some previous reviews - the controls of ACII are dog\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nCannot even beat my sibling using xbox 360 controller (not to speak about the PC keyboard) - my guy just does not move fast enough and most times jumps 180 degrees the other way he should go!\nSo paid for only being able to play it for ca 20 minutes. Nice!\nWill never buy an AC game any more.", "hours": 2.1, "user_id": "76561198047838578", "username": "lennox69913", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "A remarkable detailed storyline with historical events, locations and peoples featured in AC2! I should have paid more for this kind of good game! But sadly, I got it as a gift. Science theory + history + orchestra music + Renainsance Italy.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "ReconSixth", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-09", "text": "Great story, open world, parkour, stealth and combat systems, this is an amazing game! THIS IS EASILY MY FAVORITE SINGLE-PLAYER GAME. This is also a third person game. Voice acting is great! The franchise has an excellent concept. I highly recommend those who haven't played any of the AC games to play them! Great series!", "hours": 63.1, "username": "Jakeformer", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-08", "text": "excellent game", "hours": 48.9, "username": "szeto226", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-08", "text": "Words can't express how frustrating this game is on here. That's why I'm gonna have to write even more words. Ubisoft has given the assassins creed games on steam a death sentence due to one huge problem: Uplay. It's a shame that the AC game I consider to be the best entry in the series be brought down to the ground with numerous disconnects from its service, basically making the game go full-stop. Many, many times have I had to deal with a bunch of outages that prevents me from progressing. Basically, don't buy it.", "hours": 10.8, "user_id": "76561197998532133", "username": "Parismio", "products": 218, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 212, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-08", "text": "My oh my what a game! I loved it. Pretty much obsessed with it. This is the first AC game I've ever played since I've heard it's the best AC game ever. The storyline is amazing, the character (Ezio) is very charming and he's friends with Da Vinci. The story is placed in Italy. You will NOT regret playing this game. :)\nPS: instlal Uplay and you should be able to play this game with no issues.", "hours": 46.7, "username": "CheshireKat", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-08", "text": ">Desynchronized - Ally is dead\nNo\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 He just jumped and fell off a roof....\n10/10 would rage at AI again", "hours": 49.3, "username": "Slash", "products": 726, "found_funny": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-07", "text": "Ah AC 2, arguably the best in the series. This game put's you in the role of Ezio Auditore de Firenze,son of the nobleman Giovanni Auditore. Ezio is a very interesting character, with a very easy-to-follow backstory.\nPros:\n-Excellent graphics (for it's time)\n-Freerunning is a blast, as it's very fluent and easy to control (not as much as say, AC 4, but it works)\n-TONS of stuff to do (like Raiding tombs, beating up wive's cheating husbands, and more)\n-The story is very easy-to-follow and interesting, but has a few dull moments\n-The dialogue is ok with pretty good voice acting\n-The villans are great, from phsycopathic bankers to the POPE\nCons:\n-The pointless opening with Desmond that could've been done in a single cutscene\n-\"It's me, Mario!\" Really?\n-Uplay\nI really want to talk about Uplay, as it made me worried that my $20 was spent in vain\nIf you're VERY VERY VERY VERY...VERY VERY lucky, than Uplay will work for you. Most likley, it will not. To fix this, run AC 2. You will be prompted to log in to Uplay, but when you do, it will crash. This is fine, as we will fix this later. Now, open Control Panel and click \"Uninstall a Program\". Scroll down to \"Ubisoft Game Launcher\", or something like that, and click \"Uninstall\". After this, you should probably delete any leftover files from Uplay. Go to C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Ubisoft (On 32-bit Windows this will be in C:\\Program Files\\Ubisoft) and delete the foler named \"Ubisoft Game Launcher\". Then, you want to re-install Uplay (or else the game won't run). You can download it from here\nAfter you re-install Uplay, log in. This should work. Now, you have to click \"Redeem a game\" or something like that. Enter your Steam product key and AC 2 will be added to your Uplay/Ubisoft library.", "hours": 126.9, "username": "The King of Vietnam", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-07", "text": "Haven't had this much fun for a long time. I was hoping it will be worst than the first part, but it is definitly an improvement. The only thing I'm not so used to is a close up camera. If it was just a little bit further it would be perfect.", "hours": 26.2, "username": "Slav_Bear", "products": 29, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-07", "text": "to any one that followed or still follows this franchise it is beyond words to describe the solid corner stone AC 2 played in the franchise .\nbut to you who is wondering why would i buy this game .\nfrom climbing the rooftops of the beautiful Florence to taking (slightly romantic) gondola rides under the moonlight in Venice , To fighting dirty timplars and stopping their schemes to avenge your family .\nfrom solving the mysteries of the ancient and pausing to simply appreciate the scenaries and the view from high places along with jysperkid's soundtrack masterpiece .\nthis game deserves every minute you spend in it and every penny you spend on it .", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Blaze", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-07", "text": "Requiesta in Pace", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198084179645", "username": "Murdoc", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "assassin's creed 2 is 2\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665for me", "hours": 6.7, "username": "\u30df\u273fa new leaf\u273f\u5f61", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "Don't bother wasting your money.\nPirate it if you really have to play it on PC.\nThis uses Uplay, Ubisofts own little launcher for all of there games so they can be a special little snowflake.\nThey got the special part right cause the damn program barely works at all.\nI got AC2 to run by starting Uplay in offline mode.  It started in windowed mode, which I couldn't change and then when I hit story it just was stuck at a finding network connection screen.  The only option at that screen was to exit to windows.\nNeeding to find a network...for a SINGLE PLAYER GAME.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "MoistBuddha", "products": 671, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "i have bought this game because i am a big fan of the assassin's creed series, but once i played it i found that i couldnt see the game but just a pitch black screen, even thought i couldnt see it i could clearly hear it. I just want to warn any buyer that this might happen.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198173324030", "username": "N7", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "I'm sure the game itself is wonderful. But I can't say for sure. Because UPlay won't work. Thanks for nothing Ubisoft\nEdit:  Finally got the game to work on my computer after some digging around.  I still dislike connecting through UPlay and every once in awhile the game randomly closes while I'm playing.  But the game itself is great.  The buildings and artwork are nicely detailed, transportation is nice, missions are interesting.", "hours": 27.2, "username": "Nethfea", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 213, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "I haven't played this game on PC yet, but I beat it for xbox not too long ago, and I would say it's excellent. It has a great story, fun combat, and plenty of content. So far, I've been dissapointed in the Steam release due to poor optimization, but that doesn't change how well this game holds up, even 7 years later. 9/10\nEDIT: Though I still love this game and would reccomend it, I must say that the PC port sucks. Like a lot. The keyboard and mouse controls are abysmal and they make it extremely difficult to set it up with a gamepad, especially on a mac. Great game. Lazy port. Steam version: 1/10", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Jack", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 214, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "I'm sure the game itself is wonderful. But I can't say for sure. Because UPlay won't work. Thanks for nothing Ubisoft\nEdit:  Finally got the game to work on my computer after some digging around.  I still dislike connecting through UPlay and every once in awhile the game randomly closes while I'm playing.  But the game itself is great.  The buildings and artwork are nicely detailed, transportation is nice, missions are interesting.", "hours": 27.2, "username": "Nethfea", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 214, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-06", "text": "I haven't played this game on PC yet, but I beat it for xbox not too long ago, and I would say it's excellent. It has a great story, fun combat, and plenty of content. So far, I've been dissapointed in the Steam release due to poor optimization, but that doesn't change how well this game holds up, even 7 years later. 9/10\nEDIT: Though I still love this game and would reccomend it, I must say that the PC port sucks. Like a lot. The keyboard and mouse controls are abysmal and they make it extremely difficult to set it up with a gamepad, especially on a mac. Great game. Lazy port. Steam version: 1/10", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Jack", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
