{"product_id": "33230", "page": 215, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-03", "text": "This game does have the potential to be good, but I'm sorry to say that it just isn't. Okay, I know that it is old and dirt cheap right now, but I feel cheated not so much out of my money, but more so out of my time. I played a couple of hours to get through the utterly boring training part just to have the game freeze up when I finally receive my wrist blade. Exit the memory to see if I can just go back to that part...no...of course not; I need to complete the invisibility training again. No. Then onto the controls; Holy Cr@p! What were these guys thinking? The controls are horrible and that I'm affraid is the deal breaker for me. Do not buy this game. 2$ or whatever it's going for now isn't a fortune, but time is precious and you will be wasting yours.", "hours": 6.1, "user_id": "76561198115190185", "username": "Pastafarian_FSM", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 215, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-03", "text": "Best game out of the series. A must play!", "hours": 194.2, "user_id": "76561198039609832", "username": "giantmike13", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 215, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-02", "text": "By far the best assassin's creed game. By far. It's very cheap for the amount of hours you could put into it. The map(s) are very well made and alltogether are massive.", "hours": 25.9, "user_id": "76561198107126809", "username": "KingOfTheWorld", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 215, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-02", "text": "In the AC series I have played AC 1, AC 3, Blackflag, and Syndicate. I picked this up because many loyal fans claim this and brotherhood are the best in the series. In 2015 the game holds up fairly well in my opinion. It controls more like an RPG game than a third person action game. The story is engaging to this point and while many of the crafting and customization options are not there, I am enjoying my time with it. I know the controls are controversial but IMO they hold up fine and if you think of it as RPG controls rather than action game controls I think it helps.", "hours": 5.9, "username": "AliOgun0022", "products": 348, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 216, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-02", "text": "Not bad for an installment of the Assassin's Creed franchise. I would recommend everything about the franchise other THAN THE FACT THEY CAN'T STANDARDISE THEIR CONTROLS", "hours": 57.1, "username": "lilith", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
