{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "Now there is nothing new for me to say about this game,\nall the things that this game has done poorly as well as the ones that it did well have been pointed out on several occasions.\nSo, i'm just going to tell you my overall opinion: It was legen wait for it..... DARY\nAt some points the game was giving you annoying errands where you were just running back and forth around Italy,\nand that\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665me off, so yes the game is repetetive- all you are really doing is killing a bunch of people then going to the next city, repeat.\nOverall it's a great game and i think you should buy it.", "hours": 34.7, "username": "Lupus", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "I've heard good things about this game. I'd dearly love to play it. But so far the only thing I have seen is \"Uplay is unavailable\". Any and all solutions tried have yielded no discernable results, and anything further is not worth the time. Here's hoping I get my refund.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Totalityofthegrump", "products": 59, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "Love at first sight... i must say the best ac games are the ones that have Ezio Auditore on them. and this this is the gamne that made me like the franchise. I absolutely recomend it. but i must warn that if this is your first ubisoft game to be installed you'll have to be patient as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. for all the updates that uplay will have before you can even play the game.", "hours": 66.5, "username": "Zelinzky", "products": 291, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "This is my favourite console game, but I've had endless problems trying to run it via Steam on desktop or laptop PCs due to UPlay nonsense. For me, this was a complete waste of money buying this version, because instead of actually playing this great game, I got to spend hours trawling forums simply trying to get it to run, and eventually gave up.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "Mutator", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "This game is much better than the first game:  much more variety of game play.  There are different types of missions, weapons, and ways you can kill.  I really like how there is an economy system now and you can own shops to get discounts on buying new things.  You can also get history lessons on the Renaissance in Italy, if you're interested in those kinds of things.  The story-line is very matrix like and is an interesting story development from the previous game.  They've also incorporated a puzzle/brain-teaser like element which I feel most games nowadays lack, the puzzles are quite challenging and require much thinking.  If you're not the type of person who wants that in a game, just look at FAQs.  But I really like solving riddles & puzzles, so that element is perhaps one of my favorite parts of that game.  Overall this is one of the best games of the assassin's creed saga, and has great replay value.", "hours": 109.5, "user_id": "76561198114776608", "username": "buckman333", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 217, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "Foundation for one of today's largest gaming franchise.\nAwesome game that still aged well. Ezio is badass.\nBut \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Uplay tho", "hours": 12.5, "user_id": "76561198145812929", "username": "zionooo", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
