{"product_id": "33230", "page": 223, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-19", "text": "Just bought a couple of AC titles (II, Black Flag, Syndicate) and quickly prefered this one from a flavor and story perspective (over the more lush graphics of syndicate). The political and personal drama stories unfold and the locations are ripe with flavor...also the mix of italian with english and the clear latin emotional over rational cultural flair nicely captured.\nOnly complaint is that it does not support xbox controller like the later titles.\nIf feels like a daVinci code story and the quests to find codex and assassins tombs very flavorable...", "hours": 47.2, "username": "trimenium", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 223, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-19", "text": "All the hard work that must have gone into making this classic game. You'd have thought somebody would have bothered to debug the control system. Keyboard and mouse support on OSX is flaky \u2013 lots of restarts required. And if you're intending to use a game controller, as is totally undowithoutable if you're intending to Ezio about with catlike grace, you can just forget about it. The App Store's \"Joystick Mapper\" won't get you anywhere for now, though the developer claims to be working on a workaround.\nUbisoft oughta face up to the fact that they have, possibly by accident, made a video game which offers an occasional glimpse of The Sublime. Take some responsibility. Make this work. And see to it that we're able to play in Italian with English subtitles. Us OSX people are heavily into that sort of thing. Show us some love.", "hours": 34.1, "user_id": "76561197970837731", "username": "benrowlinson", "products": 48, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 223, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-18", "text": "My biggest complaint about this game is that it requires UPlay to be installed. This means that UPlay will have to update itself every time you open the game, delaying actuallying playing the game. This also means that the game will randomly quit when UPlay doesn't speak to the server often enough to ensure that you're not friends with pie rats.\nMy second biggest complaint is that this is obviously a port of a console game and really is intended to be played with a controller. Playing with a mouse and keyboard is doable, but there will be plenty of moments where you fight the auto-camera and think \"No Ezio, why did you leap THAT way?!\" The controls don't always play nice.\nCombat is easy enough since countering is not always an instant kill, but it's never really a challenge. More of a delayer. Most fights will be bypassed or cheesed with lots and lots of knives, or if it's just simple mooks, counter away.\nAside from that, it's stabby stabby slicey slicey. The protagonist is likeable and relateable enough, exploring and running around is fun, the collectables give rewards now and aren't completely impossible to find without a guide, and the story is decent. A worthwhile pickup if you've liked any other game in the franchise.", "hours": 35.7, "user_id": "76561198048266407", "username": "Catgirls are Love", "products": 278, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 223, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-18", "text": "ubisoft fix this game please", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Rickstar", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
