{"product_id": "33230", "page": 234, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-17", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2!!\nPros:\n>Gameplay is fun and simple (more variety of missions, weapons and outfits added)\n>Story is interesting and continues from where number 1 left off.\n>Graphics are pretty decent some of the models face's are a bit poor though.\n>Voice acting is great\nCons:\nLike most assassin's creed games and like all platformers it does suffer with repetitiveness\nI felt the ending of the game was poor.\nHave to sign up to ubisoft's crappy clone like version of steam >_> yay.....\nAlso... it does provide controller support but the buttons are messed up, patches can be found on the forums that will fix this issue.\nOverall a very good game and major improvements made from the the first in the series\n7/10", "hours": 21.6, "username": "Mithras O_+", "products": 933, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 234, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-16", "text": "", "hours": 26.9, "user_id": "76561197974845628", "username": "AMB", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-15", "text": "Ok this review is poisonous and yes i am butthurt but this is steam. we do not require multiple game launching applications. and certainly not one that pops up with the \"ubishaft has stopped working\" error message every time you alt tab to the other ubishaft website to reset your password. i've played assasin creed games before and it was hardly worth the price when i bought this thing on sale for half off. but to make the user jump through hoops like this just encourages piracy. enjoy playing this game illegally but to do it through their pathetic UI you would have to be just an uneducated consumer.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "2DANK2SPANK", "products": 264, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-15", "text": "Great game, improves everything good about Assassins Creed 1, one of those few games that I felt I just had to 100%. Great story, great gameplay, great content. Unlike the previous game, free running was still fun even after doing it for the past 40 hours, as it was so fluent and responsive. Genuinely a little disappointed when it ended. No complaints apart from uplay really.", "hours": 45.0, "username": "\u2660 Shas'O Bongosun Mont'yr", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
