{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-13", "text": "Never played the first one, and probably never will.  But AC2 is baller shock collar.  If you haven't played it, it's awesome.\n12/10 will travel to Florence.", "hours": 64.7, "username": "Majour", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-13", "text": "Assassin's Creed is an OK francise in my books, however this is the best game in the series. The story got me hooked from the beginning unlike most ACs except for AC4 and so far it's not boring. Very fun combat and it's easy to get used to the game!\n8.5/10!", "hours": 1.7, "username": "The Pizza Kids", "products": 281, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-12", "text": "Wish i could launch it", "hours": 46.9, "user_id": "76561198106397682", "username": "\ud83d\udde1Cavollus\ud83d\udde1", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-12", "text": "it has to go through uplay anyways, and trust me theres nothing more painful than uplay.", "hours": 4.6, "username": "Cat with the gat", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-12", "text": "After a few years from the first game, I came back to play through the second part of the series and was not disappointed. At first I was a little lost from the different playstyles; I spent a while trying to figure out what button it was to blend in with crowds, until I was eventually shown through the story (how to be a noob 101, here). I'm a huge fan of the story, and I have to say, the ending got me. Definitely worth it, after the initial struggles.\nInitially, getting the game to actually run was a problem. Steam didn't actually give me the Uplay launcher, per se, and because I did not know that I needed it, I was getting frustrated that I couldn't actually play the game that I had just bought. Looking through for answers, I was a bit annoyed that I had to go download a whole new launcher just to get the game to run, but I sucked it up and dealt with it, as I'm sure a number of other players have already done, and will continue to do. Aside from that initial issue, I didn't have a single problem with functionality or anything of the sort, so that's a plus.\nI've now set my scopes on part III, because I want to know how Desmond's story really ends (and don't want to do it the cheap way and search it on the internet\u2014where's the fun in that?).", "hours": 16.8, "username": "\ud835\udd6f\ud835\udd8a\ud835\udd9b", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 235, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-12", "text": "This is the best Assassin's Creed ever\n10/10 nice story and gameplay.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "$P\u20acCTAT0R", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
