{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-11", "text": "Over all an awesome game, though there are a lot of glitches with minor details. Several guards would glitch and not move from one spot making missions difficult! The rest of it was fine. Story is amazing.", "hours": 63.1, "user_id": "76561198069498708", "username": "Lexi0900", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-11", "text": "huge improvement from the first game! Both in characters and story. The setting is also amazing with lots of buildings perfectly recreated from Venice, Florence and Forl\u00ec. In the end there is a pretty big cliffhanger tho.\nGraphically speaking, colors look washed out and LOD distance is awful, the rest is pretty good.\nI rate it 8\\10", "hours": 18.5, "username": "arthurstaal", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-11", "text": "One of the best games in the franchise. \"It's-a-me, Mario!\" included.", "hours": 17.8, "username": "trikuxabi", "products": 529, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-11", "text": "Whenever I visit Venice or Florence or any of the places featured here, I will forever think that I jumped off of those buildings.\nAssassin's Creed II - making us think it is okay to climb every building in Florence in real life.", "hours": 51.6, "username": "AlexTenshi", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-10", "text": "Fun game", "hours": 126.1, "username": "Red", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-10", "text": "it is a classic if you like the Assassins Creed saga, but if you buy it here in steam it has many issues with the Ubisoft launcher, and you still need to open the game on it. A good game, but it is advised to have in in a physical format!", "hours": 67.3, "username": "BadWhite", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-10", "text": "I am once again an assassin\nStill no idea what a creed is\n2!?\n79/100", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198059402045", "username": "ergorapido", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 236, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-10", "text": "What can I say? I was urged to get this game when it was on sale because \"it is the best Assassin's Creed game yet\", and I was not disappointed. This was an awesome game with a great story and impressive graphics for a game made in 2009. I loved walking around and having the option to do what I want, when I want to. The freerunning is awesome and Leonardo da Vinci is more than willing to help you become more and more lethal. I don't like some of the main missions, though, and I thought that some of the objectives were kind of boring at times. Also, the combat was kind of disappointing after a while because it just felt so repetitive. That's just some constructive critisism, however. I think this game is more than worth the regular price let alone a sale price!", "hours": 30.0, "user_id": "76561198098101776", "username": "Cordovah", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 237, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-10", "text": "No one can defeat the Mighty Ezio, EZIO AUDITORE!", "hours": 3.1, "username": "Rabbidscool", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 237, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-09", "text": "Fabulous!", "hours": 39.5, "user_id": "76561198136848975", "username": "Crassus Parnax", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 237, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-09", "text": "Ignore all of the reviews for this game that say that this was the best Assasssins Creed and that the new ones are terrible. It's true the new ones are un-finished pieces of crap but this is... double crap. The new games at least have the fun climbing and free-running going for them, while this game has horrible clunky controls (yes I use a plug in Xbox controller) and the story is\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 If you want a good game with the Assasssins Creed controls then get Shadow of Mordor. Just go get Far Cry 4, that's a good game. Or The Last of Us. Check out my library, there's some good stuff in there.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Chad W. Alpha", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
