{"product_id": "33230", "page": 250, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-14", "text": "This game is absolutely delicious. Getting my controller to be detected properly and setting up uplay were real pains but it's a small price to pay.\nThe freeclimbing parkour\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665is extremely well implemented and you'll probably only die twice from Ezio not snapping to the right surface. The amount of stuff to actually do is ridiculous but you'll likely have a blast with each of the different activities. Additionally, you get to manage your own villa and upgrade it, which increases the income you receive from it. If the climbing mechanics look good to you, or the history part seems good, I'd advise you to get it.\nOh yeah, and uplay withholds a small dungeon from you but you can easily look up how to get it.", "hours": 34.9, "username": "UltimateXero", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
