{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-13", "text": "As a game?  Good.  As a product?  Crap.\nAC2 is a seemingly classic game brought down by technical issues, including slow start-ups, various crashes/freezes, poor optimization and uneven performance.\nIf you insist on playing this version of AC2, I suggest the following:\n- When stability becomes an issue, commonly in later maps, reduce the CPU cores used to 2 for the AC2 process (details on how can be found here:\n)\n- Avoid Alt-Tab'ing out, Steam's Shift-Tab, or any multitasking while the game is open\n- Don't bother with Steam Big Picture\nIssues will still occur, but the steps mentioned above seem to help.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Obzenium", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-13", "text": "Although I haven't played all Assassin's creed games yet, I can tell this game is a GEM, a MUST-HAVE for the AC fan. It's graphics are beautiful and the gameplay has a lot of variation. There is a lot to do in the 3 Italian cities and your own ''Town'', including assassinations, chasing evil messengers, finding secret drawings and even DUNGEONS (freaking dungeons!!!). There is also a part where you can fly!! If you are not in the mood for the story mode, you can always show your ''moves like daggers'' to those guards and run for your life, trying to escape them or beat them with the fair and fun combat system. And if you are in the mood for the story mode....you can expect a big storyline incoming. The only thing I really miss in this game is the fact you can't moonwalk (to act like a boss).\nAnyway, you should buy this game. There is no way around it.", "hours": 39.5, "username": "TheHeroOfTimeAndSpace", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-13", "text": "If you are having problems launching the game make sure that you download the lastest UPLAY from Ubisoft and hopefully it should work, (the version of UPLay that comes with the game is defunct). Also I found that the Steam Key didn't copy and paste so I had to type it in.\n\nGraphics are pretty good for an old game excluding the cut-scenes which are pretty awful. Gameplay is ok but what I don't like is the whole premise of the \"Knight Templars are evil conspirators trying to take over the world\" plot-line; sorry I think it is just really lame.\nSecondly the game is acted out through genetic memories so I could have forgiven the aforementioned had it been a more coherent plot and story but it's just silly and I felt no empathy for the characters; especially considering that you are a glorified murderer.", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561198053235064", "username": "elfhammer", "products": 513, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-13", "text": "I became the famous assassinator and assassinated some plebs and fell off roof tops #FallingSimulator2069", "hours": 25.4, "username": "Gypsyy", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-12", "text": "Gives you the freedom to explore great historical settings while on a mission to bring righteous justice to your enemies... what's not to love.\nHaving seen other people play I thought I'd really struggle to get to grips with the controls but they're a nice balance between manual and auto that lets you pull off incredible stunts without needing the skill of a master ninja while still being in control.\nI think the setting is amazing, the controls are excellent, the story is good, the difficulty is well balanced and the characters are interesting... only gripe I have is that the missions can get a bit samey (run all the way across the city and do XXXX).", "hours": 15.7, "user_id": "76561197982231182", "username": "TimSteve", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 256, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-11", "text": "One of my all-time favorites. It's open world at its best, a time and place fully realized down to the details a la Red Dead Redemption. What makes this game work so well is that its setting is such a compelling one. I've played many of the other AC games. None of the other historic settings have worked quite as well as Renaissance Italy does for this game. It's a combination of memorable cities to inhabit like Venice and Florence, colorful characters, and a feeling that this particular time and place is both unique and important. All the famous buildings that you would go to see on an expensive vacation are recreated here (fully climbable of course). The music is inspired and really sets the tone for the game.\nAs in any AC game the gameplay is fun if a bit repetitive. To me AC games are setting first, gameplay second. The gameplay is just to give you something to do as you explore the world.\nEven after five years the game still looks great on a PC with graphics maxed out.", "hours": 28.1, "user_id": "76561198026330516", "username": "marten48", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 257, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-11", "text": "Assassin's Creed II took everything that was wrong with Assassin's Creed and fixed it. A charismatic protagonist with hundreds of things to do in stunning Renaissance Italy. It may well still be the best in the series.", "hours": 40.9, "username": "Dan Bull", "products": 3619, "early_access": false}
