{"product_id": "33230", "page": 258, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-08", "text": "Took me 45 minutes to get into the game.  Get through the first cutscene and the game freezes. No fix that I found ws worth my time to try, I could torrent the game in the time it would take to get this to work.  I'm welcome to trying it out, someone let me know if I'm doing something wrong.\n0/10, great lying down on the animus table simulator", "hours": 2.6, "user_id": "76561198125082369", "username": "Smithy Winfred", "products": 271, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 258, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-09-08", "text": "Most of the first game's grievances carry over to the second one: Repetitive side quests, bland protagonist, boring combat, lots of time spent just running (or riding) around. The most compelling aspect of the game is honestly collecting all the Renaissance art. The story is more fragmented than in the first game, with characters coming and going, though partly that is due to the adherence to historical facts -- significant portion of the characters are actual historical figures and again, the largest appeal is exactly how the events of the game tie into actual ones. Still, like with the first game, you should only pick this title up if you want to see the overarching story through from start to finish.", "hours": 57.9, "user_id": "76561198049409305", "username": "thing not a person", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 258, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-07", "text": "I know Steam says that I only have 2.3 hours but I actually have over 24 hours in the game (I had no internet for a weekend so I played the whole story and most of the side-quests within a weekend)\nThe story is great, The missions are challenging without being annoying and the characters are relatable and funny (Mario) I would recommend this game to all my friends.\nI was thinking about getting this game for a while because I wanted to play an Assassins creed game and everybody said that this one was the best. My friends (who have had it since it came out) still haven't finished it and I don't know why they don't want to.", "hours": 3.0, "username": "RagingBlastoise", "products": 185, "early_access": false}
