{"product_id": "33230", "page": 263, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-12", "text": "Most of the Assassin's Creed games have gone to s**t after Ezio's games. I am a huge fan of AC but I cannot play some of the other games in their series.\nAC2 is the best. Far better than the newest ones I'll tell you right now.\nIf you're considering buying one AC game but don't know which one, it's THIS.\nThis is really the only AC game that really matters. Brotherhood and Revelations are alright too after this one if you want to continue Ezio's story.\nI'm bad at reviews so all you need to know is with this game, it's a no regret choice.\nActual assassinations, a quality storyline, and with a decent soundtrack? F*ck yeah this game.\nI will not ever stop playing this.", "hours": 145.2, "username": "Salted Cucumber", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 263, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-12", "text": "Great story, Great gameplay, Best Assassins Creed,\ni havent had the same feeling i had playing this game since the first time i plaied Ocarina of time,\nif your readin this and you havent plaied this game, fix that, easily one of my favorite games of all time,\nthe only reason i dont have more time is it is that i knew if i plaied any more id never stop,\nezio (the main character) is an interesting character that most people i know would relate too.\nyoull get attached to him and his story, and might need to get brotherhood and revalations because you like the character so much\nthe only proplem is that you need uplay, but its a small price to pay to experience this game 10/10 will play again", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Leebro17", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 263, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-12", "text": "Beat Story line in the whole series.", "hours": 34.6, "user_id": "76561198111693291", "username": "hzjw", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 263, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-12", "text": "The first impression was a near catastrophe:\n- After downloading AC2 uPlay wants to update\n- Then uPlay it always crashes, see fix for uPlay with permissiosn\n- Requires an additional uPlay account (wait, what about integration with Steam)\n- Then in the Tutorial you get a press <Symbol> but not current or default key binding\n(requires to open up the options and look things up, this was definitely better in AC1)\nHoping the content is going to be better, but Ubisoft is here to blame for the mess with uPlay, sorry, not really a Valve issue I guess.\nTo fix uPlay go to the folder where uPlay got installed (default seems to be C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Ubisoft\\Ubisoft Game Launcher) edit the security permissions and giving full permission to the users group should suffice.", "hours": 50.1, "user_id": "76561197990757108", "username": "kofi-please", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 264, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-11", "text": "This game doesn't run. It didn't run the last time I installed it. It's very frustrating.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "brawnyman7713", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 264, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-11", "text": "A proper sequel of Assassin's Creed 1, AC2 shows little changes in its setup.\nPros:\n+ nice graphics, even if a bit simple (realism?);\n+ very nice idea of having your own personal base - luna park;\n+ also, value to arts and history, which is poorly felt nowadays;\n+ exciting exploration of (fictional) templar crypts;\n+ mind-blowing final plot twist which turns your head upside down and inside-out;\n+ fun glyphs minigames, help break the monotony;\n+ maybe a bit less simple than AC1 - some missions require planning, which is good.\nCons:\n- feather quest in AC2 = templar flag quest in AC1. So much pain in the bass, very poor reward;\n- races are sometimes frustrating for their request of absolute perfection;\n- same old story, final plot twist aside: I was more excited in the \"real world\" sketches;\n- the PC is a lady killer bachelor and when he is surrounded by \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s he is embarassed. I would have liked the possibility of hiring them (not necessarily with cut-scenes), to add flavour to the character - no, he is a jesuite in the inside and you have no option of changing it;\nRecommended - for those who like this kind of game. Otherwise, try and test it before buying: once you play the first 3 - 5 hours you know how you will play for the rest of the game.", "hours": 40.8, "user_id": "76561198106889864", "username": "fagio.darkie", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 264, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-11", "text": "only good assassins creed game", "hours": 14.4, "username": "alowflaylow", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 264, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-11", "text": "The story. The combat. The graphics(of its time).\nAll were amazing. I will probably  replay this game again.\nWhy?\nBecause it's Ezio Auditore Da Firenze.", "hours": 53.3, "username": "KnightX", "products": 170, "early_access": false}
