{"product_id": "33230", "page": 270, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-15", "text": "I fell in love with this.\nBut... Problems with Uplay installation and crashing... Come on, seriously? Guys, the way company delivers the game is one the best ways to leave a good or bad impression. You leave bad one. But thanks to Steam users and guides I got through that. And, actually, i work in IT so i'm kinda used to when things that have to work brilliantly don't work at all, and there always are people who already know what to do.\nIf you want to try, get ready to fix some troubles with Uplay. Guides will help.\nNow ok, let us return to the game.\nEpic plot.\nSmart developed.\nBeautiful designed interfaces (even if there are some unnecessary confirmations: if i want to heal now, that means I want to heal now, there is no need to ask me if I'm sure or not).\nNew breath to classical vengeance stories.\nDefinentely yes.", "hours": 48.1, "username": "SomeOtherMad", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
