{"product_id": "33230", "page": 273, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-06", "text": "I have to be brutally honest: this game is crap. Whatever you do, do NOT download this game. I admit this isn't a review on the gameplay; it doesn't even start, and I've found that almost everyone has the same problem. There is a possibility that it is good, but that doesn't matter. I don't reccomend to anybody who isn't a programmer that can fix the software.", "hours": 13.5, "user_id": "76561198134109839", "username": "mitchiemoreland", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 273, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-06", "text": "Good sequel to the first, despite it being Ubisoft. Well, for the most part. Their alteration of the mouse control was absolutely unwarrented, and luckily I was able to mangle my mouse settings enough to get it to be playable. However in doing so, it has completely ruined my ability to aim well in other games... so some re-learning will be needed.\nI enjoyed the end. Will have to play AC3 now to continue the story. Interesting.", "hours": 45.3, "username": "Frigidman", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
