{"product_id": "33230", "page": 274, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-02", "text": "I just bought this game because i had it on my PS3 but my younger brother has the PS3 to himself because he has more games he plays than me, plus i have a better computer, but i bought this because i was missing the game, as soon as the download finished I started the game up to only get stupid Uplay saying that it wouldnt start i tried several times, restarted computer and looked up a few fixes this is the fix that made it work for me:\n-locate Ubisoft program folder (eg. c:\\Program Files (x86)\\Ubisoft)\n-right-click on the folder, select 'Properties'\n-click the \u2018Security\u2019 Tab and click \u2018Edit\u2019. Select your \u2018Users\u2019 and set the Allow column of check marks to \u2018Full Control\u2019. Click Ok and close the rest of the windows.\nafter 10 mins of dealing with Uplay i already hate and despise everything about it but i love the AC games hopefully no other problems arise.", "hours": 64.3, "user_id": "76561198131830824", "username": "FistMyAnusHarder", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 274, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-02", "text": "The last good Assasin's Creed, if you ask me.  Solid storyline, plenty of unlockable opportunities but it's not up in your face about it.  Gameplay is fun, though occasionally it'll get repetitive.  The game engine needs some work - I found that every time I died in-game, it was the game's fault (randomly jumping off walls into canyons, etc).", "hours": 28.9, "username": "Sgt. Ketchup", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
