{"product_id": "33230", "page": 275, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-30", "text": "It's like the first Assassin's Creed, but it's not. Much more content and a great new story and cast of characters to go about.\nAn alright port, with a few bumps in there. Overall, I'd give it - 9/10\nOne flaw however, has to be about Ubisofts Uplay Sys-\n--------------------------------------------------SUBJECT TERMINATED-----------------------------------------------", "hours": 4.5, "username": "ALoafofBread", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 275, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-30", "text": "Forget Unity, This is perhaps the best made Assassins Creed game to date. Despite others moaning about it, Uplay worked first time for me! Perhaps it was because i purchased and played AC4 - Black Flag before this one. Nevertheless, a working fix can be found on the Ubisoft website as far as I'm aware. I highly reccomend!", "hours": 32.1, "username": "Sharkbait3469", "products": 88, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 275, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-30", "text": "The game is probably very good.  I enjoyed the first one, and by all other accounts this one is better.  I don't know yet, I've only just begun.\nThe downvote is for Uplay.  Seriously UBI, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 off.  The store page says \"uplay account required.\"  Since I'd already been forced over that bridge by Rocksmith and the conversion of my old account from before Uplay, I went ahead and bought it anyway.  The store page is misleading, because it also requires the stupid client.  Which I had to fight for an hour to even register my copy of the game.  Now I feel extremely dirty for giving Ubisoft my money for something with this travesty attached, which I swore to myself I would never do.", "hours": 57.2, "user_id": "76561197990344634", "username": "sultanofsick", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
