{"product_id": "33230", "page": 275, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-28", "text": "still my favourite ac game\n+ good story\n+ some interesting puzzles\n+ huge map and cities\n+ good atmosphere and renesanse\n+ open world\n+ characters\n+ ac brotherhood", "hours": 17.4, "username": "ChaosDEATHLORDz", "products": 446, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-28", "text": "As a owner of almost all Assassins Creed games, i give this game a 10/10!\nPros:\nIts Ezio Auditore, the best assassin ever in my opinion.\nGood parkour\nAmazing Storyline\nYou're hidden blade is a gun. (WTF?)\nYou can hug Leonardo da vinci.\nYou can get the armor and weapons of Altair. (The assassin of AC 1)\nCons:\nCombat system kinda basic, but thats aight since its fun to just smack everyone\nThe reason why Ezio became an assassin makes u cri everytiem.\nIf u dont hug Leonardo Da Vinci he will make a sad face that makes u wanna kill urself.\nYou need to download Uplay :////////\nIn all seriousness, this is what most AC fans describe as the best game, and i honestly agree. There are pretty much no bugs and for a game that is from 2009, and ive played this game like 77 hours total. That just proves how amazing this game really is. Its just an epic game for people willing to try out the franchise and enjoy a good story. I do recommend getting a controller though, since its kind of weird to play with keyboard\nThanks for reading!", "hours": 77.0, "username": "Daetae", "products": 22, "found_funny": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "The story and gameplay is awesome but unfortunately it is lagging although it is over 5 years old and I have a PC which should be capable of games like this.\nIn addition you have to install uplay which takes a lot of ressources from your system. Why do I need another social sh*t program when I already have steam? Do those companies really think that I will use their f*cking software for any social activity when they force me to install it? Won't happen!\nSteam Sale or not I won't buy any more Ubisoft games and I cannot recommend them.", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198079859172", "username": "Gambledore", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "Uplay works fine for me, launchs easily and without hassle, but when I first launch the Story Mode and begin to actually play the game, the world starts having a seizure and its unplayable. Everything is shaking giving you an instant - headache. Ive uninstalled and reinstalled the game THREE TIMES, each time having the same outcome. Of course, this doesn't happen for everyone so if anyone can help me feel free to do so. This is one of my favourite later childhood games and I really want to play it so please help.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Canadian Ian", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "Uplay works now.", "hours": 6.4, "username": "SprayStealer", "products": 278, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "I don't play games like this, but Assassin's Creed 2 was an incredible experience.\nI got the whole AC series in a game pack, and downloaded AC2 first based on online reviews. I really felt like I got the entire experience of Assassin's Creed, and was so satisfied that I actually haven't played any other AC games despite owning the first four. I would strongly recommend this game for someone vaguely curious about Assassin's Creed.", "hours": 61.5, "user_id": "76561198004531684", "username": "coronavitae", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-26", "text": "I get to run around shouting things in italian, beating the crap out of people and looting their bodies and finding treasure chests ala legend of zelda style. I freaking love this game.\n==================\nOld Grumpy Review below\n==================\nWOW Where to begin with this game? This is a pre-game review as I haven't really played too much of this port to really comment on the actual gameplay. But let's get some stuff out of the way that they may not tell you.\nThis is a PC port that requires use of UPlay. If you do not have Uplay, you will need to register for it. Otherwise, you cannot play it.\nFramerate has a hard cap of ~62 FPS. From what I understand the oh so lovely Anvil Engine the game runs on is to blame. I've heard of stories of some people force unlocking their framerates on custom resolutions but I can't be bothered to look into that. They allow you to select 120hz and even 144hz refresh rates though, so more power to the game for that at least.\nThe game's age really shows though, It was meant to run on Xbox 360 Hardware after all. Textures and shadows pop in and out a predefined field around the character, and running it on 1080p and above monitors, it looks absolutely disgusting. This wouldn't be so bad if it weren't for the fact that everything looks terrible and sh*tty unless your character is pressing RIGHT UP AGAINST whatever it is you're looking at. Even when the textures are fully loaded in, they still look like\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nOverall, from a buyers standpoint, if you had to choose between playing this game on Steam or a console, it's probably better to pick up the console version for maybe 5 bucks or less than to pay 20 for basically the same thing but on PC. If it's on sale maybe for $5 on steam, then yes, it's justified.", "hours": 69.9, "username": "AssimiLeaf", "products": 416, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-26", "text": "Its not Unity 10/10", "hours": 9.5, "user_id": "76561198012357660", "username": "M i L k Y", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 276, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-26", "text": "As soon as the game begins with moving an Italian baby you know you're in for a treat.\nGreat campaign and decent story, with the deluxe edition offering a DLC that includes a ship mission that is the devil's spawn.\nPros:\n- Italian af\n- Best assassin Ezio da Firenze Auditore\n- Decently fun\n- One of the better looking games you can get for OSX\n- The music hot damn\nCons:\n- As soon as you play enough AC games you realize they're all pretty much the same. Replayability is low... unless you enjoy unimaginative sidequests and exploring sepia-hued cities while citizens remark on how drunk you are.\n- uPlay", "hours": 34.4, "username": "sinkardia", "products": 14, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
