{"product_id": "33230", "page": 277, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "I'm still getting through the franchise, but this one is a must. Ezio as a character is very well written and his story is quite touching. You will meet familiar characters from History lessons, probably kill some of them and hell will you enjoy it! All italian cities in the game are very nicely rendered and are just beautiful to look at from Eagles (= synchronizing points, y'know, the big buildings you climb on, synchronize and then jump off? Yeah, these ones.) Truth be told, buildings tend to repeat themselves, but that's a minor complaint. So hop on that flying machine that Leonardo built and kill some people! You won't forget it!", "hours": 47.9, "username": "Jpelda_CrazyCat", "products": 122, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 277, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "Best game<3", "hours": 46.3, "username": "Blake |AC|", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 277, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "All Ubisoft games NOT WORKING, after recent update of Uplay. It has been over a week, ubisoft support has not replied me yet. Dont bother with ubisoft / uplay games.\n---------------------------------------------\nSummary:\n- Installation. uplay error on  window 8. (Solution: Run as administrator / set compatiable in window 7 mode)\n- Movement control is more freely when jumping / in air, making it more difficult to jump from A->B than AC 1 )\n- The start menu took time to adapts to, after playing AC1.\n- The camera switching is really bad.\n- Venice / Florence storylines may be too long.\n+The story is finely written.\n+Missions are no longer about repeating like in AC1\n+ Graphic is soooo much better. Especially with the Eagle Vision view.  No more blur\n+ The system of money exchange is kindly considered. Money was not a concern once making investments into the city.\nCasual playing, 100% completed around 37 hours.\nDifficulty of completion: Average / Normal\nBought through Steam Summer Sale. Worth it. Recommended.\nNote:\n- Lucy had a plastic surgery.\n- I miss Altair ...who is afraid of water", "hours": 37.4, "username": "Kaito", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
