{"product_id": "33230", "page": 282, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-20", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed game so far and one of the best game in the industry at all.\nRenaissance Italy, with Florence, Venice and Toscana is perfect suited to racy character as Ezio Auditore Da Firenze, to the well thought out story and additional famous characters which is well known from history.\nMoreover, if you haven't heard the soundtrack, just go for it on Youtube. It enriches the whole game and creates an atmosphere of piece of real art.\nJust read a post called 'The Best Start To An Assassin's Creed Game' on Kotaku and you'll get the essential point.", "hours": 1.3, "username": "RITTER", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
