{"product_id": "33230", "page": 283, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-18", "text": "Marvellous game, mostly due to it's got loads to do with the Renaissance Italy (the period of the Borgias acsending to power) which makes it a nice historical backgrownd plus there's the inimitimble Ezio with all the remacable skills. The scenery is amazing. Great story , great architecture and a seemingly endless game, only seemingly though. But don't get frustrated! There're such a lot of them out there already! Although my fav has always been the Italian thread. Thank you all. Totally recommended. Best adventure ever. I ONLY WISH THE REST OF THE EPIC SAGA WAS AVALIABLE ON MAC TOO. Makes it much more comfortable. Please consider.", "hours": 60.7, "user_id": "76561198174324797", "username": "daniel_o.zaitsev", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
