{"product_id": "33230", "page": 285, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-11", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is infintely better than the original. The developers were able to take everything I hated about the first one - EXTREMELY repetitive gameplay, boring dialogue and characters, ugly color palette, etc. - and made vast improvements on it. If you're on the fence about getting this game because the first one left such an awful taste, give this one a try at least. You should not regret it.", "hours": 30.8, "username": "mooses", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 285, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-11", "text": "One of the most graphically impressive last-gen games out there, garbage gameplay. Unintuitive controls, braindead fighting, easy missions leading up to a frustrating 9 missions that can easily be cheesed against the developer's intentions, and a decent final level.  The plot hinges on alot of unfulfilled promise and little actual substance, and every character is a bland nothing or an eccentric stereotype.\nAlso there's EA origins I guess some people will have a problem with that too", "hours": 29.7, "user_id": "76561197999759672", "username": "JetMechRadio.j2", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
