{"product_id": "33230", "page": 286, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-07", "text": "I really enjoyed the game.. It ran on my old laptop fro 200$ without a problem with all the settings on high, and the graphics are quite good actually\nThe only thing that grinded my mind from the start and made me eternaly hate some of the climbing mechanics, is that when I try to climb something it jumps back (mostly happens when I'm trying to escape from guards and I'm kind of panic clicking). With some experience you can control it but at the beginning it's quite annoying.\nOverall 8/10, the game is great but it has it's bad sides, which are quite a lot and I'm too lazy to mention them, but don't get me wrong its still worth buying!", "hours": 20.8, "user_id": "76561198162388738", "username": "Egregious King", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 286, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "Continuation from the First Assassin's Creed, more details are added on , but i wouldn't wanna spoil it for those whom yet to play. There will be timeline gap if you haven't played the first Assassin's Creed. So be sure to play the first one.", "hours": 32.6, "username": "EchoZero0ne", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 287, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "Overall: Great story in the animus, fixes gameplay flaws in the original (mostly), story in the 'real' world a bit lacking.\nThe story in the animus is gripping, with the exciting chases across varied landscapes.\nIt fixes the wierd blending system, you an now hide in crowds, or hire groups to be a crowd, greatly improving the stealth aspect.\nThere is still a lot of horseback riding, but it is nowhere near as bad as in the original.\nThe combat is more complex, allowing more room for improvement, in the original you hit a glass ceiling were you could counter everything perfectly.\nThe story in the real world is the biggest flaw, it is interesting to begin with, then has a few stops and starts in the middle (with the british man keeping your interest alive with his cynicism), then ends with a shameless cliff hanger.", "hours": 30.5, "username": "ollie299792458", "products": 483, "early_access": false}
