{"product_id": "33230", "page": 288, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-03", "text": "I bought this game becuase I recently went on a trip to Venice and I wanted to revisit it, but I couldn't actually afford another plane ticket. They get a lot of things right, but the streets are too wide, and it's not crowded enough. You don't get lost as easily when you have what amounts to a map, compass and GPS on your HUD at all times. They also left San Croce, one of the districts of Venice, out of the game entirely.  This might be because it wasn't worth making into it's own district at the time the game is set. Other than that, it's a whole bundle of fun. I especially enjoyed the section of the game in Dorsoduro.\nAs for the rest of the game, it's fun. I wish you could remove all armour, since after you finish the main quest you don't really need any of it to complete the missions, and you can't see your dyed robes as well with it on.", "hours": 59.1, "user_id": "76561197971200657", "username": "Snuggles", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 288, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-03", "text": "Guard glitch. That's all I'm saying...", "hours": 40.2, "username": "sucked pineapples", "products": 38, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 288, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-03", "text": "This is a good game and better than the first in the series. It is fun to explore old cities and jump between buildings. The economy was pretty broken though.", "hours": 235.7, "user_id": "76561198023559435", "username": "josiahmanson", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 288, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-02", "text": "I previously held a very poor review for this game describing its poor controls. I recently went back and fixed everything to my liking and I can say with confidence that this is a good game.\nPROS\n-Fun, quick-paced assassin action\n-Nice graphics\n-Cool story\nCONS\n-Controls take getting used to\n-Missions are repetitive\n-UPlay\nMy take is that this is probably my favorite AC game to date. Once you get the controls down things smooth out and side quests vary your gameplay experience. Overall, I'd say it get a 7/10.", "hours": 27.4, "user_id": "76561198065343634", "username": "HiddenFile", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
