{"product_id": "33230", "page": 289, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-30", "text": "I have nothing but good things to say about this game. It is one of the best games I have ever played. The story and gameplay are both fantastic! I won't spoil anything but I just want to say I really enjoyed the story. The game takes place in Italy during the Renaissance and it has great places to visit as you progress through the game. The game does not get boring after you finish the story. It has tons of side missions to do and interesting things to find scattered around the map. This game deserves a 9/10 just because it's story and gameplay are AMAZING! I would recommend this game to anyone.", "hours": 50.0, "user_id": "76561198115016870", "username": "cuplaklix", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 289, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-30", "text": "This game is just amazing. The story made me cry, and the free-running is just amazing. This is the best game in the history of Assassin's Creed games. A must get for any AC fans. Also, this game can teach you about history. I learned some Italian from this game.", "hours": 68.6, "username": "Blind", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 289, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-29", "text": "This is still the best AC game ever. Now if you are having trouble with uplay crashing,you need to uninstall uplay and download it directly from its website. This is because downloading uplay with AC 2 makes uplay crash for a reason. Anyways this game has an epic storyline. The first few missions may be boring but right when you are about to quit the game makes you suddenly interested in the story. This games storyline is over 15 hours! Thats almost GTA V. Anyways this game is a solid 10/10.", "hours": 52.2, "username": "Fallout_Boone", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 289, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-28", "text": "better than acc unity I think", "hours": 73.0, "username": "\u0e41\u0e1b\u0e49\u0e07\u0e1b\u0e38\u0e49\u0e07", "products": 288, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "By far the best Assassin's Creed game out there besides Brotherhood, this game has a fantastic story line and will suprise you with every turn you take in the story, I highly recommend this game to everyone.", "hours": 40.0, "username": "megamutt216", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "While the Assassin's Creed franchise might involve an interesting story and a great open world atmosphere the PC version of the game, especially of the earlier versions of the game are horrible ports. What makes them so bad is that the control scheme is not translated in a way that is intuitive at all. What's worse and super lazy on Ubisoft's part. Which isn't a surprise given Ubisoft's recent history of lazy bug ridden ports is that all the controls are displayed during tutorials and such using their XBox symbols. So if you are using a keyboard none of it makes sense. On top of that even using an Xbox controller the tutorial and camera scheme still don't really give you a natural sense of the parkour that you the Assassin is suppose to become at home with. So quests that you are forced to take including tutorial sections require you to learn the the horribly awkward control scheme while also timed that if you don't figure it out in the 15 seconds they give you means failure and that you have to retry from the last check point. IDK if the newer versions of the game got the PC controls any better, but the older AC games are just awful in regards to controls.", "hours": 5.1, "user_id": "76561198007343418", "username": "Dachshund", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-25", "text": "If you would like to murder people while dressed up like an 16th-century Italian batman, then this is the game for you.", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561198109589421", "username": "Waffle Wizard", "products": 266, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "All round great game.", "hours": 13.9, "username": "duncanr8", "products": 281, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "Awesome game", "hours": 10.8, "user_id": "76561198201943312", "username": "MrsNounours", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "As far as the plot and customization go it's probably one of the best entries in the Assassins Creed series and it may have been phenomenal on consoles. Unfortunately the PC port is an absolute mess. The control layout is THE WORST I have ever encountered in my 20 years of gaming. No exaggeration. The freerunning system that made Assassins Creed popular is a s**t show in this game with your character frequently leaping in a random direction off ledges to his death even though you are aimed at a platform that you can climb. I've tried getting through the game twice and almost finished it a few years ago but after playing it again it simply isn't worth it. I got to a point where you have to unlock code sequences to reveal \"The Truth\" mini game and even though I've completed the same puzzle 5 times I'm still stuck with the prompt to complete the puzzle taking up the upper right corner of my screen. I've walked around for 20 minutes trying to get it to go away with no luck.\nI'm going to play Black Flag again and pretend every AC prior to it doesn't exist.", "hours": 57.1, "username": "Dyne", "products": 824, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "The BEST !", "hours": 29.5, "user_id": "76561198104499960", "username": "Spitzspas", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "Haven\u00b4t played AC:2 yet?\nI envy you.\nBest game (the whole chapter, including Brotherhood and Revelations) of the series. Get it after you've played the newer ones or you'll be let down by them.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "mcnikovich", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "This is a game everyone should have a go at. The movement is fluid, save for a few sections, but the stealth and combat aspects are made much more interesting later in the game with the inclusion of some pretty cool gadgets.  Despite all of the games minor frustrations, Ezio's journey and how the game gets you invested in his story is the prevailing factor encouraging you to keep fighting.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Rice", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 290, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-23", "text": "I played through this game twice before, once on the PS3 and again on the X360, and I liked it so much I played through it again on the PC.  I have to say this older game still looks great on the PC now in 2015 when I am writing this review.  I really enjoyed the first game in the series, and this second game was such a wonderful surprise to see how they expanded upon it.  I really enjoyed the story as well as all the explorations and variety of gameplay.\nWith that said there was still some VERY frustrating moments in this game as the running/climbing/jumping controls still feel clunky.   So many times Ezio will try to run up a wall instead of stopping, or will run along a fence instead of the street, or do his \"mime\" routine of stopping with his hands up in the air, or my favorite of jumping and completely  missing the haystack and crashing into the group.\nIf you can find this on sale give it a try, very entertaining!", "hours": 35.4, "user_id": "76561198024922437", "username": "Santa", "products": 440, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 291, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-23", "text": "The Alta\u00efr is dead, long live the Ezio.\nThe game is basically the same as the first, but this time... it is personal!\n- Dumn Dumn Duuummmmmnnn! Camera fates - scene twists to closeup over the shoulder of an young man in the middle of ancient Florence\nBesides main character Raymond (forgot about him?) you are playing as Ezio Auditore de Iforgot and he is as cool and manly as his name is. Singlehanded trying to take revenge on the death of his father and brother he might as well suffer through it and commit suicide after the first 12 minutes ingame, but not him! He has so many girls to hit on - and he needs to rescue his mother and sister for an less important reason to stay alive. Anyway - Fighting his way out of the town, learning about the Assassin's, he becomes cooler than Alta\u00efr ever was and you start to learn so many things that are really important for the super cool character that you haven't had forgotten now?! Raymond Miles, the boy in the Anuminus... Aluminus... in the thing with the memory ...memory-thing.\n10/10 way better ways of death from above than in the first game, plus: Character with charism", "hours": 28.2, "user_id": "76561198036498823", "username": "Solanum nigrum", "products": 1136, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
