{"product_id": "33230", "page": 293, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-15", "text": "It's still the best Assassin's Creed as of the time of writing this review(Black Flag comes in close).\nPros-\n+Production design feels authentic.\n+An epic story of Ezio the assassin sprawling almost 3-4 decades.\n+Although it hardly matters now .....but the improvements it brought to the original were ineffable.\n+Pitch perfect pacing of campaign.\n+Mission variety.\n+Plenty of side activities.\n+Each city has its own unique feel.\n+Strong supporting characters.\nCons-\n-It's animations do feel a little old now.\nScore-9.5/10\nMust buy and must play!", "hours": 43.0, "username": "Luccese", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 293, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-14", "text": "Let's be honest:  This is an incredible game.  Fun, engaging, immersive.\nThere's only one thing i can say to games in general\nPLEASE dont take 67 hours to complete!!  By the 50th hour of play time i was practically begging for the game to get over.\nI'll reiterate, i loved everything about this game, but it went on for so so long that i had to take a two month break and come back to finish it, just so it would feel like a game again and not arduous work to complete.\nThat being said, Onto Brotherhood!! ;)", "hours": 62.7, "user_id": "76561198120644719", "username": "GDeJoseph", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
