{"product_id": "33230", "page": 306, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "I don't think this game needs any introduction, and for those it does, here goes:\nYou are\nI'd even recommend to play this game (and Brotherhood & Revelations) before the original AC game with Alta\u00efr.\nGood Story, Rather good controls(bit shifty at the start, good after an hour or so.)\nWhile graphics are good, don't expect any high-def Realism. It's a good game even without excellent graphics.\nIn Short:\nIf you like free-range games, that still manage to keep you occupied or focused on several things to do, this is a good game for you.", "hours": 81.2, "user_id": "76561198047818397", "username": "Draleon", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 306, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 was universally regarded as an improvement over the first game and I am of the same opinion. Gone are the same repetitive side quests at every turn. Instead we get a game more expansive and with more depth than its predecessor and a beautifully crafted medieval Italy to explore and experience. The protagonist, Ezio, is also an improvement over Altair feeling more like a protagonist rather than a puppet that the player guides through the game world. Assassin's Creed 2 is definitely one of the best titles in the series.", "hours": 51.6, "username": "PaulP", "products": 666, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 306, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING AWESOME GAME", "hours": 2.4, "username": "stevie2kills\u2122 csgobounty.com", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
