{"product_id": "33230", "page": 310, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-07", "text": "I really disliked the first Assasin's Creed. I found the main character repulsive, and the gameplay too awkward. So I was surprised that I enjoyed the second so much. The plot is much more interesting, and maybe I was more comfortable with the control scheme too. Definitely worth trying, and many people say this was the best of the whole series.", "hours": 47.6, "user_id": "76561197970715506", "username": "toddfox2", "products": 449, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 310, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-07", "text": "Salute, Claudia.\nThis game is vastly superior to Assassin's Creed. The combat feels a lot better and the environments are much better. The mini-game of maintain the town feels rewarding, and the fetch quests to find feathers and things feel a lot better than finding Templar banners in AC1.\nMy one complaint is that it's a stealth game about assassintions, but there are some scripted sequences where you always get caught and always have to fight or escape from large groups of guards. I would have preferred if the game rewarded stealth gameplay by allowing you to bypass combat.", "hours": 26.8, "user_id": "76561198002561882", "username": "Jerk Beefy", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
