{"product_id": "33230", "page": 313, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-20", "text": "A beautiful, immersive, and spectacular game that follows the adventures of a young but brave assassin named Ezio Auditore de Firenze.\nSPOILER ALERT!!!!!\nPlot: The plot is pretty complicated, but I'll give you the short version:\nEzio becomes an assassin and tries to hunt down the people who ended his fathers and brothers lives.\nGameplay:\nGameplay is smooth and fluid.\nGraphics:\nAssassin's Creed 2 is almost 6 years old. However, the graphics still shine and look great!\nControls:\nControls are very annoying at first, but comfortable once you get used to them.\nOptimization: The game is capped at 59 fps. Well, at least for me it is. It's pretty well optimized and I've yet to see any frame rate dips.\nHowever, the terrible DRM known as Uplay makes a return, and it is pretty damn bad.\nSCORING:\nPositives: Great plot, gameplay, story, and easy controls\nNegetives: Typical DRM that you would expect from Ubisoft.\nOverall: I would give this game a 8 out of 10, and I would recommend this to a friend.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Joseph Stalin", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 313, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-20", "text": "Great story,gameplay,soundtrack,visuals.\nMasterpiece 10/10 best money i hever have ever spent.", "hours": 38.8, "username": "sasliks", "products": 556, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 313, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "Assassin Creed II is a major improvement towards the AC series.\nComparing to the first AC game, AC 2\n+ Has more diverse types of main misisons\n+ Beutiful City Design\n+ Better Interaction with surroundings\n+ Amazing Story\n+ Side quests are more interesting\nThe only drawback was minor graphic glitches and the use of Uplay.\nIt is a really good game , thus recommending it to open world lovers!", "hours": 24.0, "username": "Captain  \u00cdsland", "products": 303, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 313, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "The thought of leaving Altair behind to play with this new character sure looked like a bold and not so wise idea. The fact is, Ezio is by far the best Character I've played in any AC (I haven't played Unity and Rouge).\nNote: I've beaten the game for Xbox 360, but I've decided to buy it to collect the series now on Steam!", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Korvo", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 313, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is by far the best game in the franchise. The gameplay (combat, missions, roaming) is excellent and the storyline is quite compelling. A minor point of criticism is that the in-game economy is pretty broken to the point where money literally won't be an issue in the longrun.\nOverall, I'd definitely recommend playing Assassin's Creed 2 first instead of the other games. The first game lacked variation in missions and wasn't as immersive as I thought it would be and it clouded my opinion of the franchise as a whole. If you're just getting into the franchise, I'd recommend playing this game first and play AC1 after you've finished AC: Brotherhood.", "hours": 35.8, "username": "Damalum", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
