{"product_id": "33230", "page": 320, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "Absolutely amazing 11/10\nPLUS: Very long, tons of side activities, amazing graphics (not dated at all!) and still does not need a monster PC (unlike new AC games that don\\t look that much better), beautiful locations (if you've been to Florence you'll be surprised how realist it is in the game), creative and absolutely fantastic story with a fantastic main character, good balance between stealth and fighting, beautiful soundtrack that you''ll keep listening to after finishing the game... This game is fantastic!\nMINUS: Can't think of anything!", "hours": 63.2, "user_id": "76561198096659530", "username": "tomek.nowobilski", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 320, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "This game taught me that bards and couriers are spawns of satan himself", "hours": 46.9, "username": "JC", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 320, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-24", "text": "By far the best Assassin's Creed game. It improves pretty much on everything from the first AC and is what a sequel should be. Amazing story, amazing protagonist and amazing world. Running on rooftops and swan-diving off of 150 foot tall buildings has never been funner.", "hours": 48.4, "username": "Lesley Chang", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 320, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-23", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed will ever be. 1 was a failed experiment, 2 perfects it, 3 is a confused mess, 4 would be better without the AC baggage, 5 is broken and generic, and the spinoffs never had the support they needed to live up to their potential. There's a reason 2 is the only game in the series with its own sequels.", "hours": 57.9, "username": "Sweet T-1000", "products": 691, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 321, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-23", "text": "Amazing. Great. Epic.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Ultima6", "products": 1498, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 321, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-23", "text": "Starting from Assassin's Creed 1 and moving up the franchise, I must say that this game is certainly among the best of them. Now of course, if you start at the top then you'll likely find it lacking, but in perspective, it is still a simply superb game. It added on everything in terms of environmental freedom and side quests/activites that Assassin's Creed 1 didn't have. The combat is now all the more excellent with double hidden blades, various weapons to suit your kill style, various types of armor and awesome execution sequences. Plus you have the option of varying your costume just for fun. In terms of storyline, this likely has the best out of the first 4 AC games. It delves you much deeper into your new main character, Ezio Auditore, and makes the plot much more complex with a wide variety of characters which may be your friends or adversaries. Is this game worth your money. YES!!!! Plus, Ezio is a total bad*ss.", "hours": 76.7, "user_id": "76561198008155152", "username": "Dr. VonDerButch", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 321, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-22", "text": "A beautiful, enjoyable (albeit bloated) open world action game.  The main characters may be difficult to warm up to, but there is a lot of fun to be had assassinating the corrupt and launching yourself from the tallest towers. Read the review on", "hours": 46.1, "user_id": "76561197965813702", "username": "Drexel", "products": 341, "early_access": false}
