{"product_id": "33230", "page": 332, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-02", "text": "I'm sure this is a brilliantly made game with lots of production value, and great gameplay and stuff that makes it 10/10.\nI cannot say for sure as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing Uplay keeps crashing...while launching itself to help me launch the game. Do you want to live? Don't get this game for PC. Get it for consoles.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198065717045", "username": "Mindful Exposure Book", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 332, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-02", "text": "Beautiful and fast-paced game where you feel the pulse, while you jump head loose from building to building, in constant fygt of falling down. The game is incredibly beautiful and the player is rewarded for his exploration of the many achivements and collections that can be done. The game is delicately balanced sword in the degree, as that you get better weapons and equipment, the enemies also more challenging. A small minus is that when you are about halfway through the game, money is no longer a problem and that removes a bit of the joy of buying more and better equipment. In all I enjoyed the game and am looking forward to going to roll with Assassin's Creed III.", "hours": 43.8, "user_id": "76561198007367099", "username": "Wufei", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 332, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "As a self-admitted European history fanatic, I found this to be an immersive game with an intruiging plot. I would reccomend this game to anyone who, like myself, prefers the experience of gaming as opposed to mastering the skill of it.", "hours": 4.2, "user_id": "76561198079718384", "username": "brainiacmaniac9", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
