{"product_id": "33230", "page": 337, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "You need uplay to play this game. After you download uplay it will keep constantly crashing. I couldn't play even a bit of it. I always wanted to play Assassin's Creed, but ubisoft made uplay that doesn't even work. Hopefully, I bought this game on sale when it was just \u20ac2.50.\nBy buying this game, I made my biggest mistake ever. I shall never buy and play ubisoft games anymore.\nSo to everyone, don't buy this game even if it's on the lowest price, ever because it won't work!", "hours": 42.4, "user_id": "76561198126036077", "username": "Danish-1368", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 337, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "AC 2 is possibly the best in the series depending on who you are. Not me. Black Flag is the best in the series. However, this is the second. Though many of its features feel old at this point, but its still has good game play with many very interesting locals. The graphics are bar none the best on the PC; so even if you have the console versions I would still recomend this. The story is good, even if I think the animus feels tacked on.(Not as bad as the sequels)\nNow the negitives I found with the PC version is a short list. The 360 controller isn't great here, and the other one is that its optimization. It staggers and drop frame rate from time to time. For the most part I get 60 fps maxed out, but for no reason it will drop to 45/50/48/60----/45. If you are a console gamer switching to the master race you may not notice, and only really noticable if you watch for it. For most PC gamers it is livable, but not optimal.\nStill I recomend this game, and you should already know what you are getting into.", "hours": 3.8, "user_id": "76561198085726117", "username": "bugs1025", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 337, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Broken game\nAfter completing most of the game, the game froze when loading a new city forcing me to restart my computer. Upon starting it up again, all my data was completely lost forcing me to start from the beginning. This is a major game breaking glitch that ruins an otherwise alright game.\nFrom what I've heard, this problem exists in many Ubisoft games including the other Assassin's Creed games. I would not recomment a game from the series given these issues.", "hours": 21.3, "user_id": "76561198060047110", "username": "Transhumanist", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 337, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "The story continues right where it left off and it is great. My gripe with this one's gameplay is that the lock-on does not work very well. By \"not work very well\" I mean it fails spectacularly at what it is supposed to do, that is, LOCK ON. It does not \"lock\" it only \"sticks\". If you move the camera angle too much such that you point of view centers on another NPC your lock will transfer to that person. It's not a lock-on at all, it's a stick-on.\nOther than that, most things are unchanged, and that's for the better. Story still good, gameplay otherwise good.", "hours": 61.7, "username": "hoimingmissile", "products": 870, "early_access": false}
