{"product_id": "33230", "page": 342, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-21", "text": "Blended in with the priests to walk unnoticed to the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s whom I hired to distract the guards so I could assassinate the man who killed my father and two brothers.  Revenge was as sweet as this game.", "hours": 45.9, "user_id": "76561198012245691", "username": "Sparrow", "products": 554, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 342, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-21", "text": "I loved playing this game on 360, so I decided I would buy it (it only cost a few dollars). I'm sure I would enjoy it on PC, too, if Upla didn't \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing crash everytime I tried to play. Get youshit together, ubisoft.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "Trent Dallimore", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 342, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-21", "text": "One of my favorite stealth-type games. I love the setting, characters, gameplay, and story. It is such an amazing game. Worth $40 if you ask me.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "Splinkerton Forkendoggen", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 342, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-21", "text": "If you still have not bought this game then I ask you WHY? This game takes the excellent ideas in the first one and makes them fun!!! Yea, what we've been waiting for.\nThis is most people's favorite of the Assassin's Creed games. It introduced Ezio Auditore da Firenze, the by far most likeable protagonist (perhaps because he has a personality!) This was also the FIRST game with Ezio so he wasn't old hat yet.\nThe new setting of renaissance Italy is great. The cities, like in the first game feel different (Florence is huge with large cathedrals and town squares and Venice is more cramped with canals), but unlike the first game the cities seem varied. One block in Florence looks different from another block in Florence.\nOne of the bigger additions to the game was money (a staple in the series now.) Money is f*cking useless! I breezed through the whole game and bought nothing. Literally NOTHING. You can also use money to renovate your villa to gain more money, but this is boring as f*ck!\nEven though that sh*t's dumb, most of the new features are interesting. There are loads of new murdering gadgets and more missions than before. It has gone from 10 hours of tedium (and some fun) to like 30 hours of fun.\n*SPOILERS*\nAlso, the final boss is the pope, so that's a plus if you're into channeling your papal anger.", "hours": 93.1, "user_id": "76561198080021055", "username": "Neon Jesus", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
