{"product_id": "33230", "page": 350, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-08", "text": "Although the game is good, the launching process is a TOTAL CHAOS. WTF IS UPLAY DOING IN STEAM? And it even crashes on the intro movie! NICE ONE FOR 20 BUCKS! I am VERY upset for this amazing game.\nEDIT: I now recommend this game because I noticed that it just takes a long while to launch. Very good game btw", "hours": 7.7, "username": "Vulpes Ignis", "products": 118, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 350, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "The seamlessness of the parkour and, to a lesser extent, combat flow (both from the first game) is revolutionary in its own way. The animation is plenty enough to get excited about, and parkour chase/escape scenes work especially well, letting you focus on where you want to go and the method of your escape, whilst the execution of jumps, turns and climbs is mostly automated.\nTurn off the minimap. Instead, bring up the full map when you get a new objective, then follow the streets, landmarks, and your sense of direction, to find the target, and your camera to search for guards. Make yourself be drawn into the beautiful recreations of beautiful cities, the colours, the changing atmospheres, the rich environmental soundscape enhancing with understated music, and you might just fall in love with this game.", "hours": 33.3, "username": "72.8% Water", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 350, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "+ awesome story\n+ awesome music! (Jesper Kyd)\n+ nice places (Firenze, Venice, Toscana etc.)\n+ start to worth to make optionals\n+ balanced content\n- still poor fight", "hours": 60.3, "user_id": "76561198069358881", "username": "juhasz.roland.istvan", "products": 224, "early_access": false}
