{"product_id": "33230", "page": 351, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "I can't the describe the feels this game gives me. I think tha AC2 and Brotherhood are just 2 masterpieces in the AC saga and probably the whole modern gaming generation. I remember playing this the first time on a ps3, and some days ago it was on sale, and I got caught by nostalgia and decided to buy it. Probably the best spent money in my life. Also, I live in Italy... so the feels are really. The places are so well done and just look so real, like they where taken directly from here! The graphics are the only thing that might disappoint you... in 2010 we had some really good games with amazing graphics, and AC2 really wasn't up to the standars, and it still isn't of course. But you know, the emotions a game gives you is what really matters. Great game. Get it.\nP.s. the mac port is fairly decent\nP.s.s. you might have to rebind some keys on your keyboard and find the best setup that's good for you... cause default is seriously messed up", "hours": 18.7, "username": "Tyler, The Creator", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 351, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Well, like so many others i bought this game and \"uplay\" ubisoft proprietary drm system doesn't work so i can't play the game i paid for. SAVE YOUR MONEY... ubisoft and steam have evidently colaborated to rob people :(", "hours": 2.0, "user_id": "76561198087773402", "username": "chomp_u", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 351, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "This by far has the best story out of all the Assassin's Creed games, but graphics are not the greatest. Like Ezio the best of all Desmond's relatives.\n9/10", "hours": 47.4, "username": "Sn0w CrAb", "products": 47, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 351, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed II\n+ Exploration is great\n+ Great story, from babyborn to middle aged man\n+ Renaissance Italy\n- Little different with low and ultra setting\n- I'm real assassin! I don't need armor! Take it off from me!\n- Sometimes the parkour is crap!", "hours": 18.2, "username": "Talos", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 352, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Pros\n-Does not get boring can play for six hours straight!\n-Good Story\n-Smooth Parkour\n-No Bugs Or Glitches\n-Good Graphics even to 2014 standards\n-Good Story\n-Good Combat System\n- i got it for $7 on sale but even at $11 it is VERY WELL PRICED\nCons\n- Instead of saying; \"Press Q\" The game will say \"Press []\" Which means you have to dig through 4 menus and look at the controls to see what button [] actually means but after 1-3 hours you get used to this\n-after a while you can't even take one step out side before being spotted by a billion guards\n-beggers\n- Controls take a long time to get used to  UP TO 1-3 HOURS!\n- uses U-Play and i had to reinstall U-Play TWICE for the game to work\nMost of the faults/cons are minor so i give this game a\n9.5/10", "hours": 12.8, "username": "SquattingLatvian tupus latvietis", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 352, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Didn't play it, couldn't play it. Uplay is terrible. Have to sign up for 2 different accounts just to start the game. I'm sure the game is great, AC games get great reviews. But this port, with Uplay and steam is terrible. I wish there was a disclamer in the steam store that said in GIANT letters. \"Needs some stupid other program to even have a chance of running'", "hours": 0.8, "user_id": "76561198145199101", "username": "hellicrination", "products": 22, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
