{"product_id": "33230", "page": 352, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-04", "text": "While this is a really fun game, I do have to say it has some major issues.\nPros:\n-Fun parkour\n-Well-told story\n-Assassination is fun\n-Lots of extras\n-Authentic-feeling historical setting\n-Open-ended levels with multiple ways to do things\nCons:\n-Inconsistent narrative\n-Repetitive combat\n-Crap controls\n-Stealth is near impossible\n-Uplay integration (not really an issue for me, but might be one for you)\nIn all honestly, it's a game worthy of twenty to thirty dollars, and it's a fun way to kill some hours over the weekend. Just know what you're getting into before you give it a shot.", "hours": 25.0, "username": "Troll Under The Bridge", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 353, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "I love this game.\n\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Uplay. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 uplay.", "hours": 5.8, "username": "Icedoktaine", "products": 454, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 353, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "A fun and exciting sequal that improves upon the first game in all the right ways.\nGameplay - 4\nGraphics - 4\nStory - 3\nUI - 4\nReplay Value - 3\nOverall - 4\nGripes:\nUpgrading your home didn't really do much in terms of story or gameplay.\nThe game was a bit too easy.\nIn debth:\nMore to come...", "hours": 33.9, "user_id": "76561197969628949", "username": "ImAGodDmnDragn", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
