{"product_id": "33230", "page": 367, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-04", "text": "Who ever made the kill animations in this game deserves a medal.I know this game is quite old, it's still good, afterall it is an assassins creed game. 9/10. a bit clunky at points but really cool. :D", "hours": 80.5, "username": "big lad", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 367, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-03", "text": "This is what got me into Assassins 's Creed, still holds up well even today. The story isn't the greatest but the game play makes up for it. Graphics are really good too, given the age of the game.", "hours": 12.8, "username": "BlazinJ77", "products": 184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-03", "text": "If you your thinking of buying this game. Let me tell you, this game will put you under the hood of the one of gamings best protaganists. The name \"Ezio Auditore Da Firenze\" is one you will never forget.\nI must warn you though, that this is a 3 parter game, starting with the begining in ACII, then AC Brotherhood, and lastly the conclusion in AC Revelations. so plan to get all 3 on sale if you can, and prepare for the ride of your gaming life.\n(Xbox controller is highly reccomended)                                              on average i give this trilogy a 8/10", "hours": 71.7, "user_id": "76561198026943694", "username": "Nyx-Nul", "products": 114, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "So great", "hours": 48.2, "user_id": "76561198068559623", "username": "hedyX", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "This game has some of the best character development in any game. You start off with Ezio being born, a small defenceless baby. You translate that into an irrogant teenager, thinking he is invincible. A family tradegdy then converts him into a mess of emotions. By the end of the game he has grown into a fully mature man, realising what life is really like.   \"Nothing is True. Everything is Permitted\" - the interpretation of this phrase shows you where he is at, maturity wise.\nOverall, a great game with many improvements from the original, but its the complexity of character that compells me\n9.5/10", "hours": 28.9, "user_id": "76561198023478253", "username": "^0JD", "products": 138, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "This is a very good Assassin's Creed game. I enjoyed every single hour of my 20h run! It has a very immersive story and there is a lot of attention put on riddles!\nPlay&Enjoy it!", "hours": 60.0, "username": "Xfiudong", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "Found this game boring. Lots of running back and forth.", "hours": 2.0, "user_id": "76561198031758729", "username": "sligocki", "products": 170, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "AC 2 is great game, much better gameplay,\ngood story.\nmore weapons.\nmore options.\nDefinitely recommend this game to everyone.", "hours": 21.0, "username": "KingSin", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "In my eyes the best game I have ever played. The setting, the characters, the music make this game an amazing experience. If you like games that are set in the Medieval/renaissance era this is a game that you must play.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Runi215", "products": 496, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "This game ends in a \"what the f*ck\" moment. Literally said by Desmond.\nAwesome combat. The combat has more options compared to AC 1. Unarmed combat is now the most over-powered combat of all. Able to take on 5 BRUTES without getting injured. Just keep disarming and killing them all the time. Now with multiple Assassinations options, you don't have to run up to your target and stab him all the time.\nStoryline is decent. And as usual the history is a little bit different with so many controversial conspiracy theories.\nI have killed so many innocent guards. Makes me question this creed.\nWould Reccomend.", "hours": 46.5, "username": "Ascorbic Acid", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-02", "text": "Third person, Italian, Renaissance Call of Duty without dog. Good storyline, solid controls and game mechanics, not many guns though.", "hours": 37.1, "username": "PUSSYDESTROYER LITCHFIELD", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 368, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "if uplay is not working...then..completely uninstall UBISOFT launcher from add/remove programme...\nand also delete files from C: drive\nthen download from internet uplay laucher...install it...\ngame will run..normally\nBest game ever...", "hours": 4.2, "user_id": "76561198027480158", "username": "Assassin", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "Just as AC1 most should know this game by now and to a lot of them this had one of the best storys in the series\nthey added a lot in this one comparied to the first and changed a lot fo the machanics which was nice i wont say so no spoilers for any who havnt played but if you played the first you will see the changes\nOver all its a great game and fun to play even the story is pretty nice\nOff the game a bit onto Requirments\nUnlike the first this one does require Uplay and a active Uplay account some claim its couse of that the game doesnt work right and such that is false\nThe game will lag at time and does run hard on the pcs but its not Uplay its there codding in the game itself longs you have ana ctual gammking pc that sint from 10 years ago you should be fine and should run smooth. this is one of those games you really need the recamendded system stats not the lower end ones", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561198010773552", "username": "Nagisa", "products": 387, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "Not a bad game. I bought this after playing Assassin's 3 already and pretty glad I did. Had to get used to the different keybindings it uses but other then that, recommendable.", "hours": 181.9, "username": "rickmagee", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-01", "text": "*Keep in mind that the game itself is good but Uplay is annoying AF.\nI highly recommend this game, I was new to the Assassins Creed franchise and chose this one to be the first of their games that I play, and let me tell you it's great, if you love open world enviroments for you to explore this is just perfect.\nYou can run and jump around like a madman and explore everything, the world feels emmersive and I rarely get pulled out, also when it comes to the fighting it's more about stealth than beating up everything in sight, which I love. The story is pretty good, I got into it pretty easily.\nAll I can say past that is buy it, if you want you could try and wait around for a sale but personally it's worth the full price.", "hours": 59.4, "user_id": "76561198118305870", "username": "ShrugViper", "products": 199, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-31", "text": "good game,good story.advised.", "hours": 9.3, "user_id": "76561198134395802", "username": "Dragofurioso5", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
