{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-30", "text": "Lots of fun playing this if you like jumping on the roofs, killing your enemies silenty with poison for example..\nNice semi-large sandbox game, with awesome storyline and nice small side puzzles.", "hours": 41.9, "username": "Butt Stallion", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-30", "text": "AS is one of my most favorite game series, i have played a few of the serie on the PS3 but when i saw they were on seal i bought most of them :) this is definatly a recommended game and it works well even on budget computers!", "hours": 39.1, "username": "-Malokbahl-", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-30", "text": "Story: 5/5 Gameplay: 4/5 Artwork: 5/5 Soundtrack: 5/5 Verdict: 4.8 Superb game. Conclusion: A worthy sequel to the first game. Ubisoft improved so much about the games formula and the beautifully designed cities of Italy are just there to suck you in. I would recommend the game to anybody who played any of the Assassin's Creed games, and fans of historical games as well.", "hours": 24.4, "user_id": "76561198028599399", "username": "SauronMustDie", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 369, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-30", "text": "Where should I start, this, this was and still is the best game I've ever had the chance to play in my life, dear lord, my heart tingles just by remembering it,", "hours": 19.3, "username": "H72N3VAV", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-29", "text": "Best of the series so far. Not only one of the best of the series, one of the best games I've ever played period. Fantastic story telling, memorable assassin Ezio Auditore, better combat, get to be stealthy and meeting some awesome characters along the way.", "hours": 26.3, "user_id": "76561198084588021", "username": "Duster_Man", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-29", "text": "kill people and make", "hours": 1.3, "username": "BALD_EGLE7", "products": 306, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-29", "text": "I thoroughly enjoyed the Assassin's Creed games in the early years of them. This one was good because of the same great game play, graphics, and story similar to the first one. I would recommend this game if you like the other games of the series or have played games like this one.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561197995957283", "username": "Lord of Chaos", "products": 754, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-29", "text": "One of the best AC games in my opinion besides black flag.", "hours": 75.6, "username": "Water Boiler", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-28", "text": "From AS1 to AS2 the story seems interesting. The end however was a big disappointment.  Lots of ways to make money in the game. I would strongly suggest investing right away into the villa his uncle has, its return makes it a better investment then running around collecting feathers or chests or boats with money.  The feathers and the races are the worst, at first the races were a tad fun, but later on they just get annoying.  Maybe it was the fact i was playing with the keyboad but the races got annoying and i never finished them.  Also i thought the flags in AS1 were hard to find, the feathers are evern HARDER to find.  They don't stand out much.  The game is fun, and the stealthly missions really made it more interesting then just going for the kill, having to use tactics that are there but needed for stealth kills.  All in all a fun game, and look forward to playing the next installment today or tomorrow just to see where this series leads in the story itself although the ending was crap. On the + side at least you can go into water unlike AS1 haha.", "hours": 37.5, "user_id": "76561197962667928", "username": "[SGV] Giovanni", "products": 382, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-28", "text": "Tried to install it, Steam needed Uplay to run, I installed Uplay but didn't give it my true birthdate, because the company does not legitimately need it and it's a potential security risk to give out.   Now when I try to start Assassin's Creed, Uplay starts and then the following message box appears \"Uplay has stopped working\".   And since it appears to be impossible to cancel the Uplay account and start another account fresh, I can't play the game.  Nevertheless, Steam reports that I have played the game 9 hours today.   A friend reports that Assassin's Creed is fun - I guess I'll have to take his word for it?", "hours": 10.4, "user_id": "76561198158544086", "username": "douglasjfrazier", "products": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 370, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-28", "text": "I reccomend it, as it is a good game, but I didn't enjoy it as much as the original. Just didn't grab me in the same way.", "hours": 12.4, "username": "Cpl. Burden R 3294", "products": 426, "early_access": false}
