{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-26", "text": "Derp, bought this game on sale. When buying an Assassin's Creed game i looked up on internet about which one to buy and 2 and Brotherhood came out as the best. So i though 2 would be the best choice. I don't like free roam games with linear story and missions, like you have to do one thing to move into another one.\nThis game is good, but it's just not for me.", "hours": 10.5, "username": "Alfredo", "products": 601, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-26", "text": "Love this game!  Builds so much on the uniqueness of the first, but adds money, variety of locations, and improved mission parameters to vary the successes.", "hours": 1026.5, "user_id": "76561197982416990", "username": "apocalyptic_socks", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-24", "text": "In my opininin the best of all Assassins Creed.\nEven now I\u00b4d still recommend you playing this if you\u00b4re into these kind of games!", "hours": 39.6, "username": "Balgati \ubc1c\uac00\ud2f0", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-24", "text": "If you loved Assassin\u2019s Creed 1, then I highly recommend this game.  Ubisoft took everything about the first Assassin\u2019s Creed and  improved it.  Better combat, more mobility, fancier assassinations, more weapon options, your own city to manage, and more.  Play it.\nThis is a good port and the only issues I had were with lag spikes (very rare) and a specific cutscene that would freeze the game (the cutscene where Ezio first receives his hidden blade).  The cutscene bug can be fixed simply by pressing the key \u201c2\u201d.", "hours": 34.2, "username": "Pertransient", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-24", "text": "diss is da worst game ever made fk codex pages", "hours": 26.0, "username": "powerdarnell", "products": 579, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-23", "text": "highly recommend for anyone regardless of whether or not you played the first", "hours": 154.7, "username": "wongzy", "products": 124, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 371, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-23", "text": "At first I didn't pay much mind to Assassin's Creed. Big mistake. When I was gifted this game I felt like it would probably not be the best game. I was wrong on the highest level possible. If you're not playing Assassin's Creed, you're missing out. The fighting is more than just beat-em-up style. You can counter attacks and instantly kill enemies. You assassinate high-up people responsible for a conspiracy behind the death of your father, and brothers. You even have a pistol later on in the game! Plus, you get to kill a corrupt politician with the title of \"doge.\" That's another bonus to people tired of that twelvie may may. To cut the story short:\n>desmond gets in animus to remember a second assassin named ezio\n>ezio is 17 year old boy\n>ezio's daddy and little + big brothers get arrested\n>fat guy friend of ezio's family volunteers to take care of him\n>fat guy says he'll free his family\n>fat guy is actually mean politician aristocraty dood\n>fat guy has daddy and brothers execooted\n>ezio gets mad and sad\n>ezio keels fat guy\n>ezio gets trained by his uncle mario\n>ezio keels off the rest of the conspirator connection over a 10 year period\n>ezio beats the leader in a fist fight and leaves him to rot in a vault, followed by meeting a goddess\n>ezio gets the leader's staff of godly power\n>ezio gets called desmond by the goddess cuz desmond is in a chamber thingymajikker to remember ezio's life\n>ezio gets socially anxious from unanswered questions and goddess leaves him\n>desmond gets out of animus and beats up modern templar guards and chases the templar official but he escapes\n>the end", "hours": 57.2, "username": "\u00aePepper\u00ae", "products": 232, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
