{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "Having played through the first game via steam, my initial reaction is that the first one is a lot less buggy. There are new mechanics such as picking things up, mission logs/sequencing, and looting, which are glitchy - there is certainly a delayed action feel in general to movement. There seems to be issues with the dubbing as well being massively out of time with the actions of characters, which can lead to amusing/tedious mime shows during set pieces. I suspect as a result of all the new added features the interface between map and other tools is a little unwieldly. But whilst some of these can be frustrating, there arn't enough to seriously dampen an interesting and enjoyable game.\nUPDATE\nHaving now completed the game, I would say the lack of a difficulty curve is balanced by the at times flailing control system. There were several points which felt like a natural end point, but which were then padded out to add a bit of time. Overall, I still have a positive opinion, and I like a lot of the new additions a lot (thanks gods for the fast travel system) - but I think I had more fun with the first game in the series.", "hours": 52.1, "user_id": "76561198024525677", "username": "SK42", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "I just didn't care for this game sadly.", "hours": 18.8, "user_id": "76561198009337503", "username": "SHA33", "products": 324, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "uplay sucks.\nat first launch, uplay crashed at login process, continously.\nso I googled it.\nI reinstalled uplay client that downloaded from uplay official homepage, after uninstall uplay client.\nI could play it first time.\nfew days later\nI launched this game at steam, and nothing happens.\nI just saw a cd-key window. I clicked play button and nothing happens.\nso I launched uplay client and clicked play button in there.\nthen uplay launcher says 'loading steam client' and gave me steam cd-key window..\nno response at all. even a error massage.\nI googled it, again. at this time, I can't find any evidence about this symptom.\nbut I uninstalled and reinstalled uplay.\nand it worked.\nwhat the hack is this?\nshould I uninstall and reinstall uplay client, each time when I want to play this game?\nthis is ridiculous.\nI hate uplay.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "\uc0ac\uc2b4\uc798\ub9b0\ub179\uc6a9\uc65c\uc8fd\ub098\uc694", "products": 721, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "Some game's age well, remaining entertaining and challenging long after release. ACII does not appear to be one of those games. The greatest challenges you'll face are not enemies or puzzles. No, the combat is laughably simple and the platform puzzles straightforward. Instead, the challenge will lie in the poor camera and loose controls. You will never die in combat, but you will die to jumping in a random direction many times.\nAs for the story, it starts strong with good human interest and character growth, but quickly runs down the rabbit hole of JJ Abrams style mystery and conspiracy with no satisfying conclusion.\nThe last 6 hours of gameplay I was gritting my teeth, forcing myself to finish this bloody game once and for all. It was not fun. It was repetitive and simple and frustrating. If you're debating whether to get back into the AC series after years away, I would strongly recommend against it. Read the wiki to catch up on the story and buy the latest sequel, if you absolutely must.", "hours": 49.1, "user_id": "76561198040495167", "username": "Spaceman", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "Great Game, Reccomeded", "hours": 193.3, "user_id": "76561198007270204", "username": "RHIC", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-16", "text": "I recommend this game for the story. The gameplay was powerful for its time, but the battle system is too easy. How can the guards watch their friends being killed without doing anything?", "hours": 32.4, "username": "Hari Esok", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 374, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-15", "text": "Once you get over the strange PC control scheme and the first mission which is ridiculously difficult (what were they thinking?), it's actually a great game! Awesome designs for the surroundings and the main character, and the gameplay has some huge potential. I'm glad that I finally got this and resisted the urge to uninstall after the aforementioned blunder.", "hours": 25.5, "user_id": "76561197982734704", "username": "simesky", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
