{"product_id": "33230", "page": 375, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-15", "text": "Wow, i was so impressed, i heard about, Assassin's Creed is the best Game ever, but it's better. Yes, it's better because it's Assassin's Creed 2, haha. I love Florence, and the history about the Medici. The Gameplay with my Controller is perfect. After i learned it, i never wanna play a game without controller. This game is a must have, for everyone.\n+ Gamedesign\n+ Controls\n+ Story", "hours": 36.1, "username": "DanaRedfield", "products": 267, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 375, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 what can i say about it that hasn't been said this is my favorite entery in the series you play as Ezio Auditore da Firenze, a young Italian noble with carisma and exellent set of skills he is by far the most badass assassin in the series you can feel the pain he goes through as he hunts down the people that wronged him and his family i don't want to say anything to ruin the story but its is awesome i got it for christmas back in 2009 it was by far one of the best games i have played before it took everything that laked form the first game and inprooved it by a long shot i stronglly recommend it for any one  my rating 9,5 out of 10 now stop reading this review and buy it already", "hours": 36.5, "username": "BuFFu\u2122", "products": 349, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 375, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-15", "text": "While I will always be partial to the original Assassin's Creed inside, Assassin's Creed II improved on nearly every aspect of the first game. Better graphics, mechanics, more weapons, more varied missions, Ubisoft really improved on the core mechanics set up by the original. While later games in the series suffer from being too similar to one another, II really raised the bar for the series in a  way they didn't do again until Black Flag was released, and even it is clearly the child of AC II, not I. Great game, great mechanics, great story (that will probably lose you in the next couple games).", "hours": 43.0, "user_id": "76561197990127264", "username": "spitfirem21", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 375, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-15", "text": "- Doesn't saving game progress\n+Great Graphics\n+Awesome Story", "hours": 12.3, "username": "skreech", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
