{"product_id": "33230", "page": 377, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-12", "text": "High premises, low delivery. The game is very iffy, it can crash just because you've opened the men\u00f9 or else, like walking. I've lost almost 25+ hour because the game decided to crash while autosaving (I wanna meet the Ubisoft executive who decided that manual saving is outdated) and UPlay kindly decided to sync that file in, therefore losing almost a complete game. It's very good as game, but also it's very bad being a game.\nPro: the original Assassin's Creed lack some gameplay qualities that where introduced in the II making it almost perfect as game mechanics.\nNeutral: Even if the original Assassin's Creed was based in fiction it had strong historical basis. However this game starts to feel even more fiction than accurate.\nCon: UPlay, forced automatic saving, weak program in general.", "hours": 46.8, "username": "Randy", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
