{"product_id": "33230", "page": 382, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-08", "text": "Just bough it on sale (first timer on Assassin's Creed) and even before getting to the game, I have to register with some stupid UPLAY. WTH? I bought on Steam, I don't need another ****** program (love Steam though) to be able to play the game I just payed for.\nIt's like the dumb Windows Games thing. Why are these things on Steam?? Why doesn't Steam warn people before they buy the game...\nSeriously GFY Ubisoft!\nWant my $$ back.\nEDIT: (after 1hr of play): The gameplay and controls are very bad. No proper tutorial, controls guide with a 'head','foot,'hand' and other symbols - really? Can't you just say: shift, space etc.??\nNo more Ubisoft for me :)", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Marek", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
