{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-30", "text": "The game that set the template for the modern AC games. Ezio is one of the better protagonists in AAA series. Gameplay is fluid and fantastic. The missions are tedious sometimes (too much stealth with instant fail) but it's a very good game in my favorite AAA blockbuster series,", "hours": 30.6, "username": "gutenbergn", "products": 782, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-29", "text": "This game is possibly the best Assassin's Creed game that has been made. (That means better than Black Flag)\nI say this because the story of how Ezio became an Assasin and his journey for revenge is, one, truly amazing, and historically semi-acurrate.\nMy biggest problem however is the fact that the objective is sometimes unclear.\nThat being said, I still encourage everyone to buy this game!\nI have beaten it 3x on my Xbox 360", "hours": 7.5, "user_id": "76561198046835013", "username": "finnanutt", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-29", "text": "This game is awesome.  I only wish all the AC games previous to 3 were cheaper.  Plus it would be nice to be able to skip scenes.", "hours": 293.0, "user_id": "76561198078204967", "username": "zprinter", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
