{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-29", "text": "The start of the Ezio trilogy, considered as one of the best character to have such compelling background. Started of when he was only 17 years old and since then the beginning of him as an Assassin. It took me 46 hours just to complete this game. 2 Tries. And that's not even 100% completion. There is just so much in this world. The hidden secret and all of those things. Despite being a 5 year old game the replayability of this game is just amazing. The game start off at an amazing pace telling you what happen in the previous game quite well.\nI have never played Assassin's Creed, but I heard that this one is the Holy Piece in the Assassin's Series and boy I was not disappoint by it. Great game.\nFor me here is the pros & cons :\nPros :\n+ Great story.\n+ The story of Ezio from the age of 17 till he is around in his 40's.\n+ The game graphic still looks \"Ok\" for my eyes.\n+ Stabbing people in the back has never been so good.\n+ So many hidden secrets.\n+ Great replayability.\n+ Gameplay pretty fluid\n+ Requiescat in Pace\nCons :\n- F***** UPLAY is sh***\n- Still some minor bug\n> For me this is an 8.5/10. Get the whole trilogy of Ezio if it's on sale. But be prepare for the sh*tty Uplay.", "hours": 47.2, "username": "Zgames", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-29", "text": "Free running and city/crowd simulation saves this otherwise abysmal game concept.\nJust the thought of some studio exec seeing the game and saying \"Hmm, it's just medieval? Like that? Well, why not spice it up by adding some random sci-fi poo poo in it? Like what if... THIS GAME WAS A SIMULATION MADE FROM SEQUENCING A GENETIC INFORMATION OF A DESCENDANT OF THE SECRET ASSASSIN ORGANIZATION?\"\nWell, the game's relatively fun otherwise.", "hours": 20.8, "username": "JJ544w5rgh", "products": 798, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-28", "text": "I LOVE HOLDING THE SAME KEY TO DO EVERYTHING. WHY THINK HAHAHA", "hours": 0.8, "username": "Bosco[Execore]", "products": 508, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-28", "text": "there is no way to know what hidden jew-ware has been put on my system through this game\ntime to purge my system\nthis shouldnt be legal", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198015480889", "username": "Lafayette, Lafayette!", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 385, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-27", "text": "", "hours": 16.1, "user_id": "76561198046675266", "username": "Dustin", "products": 1407, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-27", "text": "this game is great.. I think you will try this...:D", "hours": 32.8, "user_id": "76561198128943827", "username": "MrBN", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-27", "text": "For me this game was pretty fun for a first play of an Assassin's Creed game, even though the mechanics are outdated it makes up for it with a fun free-running and combat system. I'm not too sure about why this game is the best AC game to be honest, I think its because people are comparing it to Assassin's Creed 1, and yes, from AC1 to AC2 it was a huge leap, but I wouldn't call it the best Assassin's Creed, the combat system is updated more in Brotherhood but if you want to get the whole feeling of Renaissance Italy and get to grips with Ezio Auditore da Firenze then I suggest you use this as your first stop and work to Revelations. Its definetly worth it.", "hours": 85.5, "user_id": "76561198031321711", "username": "Aaron404", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-26", "text": "Great game, absolutely blows the first game out of the water, the main character is a nice change of pace from Altair. The new weapons, fighting techniques, gadgets and setting really make this one a lot of fun. The story is much better in this one by explaining more of the back story to us, the voice acting is top notch and the game still holds up really well to this day.", "hours": 24.5, "user_id": "76561197966003311", "username": "narc", "products": 426, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-26", "text": "Assassins creed is one of the best game serieses i have ever played\nWith AC1 not being as good as it could have been, AC2 was a HUUUUUGE set up\nIt's not repetitive like AC1 and follows a main storyline. There is sooooo much to do when the game is completed. Guards are more aware of your actions with the noterioty meter where as in AC1 you would run past a guard after killing another guard and they would do f*** all. The final thing is the amount of side missions that this game has to offer. Races/Mail/Beat-up events are amazing and give you a little break from the normal story line.\nEzio is a legend and is so much better then Altair. But it is not the best in the Series. Black Flag holds that honour", "hours": 41.7, "username": "ThePandrus", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-25", "text": "Play it for an hour or two and you'll have seen about 90% of what the game has to offer you besides the story itself. Which is terrible in its own right as well as being part two of a trilogy. Ish.\nThe environments of renaissance Italy are very nice, but I don't think the AC2 team can take much of the credit for those as the more original environments, by comparison, are kind of dreary and unimaginative.", "hours": 22.6, "user_id": "76561197970590902", "username": "moguri", "products": 293, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-24", "text": "The Definitive Assassins Creed Game\nDeep, Beautiful, Immersive Soundtrack and if you are good enough some secret creepy music\nIncredible, Fun, Dynamic Gameplay\nHard but Fun Fighting\nFluid Climbing\nExceptional Storyline and Storytelling\nThe Best Conspiracy Storyline moments and minigames in the entire series\nYou get to play as Altair and they play that badass music from the first game while you do\nOne of my favorite games of all time - 12/10", "hours": 34.2, "username": "Zim Bobway", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-24", "text": "So I bought AC2 at the same time i bought AC1 and thought \"The sequel should be better\" as i hated the first game.\nI found this game to be a sequel true to its predesessor. Good graphics, with a bad sorry, unforgivibly bad voice acting, and more tempar \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t.\nAnd to top all that off, you have to sign up for this Uplay bull**** that ends up lagging everything up and never wants to turn off.\nI have to open my system tray and end the process to get it to shut off.\nScrew Uplay.\nI really wish i hadn't spent money on this game.", "hours": 2.1, "user_id": "76561198043972761", "username": "Professor ZeitGeist\u2122", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-24", "text": "If you are interested about the series, but are not sure how it plays out, I recommend not to buy this one. Buy AC: Brotherhood which is a better game in gameplay and level design. This I recommend only to those who want to start the Ezio Auditore da Firenze plotline from the beginning. For the subplot(modern day), one propably could go for this or the first. The subplot doesn't advance that much during one game, so it really doesn't matter.\nEzio plot isn't that great in this game, it's a bit illogical revenge story. It's feels occasionally quite forced and all the side quests feel like just \"something extra to do, but not relevant in any way to anything\". I understand the game has a bit long time scale, but it still kind of feels funny that Ezio would be spending his time running races on the rooftops against random people just for few florins. Especially since florins are quite useless after 1/4 of the game.\nLevel desing is good most of the time and the cities are quite interesting places. On the other hand, player spends most of his time on the rooftops. There's not much to see on the streets apart from walking people, so there's no reason to walk around just for fun. Also this game takes place in many cities, so one does not get familiar with any of them. General flaw in a sandbox game I think: make the city so big that no one never learns to recognize anything else but the minimap screen. Then again the game artificially constrains some areas as \"not available\" until later in the game.\nI also recommend having a controller to this game. I played my first with kboard and mouse and now I played with controller and it felt so much better, even though not as good as AC: Brotherhood. Especially since this game doesn't have a proper key mapping.\nAll in all, it's not a bad game, it just has some annoying flaws and almost everything is made better in AC: Brotherhood. So I say I recommend this game, but with a grain of salt.", "hours": 91.2, "username": "perato", "products": 448, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "It\u2019s a world full of history and colour, more vibrant than any number of fantasy settings. E Venezia? \u00c8 bellissima.", "hours": 59.3, "username": "Vandy", "products": 840, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 386, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "Assassin\u2019s Creed is one of my favorite game series : really nice gameplay, and something very rare in video games : a strong story with multiple levels of understanding. With this second episode, the game becomes a real hit, and Venice is just amazing.", "hours": 39.3, "username": "Cyrille", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "Much better than the first game. The original AC had me bored after about an hour, it actually put me off trying AC2 and how glad I am that I actually gave this game a go. Looks good for it's time, very enjoyable, fun, plenty to do, definitely worth recommending (I can't wait to play Brotherhood now!!)", "hours": 36.2, "user_id": "76561198032625919", "username": "AfraidN0T", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed in my opinion.", "hours": 25.3, "username": "Gary Paterson", "products": 363, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "Well, I've played all AC games so far (except the minor ones, like Liberation) and I can say that this is the one who made the saga an epic win. Brotherhood overall is the best one, and Black Flag is the most complete one... But this one has an especial place in my heart. Don't get me wrong, I like the first one, but Ezio outstands among all protagonists... And doing parkour through 15th century Italy is an utterly amazing experience.\nTry the classic.", "hours": 66.6, "username": "SergeKent [AJSA]", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-23", "text": "I can't comment on the gameplay as I haven't the chance to see it in action. Ubisoft's notorious Uplay DRM has locked me out of the game completely, and I can not play a game which I paid money for.\nThe game itself may be grand (and I have no doubt it is from what I've heard), but I'm giving this a thumbs down due to how the anti-piracy has been implemented. This only hurts willing buyers, and I will not support Ubisoft any longer if they keep this up.", "hours": 1.6, "username": "[GWJ] Unicycles", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-22", "text": "For me.. the very best of saga!\nAwesome soundtrack, great history.\nRequiers Uplay! (not a big dead, but just to let you know)\n8.5/10", "hours": 33.4, "username": "Pedrogvz", "products": 1019, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-22", "text": "What happens when you take a console game to PC without making any real attempt to map the experience to a PC gamers expectation.  Virtually unplayable.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "wolvesdread", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
