{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-21", "text": "Okay 1 this game runs on ubisoft so that is already bad, but this game does not look good at all and the combat system is terrible. You start off as some nobody and you are not assainating people which is why i bought this game for very dissapointing. Also the game is too hard to play.", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198072600437", "username": "SkiddinX", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 387, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-21", "text": "As a fan of the assisns creed franchise, I must say that this is my favorite game. The story is memorable, the character is interesting and the enviornment really gets to you. FOr the game is a 10 out of 10. no doubt that ubisoft really put a great effort in this game and probably we will see a lot of  games of this franchise.", "hours": 68.5, "user_id": "76561198079991656", "username": "jarbelaez", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-20", "text": "This is the best game i have ever played with an amazing story line", "hours": 14.2, "user_id": "76561198051807596", "username": "Kardiac", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-20", "text": "An Ubisoft Game i think it met its expectations!Continuing from where AC left us,AC2 shows Desmond another of his ancestors Ezzio Auditore da Firenze!\nGet ready for a very nice gaming experience!", "hours": 16.7, "username": "Messiah21", "products": 255, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-19", "text": "great game", "hours": 11.3, "username": "Pieromaniac", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-18", "text": "In my opinion, AC2 is the pinnacle of the AC franchise. It has a great story and atmosphere that was never quite matched by any of the other AC games.\nI've recently come back to it after playing some of the newer AC games and I miss many of the small improvements that have been made to the combat system (killstreaks, dual wielding, crossbow, call assassins) but overall this is still my favorite AC game simply because this is the most polished AC game in the series. It also helps that Ubisoft finally relented with their misguided always-online DRM so the current version of the game is playable offline.\nThe only glaring issue I've run into is the horrific xbox controller support this game has out of the box. The strange thing is that the game recognizes the xbox controller, but default control mapping is absolutely terrible and doesn't match the xbox version of the game at all and can't be made to match it. This appears to be due to a poor controller implementation where they treat the xbox controller as a generic gamepad so that the triggers are analog inputs that can't be mapped to button actions. Thankfully there is a fix\nbut it's still sad that Ubisoft hasn't bothered to officially fix it despite the popularity of this game. I was able to use an xbox controller with the newer AC games without any issues.\nI still strongly recommend this game if you have any interest in the AC franchise.", "hours": 3.3, "user_id": "76561198027141250", "username": "gamer1000k", "products": 1152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-18", "text": "The game freezes and then my laptop shuts down. I have a Macbook pro from 2013 with 4GB RAM and 500GB storage with an Intel Core i5 processor and an Intel HD 4000 graphics. It doesn't work. Money wasted and it is stupid that you can't get a refund.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198089904275", "username": "JDParkesBT", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-17", "text": "Yep this sucks as well - Steam please remove this app from my library list.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198011550272", "username": "Aniphorah", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-17", "text": "One of the best games in the Assassin's Creed series. Ezio is a bada$$", "hours": 41.2, "username": "\u2654\u0418\u00efgh\u2020m\u03b1r\u03b5\u265b", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-17", "text": "This was perhaps my favorite of the franchise so far. The story with Desmond really begins to pick up, and I loved the aestheic of towns in the game. Game play as pretter standard for the AC franchise. Although I did see some improvement to the rooftop running and jumping around. Soundtrack is also amazingly well done.", "hours": 61.1, "username": "Malethos", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-17", "text": "After Assassin's Creed 1, Assassin's Creed 2 is a great improvement. The game is fun to play (apart from some minor free running quirks) that takes what worked in AS1 and actually makes it fun. Being able to customize your villa is a nice touch, but, apart from being a completionist, there's not a lot of incentive to completely finish upgrading it - and once you do the villa mechanic feels a bit flat.\nOverall, a great move forward in the franchise.", "hours": 35.5, "user_id": "76561197972037748", "username": "Scoilt", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 388, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-16", "text": "Can't even get into the game...", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561198089670209", "username": "Atomic_4_Skin", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-16", "text": "Great game, horrible system. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 YOU UPLAY", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198070673048", "username": "Boleslaw the Cheese", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed II takes everything that was good about the first installment and improves it. It also takes all the complaints in the first one and does away with them entirely.\nThe story is engrossing and captivating. You wanted to keep playing, even after fatigue had set in, to continue the story and see what happens next. The characters are lively and entertaining while adding to the overall story of the game.\nWhile I am a fan of adding and improving the variety of your arsenal, you will find yourself sticking to your hidden blade most of the time. Not that this is neccesarily a bad thing; it just happened to be how I played it.\nThe only thing one needs to know of this game is it is a must have, especially if the first one was able to suck you in.", "hours": 40.2, "user_id": "76561198072889036", "username": "Xaryn", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-15", "text": "The best title in the series :D", "hours": 36.1, "user_id": "76561198049515114", "username": "Ayam Penyet President", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-15", "text": "A good (if perhaps a bit repetitive) game...\n...But Uplay :'-(", "hours": 8.7, "user_id": "76561197970904710", "username": "[ratot]Tasselhof", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-14", "text": "The game mechanics have improved 10 fold compared to the fist assassin's creed. its a lot of fun and has lots to do. with a decent story line to boot", "hours": 69.3, "user_id": "76561197963971267", "username": "Leem", "products": 329, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-09-13", "text": "Biggest let down of the week. I've looked online and found (as you will see) that people are having trouble with Ubisoft's\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665laucher that crashes every time you try and sign in. Which seem ok. Well you need to sign in on that stupid thing to run your game. Thanks Ubisoft. Don't waste your 20 dollars. I love the Assasin's Serise dearly, but trust me when i say \"get it on console.\"", "hours": 18.4, "user_id": "76561198127917046", "username": "Cragg", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-13", "text": "Let's just say Ezio's a sweetheart. Who kills people.", "hours": 28.0, "username": "abloodynerd", "products": 441, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 389, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-13", "text": "Having Played AC I, II, Brotherhood and Revelations I must say this game is the best of them. I really liked the Story and the Gameplay. You don't need to play any other Assassins Creed besides Assassin's Creed 2!", "hours": 26.0, "username": "Byder", "products": 383, "early_access": false}
