{"product_id": "33230", "page": 391, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is one of my favourite games of all time. Its predecessor, Assassin's Creed, is also an incredible game, but the sequel took the already-hightened bar and heaved it through the roof. The mix of history and fiction is a beautiful thing, and the inclusion of real-life figures from history, such as Leonardo da Vinci or Niccolo Machiavelli, makes it even more historically interactive. The continued theme and story from the first game in the series proves to remain just as captivating if not even more so. The gameplay is amazing and the things you are able to do with your character (in both combat, customization and just overall movement) are incredible. With all the things you can do, the amazing plot and the fun customization options, I highly recommend this game for any gamer, with a special recommendation for history buffs such as myself.", "hours": 40.2, "username": "The Watchman", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 391, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-05", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is the second game in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Creed Franchise (No Sh*t Sherlock) and is a great starting point. This is one of the those cases where the sequel is better than the original. That's a good thing because that's what a great sequel should be, better. The Story is very intersting but can be confusing during some parts. One thing I kind of had a problem is putting Leonardo Da Vinci in the game because after about 1/3 0r 1/2 through the game he just stops being involved in the plot. The Gameplay is very fun like the Parkour but the combat is just Blech. I try to avoid combat because I don't like it very much and the noriety bar will fill up making guards recognize you faster. But since there's a lot of combat I recommend getting good armor and using the hidden blade as much as possible. One thing I didn't likeabout the Parkour--This is kind of a nitpick--is that I would sometimes fall from 4 stories up and land onto a 1st story window being just fine. I know you could just say it's Video Game Logic but I've been doing more Parkour IRL and I find it Ridiculous that Ezio Auditore can do this kind of stuff. This next thing is random: In the begining you play as him as a new born child.\n[SPOILERISH] I warned you. The ending doesn't make a lot of sense but I kind of understood it. at first I was with Desmond like, \"What. The. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.\" but it kind of made a little sense.\nTL;DR - Solid Story, Fun Parkour, meh Combat\nFinal Rating - 8/10", "hours": 24.5, "username": "Nighthawk", "products": 172, "early_access": false}
