{"product_id": "33230", "page": 392, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-31", "text": "Very great game!, a huge improvement over AC1 and I liked the more open world style feeling of the game. I think also the cities and all the extra information they gave about the buildings and the people are very interesting, it actually made me go to Google sometimes to read even more about the history.", "hours": 40.7, "username": "Etherus", "products": 1699, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 392, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-30", "text": "The game that introduced the best character of the series, Ezio. He is the man and has the best story of all the characters in the series. This game is the first in a trilogy of featuring the best adventures in the series, following Ezio as he starts as a young man and ends with a much older, seasoned man.", "hours": 89.4, "username": "Cousss", "products": 979, "early_access": false}
