{"product_id": "33230", "page": 393, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-22", "text": "I played this when it came out. Still a great game for anyone. Better history lesson than what my teacher teaches at school.", "hours": 29.3, "username": "bombaykid", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 393, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-21", "text": "An excellent game, it improved upon the best features of the first and got rid of most of it's failings. The storyline is very engaging (who doesn't like a conspiracy theory that spans millenia) and well told through cutscenes, flashbacks, items, and in game events. Combat is more varied than in the first one and took some practice to master, which is always good because it then feels like it takes skill rather than button mashing or simple 'timed clicking'. Again, the open world was excellent and climbing random buildings was great fun, though I did find at times that I couldn't go somewhere that I expected to be able to which was frustrating. The developers also threw in some more collectables and the ability to add items to a 'house', which seemed like just a gimmick at first, but was somewhat addictive when actually playing.\nDefinitely going to play the other games in the series.", "hours": 41.3, "username": "wackozacko", "products": 471, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 393, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-20", "text": "So take Assassin's creed one and fix 80% of what sucked about it and you have Assassin's creed 2...its just a much better game.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "Verolain", "products": 967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-20", "text": "In my opinion best ac game. If u like other assassin's creed games u will love this. Controls are better than in other ac games. and story is amazing.", "hours": 7.2, "username": "The Grim Reaper", "products": 213, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-19", "text": "Eh, it was good fun exploring the cities - parkour! - and the storyline was decent, but I found the combat boring and certain quests, like tailing quests, to be incredibly irritating. Assassin's Creed 2 definitely improves on the original, as the vistas look really damn shiny, the lore is much deeper, Desmond isn't a useless \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, and yay, Renaissance Italy! However, the blah combat, ridiculous monetary system (honestly, after a little investing, you could basically win the Assassin Templar war by buying out all their property because that is how much money you end up with >> ), and that annoying camera angle change that causes you to leap off ledges.... :P Well, I had fun, but the fun was intersperced with moments of frustrationi.", "hours": 39.9, "user_id": "76561198094811515", "username": "teawithcthulhu", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed game series are kind of masterpiece to me.\nThey are nice open-world games with catchy story together with virtual-travelling agency :). You can visit beautifuly modeled cities in their most famous times. Living cities.\nAC2?\n+++ aka Pros\nBeautiful graphics, even nowadays. Everything modelled and textured with artistic feeling. Everything fit its place. Real work of architectonics.\nDynamic time of day.\nStreets full of people so one can feel really living city.\nIf you get bored in Venice, just go relax and drive gondola, watch city life mirroring on channel waters between houses during sunset.\nVery nice audio environment too. Heralds shouting their anounces. People talking each to other. Vendors shouting their offers. Just close your eyes and you can easily be there in those living cities.\nMain character Ezio runs and jumps same easy and flow as Altair did before him. And it is same fun.\nClimb or jump EVERYWHERE. Absolute freedom of movement!\nCombats - i'd rather avoided conflicts and when it was about fight i just tried run away. And when it really came it was fun. Lot of attacks and combos with counterattacks. Just do your clickity-clicks and watch Ezio dance his \"danse macabre\" between enemies :).\nCombats II. - you think you can run over the rooftops? :) Beware, guards are able to pursuit you even there.\nNice side jobs, eh, assassinations ;), because what could Ezio better than that. And i loved those boat/ships hijacking, get there unnoticed and do my job.\nI found or encountered almost no bugs or glitches.\n--- aka Cons\nI HATED FIXED CAMERA and/or AC2 CAMERA OVERALL SO MUCH! (sometimes ;))\nOne can very soon got really feel \"hey, i am console port\" - i can imagine with gamepad could be playing less frustrating in some parts (every time when game switches from player camera to some fixed camera in space etc.). It can get really frustrating even more when you raid some of Templar lairs or Assassins tombs, there are enviromental puzzles, which completing means very often to be fast with Ezio and jump and climb very precise with precise timing. Which icould be hard when you run a wall and suddenly, camera switches to some weir fixed position and because Ezio's movement is related to camera it could switch Ezio's direction during his movement in no time ... and you finish somewhere else where you shouldn't.\nAnother due to console-port pain - it is the graphics. It is nice, but no one can really tune it up. In case of shadows and LOD distance even at highest settings one can see popping higher geometry details or drawing shadows in front of his eyes.\nAlso sometimes in combat, mostly in tight streets and/or closed spaces camera does its strange work and ends in tree or in Ezio's body so you hardly can see what is happening ... during combat :/\nNo one of guards can swim. Just run, run, run and jump into the water, if you can and swim out of area of distraction and you are safe. No one will hunt you on water. Looks strange in rest of almost perfect gameplay and AI behavior. Guards just watches you swim away, eventually shouting and throwing rocks at you :).\nConclusion:\nSame as AC1 was AC2 has fantasy, but yet very believable and catchy story, decently built on pillars of real historical events. One has a huge opportunity to expand his knowledge during gameplay about parts of history which formed our today euro-atlantic civilization. This is what i loved on AC1 and i loved it again in AC2.\nVery good game with over 50 hours of playtime if you do all side missions/jobs.\nLooking forward to play next games in AC series.", "hours": 71.1, "user_id": "76561198076587335", "username": "bujablaster", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-19", "text": "This game was an improvement on the first, and it certainly is still fun to play. The story and gameplay are still excellent, and the added variety to the missions don't give it that repetitive feel that the first one had. The customisation element is nice as well, and the interactions outside the Animus are not bad, given there aren't many. Ubisoft took a step in the right direction with this game, and it is still worth the buy.", "hours": 42.2, "username": "DarkBlade", "products": 559, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-08-18", "text": "Had I known, what extreme \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t Uplay is, I would never had bought the game.", "hours": 157.4, "user_id": "76561198010486681", "username": "Titus Pullo", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-17", "text": "The best AC ever is either this or AC4. If you want to play AC, buy this. Only real negative is that it's kind of a bad console port so the prompts on screen are all for controllers. You can fix this pretty easily though by just playing with a controller or by learning the controls through trial and error.\n9.5/10", "hours": 20.5, "username": "djsfnksdf", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-17", "text": "GOOD GAME", "hours": 20.4, "user_id": "76561198096390030", "username": "T3P7", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-17", "text": "The next one should be in China and the main character voiced and modelled on Jacky Chan (I suppose this will mean he's \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing old but who cares)", "hours": 51.8, "username": "a good wan\u043a", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 394, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-08-17", "text": "This game is quite impressive, even though its got a few years on it, it remains a strong and enjoyable game, that I can honestly reccomend to anyone seeking action, adventure, lots of insight into a new world, and a ton of awesome free running.\nThis game has a very solid story, maybe a bit fantastical to some degree, but solid nonetheless, by that I mean it keeps you hooked, you want to know what happens next, you want to know how this happened, and you want to excperience this feeling over, and over again.\nI might be a bit biast, but I'm not too worried about that, this game is great,which is why I would wholeheartedly tell you to get it personally if I got, but I can't, so this should do.", "hours": 46.2, "user_id": "76561198074284105", "username": "Bordity", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
