{"product_id": "33230", "page": 399, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-29", "text": "Great Game but...\nThe game itself is great. Gameplay is fun and the storyline is pretty good too. Graphics are decent but..\nThe game randomly lags. I have a decent laptop (3Ghz 8GB, with built in graphics [at 1GB]) and the thing still lags. After awhile I figued out the only way to fix this is either restart your computer or give it a few hours before starting again. This is really annoying but besides this it is an awesome game.\nAs a side note Ubisoft have never been well know for their amazing console ports. I had problems with Far Cry 3 for awhile but it was later fixed", "hours": 26.0, "username": "lukethadrummer", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 399, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-29", "text": "My old review was me rating this down but i worked out a way to help everyone to get it to work.\n1. unistall the game if you havent already\n2. install uplay from the website\n3.go register game code on uplay\n4. type the assassins creed code in\n5. close steam\n6. press play on assassins creed 2 in uplay\n7. it will launch steam and install it\n8.wait till its done\n9. press play on uplay not steam\n10. have fun\n10/10\nrate up if this helps", "hours": 5.5, "username": "REM1X", "products": 105, "early_access": false}
