{"product_id": "33230", "page": 409, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-02", "text": "While the games mechanics are a little dated, the game still offers a pretty good story. It runs a little long and can get a little repeative (you kill one or two main guys and move on the the next chapter). It's got some puzzle elements (that can be hella creepy). The climbing controls can make you wanna put your fist though a wall. But it's an older game now, so you can look past all those minor annoyances (also since they're approved upon in sequels). If you're looking to jump on the Assassin's Creed train, I'd suggest starting here. (The first game doesn't hold it's age well, I don't think.) ACII's got sealth but not in a super serious style, platforming and there's lots of stabbing. Oh and collectibles, lots of collectibles.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "AussieCrystalis", "products": 173, "early_access": false}
