{"product_id": "33230", "page": 409, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-02", "text": "This game is no doubt a great one.\nStaff reproducing the beauty of Florence and Venice so perfectly that I want to be there badly.I got the same feeling playing AC1, sightseeing in Jeruslem.\nBeyond question, Ezio's family is the best tune of AC2.\nIn this sequal, assassination operates more easily.You can kill the target either from above, or from below, let alone from a hiding spot.You have different methods to assassinate your target, rather than walking quietly and stab in the back, or cut throat.\nThe DLC contains several mission in Florence, which are quite challenging. I practically learned by myself how to infiltrate a highly protected ship and assassinate all the staff after, no less than 20 failures.\nAbove all, no matter what type of game you usually prefer, this one will NOT let you down.", "hours": 41.1, "user_id": "76561198099180267", "username": "soldadad", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "This game is amazing, I Reconmend it to anyone, I never played the first game, but i think that this one is great place to start.", "hours": 235.1, "user_id": "76561198086036475", "username": "LordofGlencoe", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is an open-world Third Person Action/Stealth game that takes place in Renaissance Italy. You play as Ezio Auditore, an Italian noble, as he seeks to gain revenge on his enemies and further the causes of his faction, the Assassins. Much like the first game, gameplay is split between modern times where you play as Desmond (and not a whole lot happens), and historic times which is where the majority of gameplay takes place.\nThe game is vastly superior to the first in the series, expanding on nearly every single area - collectables are still present but are not so meaningless, there's an economy of sorts, the missions are not as repetitive, and the combat has been opened up some. However, with the combat becoming more accessible, being stealthy/unnoticed is no longer as important - the game has taken a serious step in the direction of more action game than \"assassination,\" a trend which continues throughout the series (but which in many ways improves it for how most people would like to play).\nI played and beat this game on the 360, hence my play time, and I highly recommend it.\nNote: This game is excluded from Steam's Family Sharing service, and it requires the use of Ubisoft's Uplay program. If either of those bother you, then I would avoid this game.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Jragghen", "products": 1162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "This game's aged a bit, but it's still a stellar title.\nIn ACII, everything from the first game is improved upon. I mean everything. The climbing, combat, music, etc ends up being miles beyond what ACI offered.\nPlaying as Ezio Auditore, you'll explore Renaissance Italy on your personal quest to avenge your family, but there's much more to Ezio's character arc than just REVENGEANCE.\nACII is quite long, it'll take you more than a few hours to complete, and that's if you don't bother with any of the side stuff. Of which there is a fair amount of.\nCombat is rather simple, but it's satisfying and visually entertaining. No real difficulty to it though. Brutes are a needed addition to the enemy combatants, but they really aren't very intimidating in comparison to how they need to be.\nThe PC port works fine in my experience, though the Uplay client can be a bit frustrating.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Bwettfett", "products": 731, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "Mac owners beware. The steam version does not work on mac. If you own a mac get this game on the mac app store.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198066783709", "username": "SudgeSlug", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
