{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "- Interesting storyline and many side missions\n- New assassination techniques and weapons\n- Various city in Italy\n- Economic system\n- Tricky Glyphs\n- Assassin's Tombs\n- Rather boring at the start of the game (until sequence 3)\n- No auto-push people when sprinting\n- Sometimes Ezio couldn't counter attacks from behind and need a good timing to counter-kill with hidden blades\n- Can't high climb (before sequence 7)\n- No Synchronization precentage", "hours": 48.7, "username": "\u300c\u7a7a\u300d\uff21\uff32\uff23\uff21\uff2e\uff21", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "The first assassin's creed game was pretty good altough i was a bit dissapointed, However this game.. Assassin's creed 2 is incredible, it's 100 times better then the first game and i fell in love with it. The story, characters, the new skills... EVERYTHING is so much smoother and more awesome. An Incredible game i'll recommend to anyone it's one of the best games you can get for 9,99\u20ac at the moment.\nGraphics - 7/10\nAudio - 8/10 ( fantastic soundtrack )\nGameplay - 9/10\nStory - 8/10\nOne of the best games i've had the pleasure to play.", "hours": 26.6, "username": "Vargiblodet", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Great game. I highly suggest playing with a butter bread in one hand, and your mouse in the other. The keyboard is completly optional, and the keyboard actually decreases the quality of the game. Using only the mouse increases the difficulty sevenfold; I have been stuck on the first part for 8 hours. *Note: This review is based on the default controls*\nMy rating with keyboard and mouse- 7/10\nMy rating with mouse only (no keyboard at all)- 9/10", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Goat Milk", "products": 98, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Awesome game is awesome.", "hours": 40.9, "username": "fernandocr04", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 410, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "In my oppinion, the last proper game Ubisoft made. Love this game, its basically a straight upgrade from the first one, It leaves out the whole investigation system from the first game (which I really liked but I can live without) and added a metric ton of content and new mechanics. The characters are memorable and you really feel like the world around you is alive. Unlike Assassins Creed 3 (In my oppinion atleast).\nAlso I swear Uplay is absolute\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 It went through like 10 updates, as if it was installing the first uplay browser all the way to the la\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 one. And on top of all that you NEED to make a special Uplay account, EVEN THOUGH you are already signed in to steam.\nBut yes if you can get passed the whole Uplay BS you can enjoy a great game. Get the game if you liked the first one, this one takes those concepts and enhances them tenfold.", "hours": 27.7, "username": "[SRB] Shrapnel", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 411, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Awesome game is awesome.", "hours": 40.9, "username": "fernandocr04", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
