{"product_id": "33230", "page": 411, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Generally a good game, consequent continuation of the first one. Finally our assassin learned some moves so much needed before (like attack from above). The Only thing I didn't really like was an ending - I think at some point it was overdone.\nFinally - I think I preferred the first game better - but only because I could \"feel\" the XIIth centrury Holy Land somehow better than XVth century Italy... Personal preference :)\nRecommended of course :)", "hours": 40.4, "user_id": "76561197963321051", "username": "Troll", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 411, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "One word: YES!\nThis game redefined the definition of action-adventure gaming. Unlike the other games involving Ezio, which only had one city, AC2 has multiple massive cities! After nearly 10 hours of running around Florence and Fiorli, I found I was going to Venice. They just keep throwing new and exciting cities at you. Furthermore, unlike the cities of the future games (AC3, or AC4), each city is massive and visually different in many ways.\n2009 and 2010 was the peak of great games, and AC2 is the peak of the series. If you don\u2019t own it, get it.", "hours": 60.4, "user_id": "76561198082290575", "username": "krimsalt_", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 411, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Great storyline and a great game in general.  Highly recommended.", "hours": 33.3, "user_id": "76561198015633156", "username": "Mandonut", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 411, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-30", "text": "Bloody amazing.\nThis game has it all. Adictive upgrades and plenty of them, parkour, assassinations with tonnes of ways to kill and it runs flawlessly. The game isnt easy but its not frustratingly hard aswell so at no point does it get frustrating 9.5/10 would bang", "hours": 26.1, "username": "alt0191", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
