{"product_id": "33230", "page": 413, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "Bought for MAC. Have managed to get the game to start once. DOES NOT SUPPORT CONTROLLERS.\n'uplay' breaks constantly and thinks i do not have an internet connection.  Once i got to the menu screen and the resoloution was about 1300 X 16000 so i had to turn off my computer without shutting down.\nA Car Crash , Valve should be ashamed of themselves for selling out and supporting this developer.  REFUND PLEASE.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198131406427", "username": "johnmhblake", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 413, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "I'm sure this is a great game. It looks fantastic. But because I own a Mac it takes a lot of tampering with my computer to get this to run. Then, it's a battle with U-Play and a bunch of trial and error to see if it will even connect to U-Play even though your internet connection is fine. And once you do get it set up to actually run, you find that you can't have a controller, mouse, or anything plugged in, because if you do, the game locks all your controls. Meaning that if you want to play this game and you're on a laptop, you're stuck with a keyboard and trackpad. This game was not designed for a keyboard and trackpad. It's almost impossible to play. I don't have access to a Windows PC at the moment so I'm stuck with this horrible port that I paid for because I wanted to see if I could get my Creed on.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Bopsterjazz", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
