{"product_id": "33230", "page": 413, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is an amazing game. I've played all but III and IV, and II is still so good that I crave going back and playing it again. If you didn't like ACI (it had it's issues, but I still loved it), then give ACII a try. Some people suggest skipping ACI entirely, but I don't. Pick it up for a fun experience, but know that almost every issue with the game is fixed with ACII and beyond.", "hours": 66.6, "username": "Juniper", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 413, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "This game is better than the original Assassin's Creed in every way.  Where the original felt repetitive and the environments all felt similar, Assassin's Creed 2's Italy is beautiful, although now a bit dated.  The armor and clothing is vibrant and well crafted, and the combat, exploration, side missions and story are miles ahead of the original.  The protagonist, Ezio, is likeable and entertaining.  I would highly recommend giving this game a chance, even if you've disliked or haven't played AC1.\nAssassin's Creed 2 is tied with AC4: Black Flag for my favorite game in the series. With that said, I would also recommend playing AC: Brotherhood and AC: Revelations if you enjoy this game.  They continue and complate Ezio's story.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "ablaine", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
