{"product_id": "33230", "page": 422, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "This game is still great. 5 years old and more than three entries behind, but this is still a fun experience-- having to use that stupid launcher is annoying and the combat, while fun at first, is just counter-swing-counter-swing-counter-swing, but it's looks good and is pretty essential to the overall story.", "hours": 44.8, "username": "y = ax\u00b2 + bx + c", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 422, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "This game continues the story of Desmond Miles, an individual who has been chosen for an experiment with genetic memory, where he re-lives the story of his ancestors. AC2 is the beginning of the story for Ezio Auditore, a young Italian guy who helps his father, a merchant, run the family business. Little did he know about the \"family business\", and that he was about to become a key piece in the Assassins history. Without a doubt, one of the new generation classics.", "hours": 34.7, "user_id": "76561198083964146", "username": "blacklobox", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
