{"product_id": "33230", "page": 426, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-28", "text": "Definitely a fun game, unfortunately though through this series of Ezio's life, we never learn much about the Assassin's Creed or their order, besides a 15 minute shocking ending in assassin's creed revelations. All in all though AC2 was a wonderful, tacticful, intriguing, and surprisingly frustrating game. I would pay like $50 to play this series.", "hours": 229.8, "user_id": "76561198064000842", "username": "Queef Stainz", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
