{"product_id": "33230", "page": 427, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "I like this alot more than ascreed 1 the controls seem more controller friendly and fighting much smoother overall ascreed 2 is an improvement a step in the right direction I will come back and update this as I play more of the story I guess the afk hours also count toward game when I leave it on", "hours": 55.4, "username": "\ud83d\ude48[K\u00c4PY] Pimkuma \ud83d\ude48", "products": 947, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 427, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "This is easily one of the best, if not THE best Assassin's Creed game in the series. The open world exploration is great as well as the game's story. There are just so many extra things you can do aside from the main story line missions. I think people have mentioned this before about how this game runs pretty poorly on PC even when having a good graphics card. I had a decent graphics card on my laptop and I was getting under 30 fps in most areas of the game on lowest settings. I somehow get the feeling that this game wasn't ported to the PC very well, but I was still able to beat the game and had a lot of fun. The world of AC2 is vast and beautiful, not the mention the soundtrack for the game is pretty good as well. Combat is fun, and for anyone who has played Assassin's Creed 1, the combat is much improved and varied because of all the different skills and weapons you have.\nIf you have a very good graphics card, then the PC version is great. Otherwise, I would stick with the console version for a more enjoyable experience. I am going to give this game a 9/10 because it was fun even though I wasn't able to run the game very well.", "hours": 56.6, "username": "ECHAN", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 427, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "The best AC game in my opinion. That's all I have to say. Play it!", "hours": 55.6, "username": "Vicxx", "products": 547, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "This is easily one of the best, if not THE best Assassin's Creed game in the series. The open world exploration is great as well as the game's story. There are just so many extra things you can do aside from the main story line missions. I think people have mentioned this before about how this game runs pretty poorly on PC even when having a good graphics card. I had a decent graphics card on my laptop and I was getting under 30 fps in most areas of the game on lowest settings. I somehow get the feeling that this game wasn't ported to the PC very well, but I was still able to beat the game and had a lot of fun. The world of AC2 is vast and beautiful, not the mention the soundtrack for the game is pretty good as well. Combat is fun, and for anyone who has played Assassin's Creed 1, the combat is much improved and varied because of all the different skills and weapons you have.\nIf you have a very good graphics card, then the PC version is great. Otherwise, I would stick with the console version for a more enjoyable experience. I am going to give this game a 9/10 because it was fun even though I wasn't able to run the game very well.", "hours": 56.6, "username": "ECHAN", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "The best AC game in my opinion. That's all I have to say. Play it!", "hours": 55.6, "username": "Vicxx", "products": 547, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-20", "text": "Fixes everything wrong with the original, an amazing story, looks great on the pc, an absolute classic!\n10/10", "hours": 21.4, "username": "doom4307", "products": 2447, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-19", "text": "this game... is the begining of a legend and one of the most enjoyable games i have ever played", "hours": 57.5, "user_id": "76561198111025923", "username": "Papa Yummus", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-19", "text": "Back in Ubisoft's better days....\nWhat can I say about Assassin's Creed II? It's the excellent first chapter in the Ezio trilogy, followed by another great game, Assassin's Creed Brotherhood.\nStory-wise, this is the best in the series. No spoilers here, you'll have to play it :)\nThis game will take quite a lot of time to get 100% but it's worth it!\nI recommend getting this game when you can. It's worth spending your money on.", "hours": 39.0, "username": "Nurse Mathye", "products": 670, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-18", "text": "Okay, first up, I recommend this game. It's massive and yet, at today's price (very cheap!), you'd be a fool not to give it a go. However, I feel somewhat mixed about this game...\nI played for 23 hours...that's a long time while mainly focussing on playing the main campaign missions, alone. I did have some silly side-mission parts (temple puzzles), but for the most part, I stuck to the story. Still, after finishing Assassin's Creed 2, I was almost left feeling a little bored. And the ending didn't really clear much up. In fact, it left things in a very ambigious way. Playing this 4 years after it came out, I'm glad I left it as long as this, as I can buy the next game in the series and play on!\nThe good points = The combat is pretty decent, lots and lots to do, plus those silent assassin kills, awww yerrr. :)\nThe bad points = The control system...the BLOODY control system!! The amount of times when my character jumped ways I never wanted, meh! OR, when I was chasing someone, while being pursued by guards -  my target's in front of me, so I press the lock-on button, but it locks onto a guard following behind! WTF?? Truly, these moments brought out my younger self, cursing the game and the controls, LOUDLY! I can't think of another game that does this to me.\nAnyway, I'm rambling a bit. Overall, it's a massive game and if you love that kind of thing, this is for you. However, beware the controls. Sometimes, they just\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665you over. But...if like me, you want a fairly shorter, less tedious outing, perhaps Assassin's Creed 2 is not that game.\nHopefully this explains my mixed feelings about the game. It was a better AC game than the first, that's for sure. But, a little overly long and somewhat repetitive at times. Still, have at it!", "hours": 23.6, "username": "Imdur", "products": 1162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-18", "text": "Well... I'd LIKE to say if this game is good or bad... IF I COULD PLAY THE GAME!!!! Yeah... so kinda wasted twenty dollars there. Those 1.3 hours of \"gameplay\"is just me staring at a Connection Error message. And beleive me, it's not my internet. I've reconnected, reconfigured, I have done EVERYTHING in my power to play this. I hope Assassin's Creed III will make up for this on my Xbox...", "hours": 10.9, "username": "lavamasterx", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-18", "text": "Got a good 40 hours or so out of this one - considerably better than the first. Plot is slightly ridiculous but pretty good fun!", "hours": 39.1, "username": "[HoB] Turx", "products": 376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-18", "text": "A good game but constantly having to be on the internet to play gets extremely annoying if on a wifi network that is not reliable, at times makes the game unplayable", "hours": 47.4, "user_id": "76561198123353077", "username": "hayden-mcmillan", "products": 115, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 428, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-17", "text": "yes yes yes yes yes yes yes yES YES YES YES", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198063171566", "username": "Vespi (\u273f\u2267\u25bd\u2266)>> \u2606", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-17", "text": "Best game in the series thus far. It's rewarding to attain 100% completion and keeps you on your toes in the meantime. AC2 vastly improves upon the original with a new character, better memories and a fresh environment.\n9.6/10", "hours": 27.3, "username": "DETOXIFIED", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-16", "text": "Not actually a game - it's just an executable that launches UPlay and then fails at that point. Never again, Ubisoft.\nStay away unless you'd like to be enraged.\nUnacceptable.", "hours": 5.4, "username": "with_maltodextrin", "products": 454, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-15", "text": "Don't let my low playtime fool you, I've played it through to 100% completion on PS3. Such a great game, a vast improvement on the first game; this is what Assassin's Creed should have been. The overall story and characters are much better, the game and progression is far less repetetive, and it runs smooth as silk on PC thanks to being a mostly-great port. (With admittedly few options to custumize graphics settings and not recognizing the triggers on my 360 controller as button inputs.)\nIt's disappointing that Steam doesn't have the achievements built in, since they were satisfying to get and weren't ridiculous to try and achieve. It's also a pain that you have to use U-Play in addition to Steam, but at least once you get it set up and installed you don't really have to mess with it again.\nThis is an easy game to recommend. There are some refinements and additions in Brotherhood and Revelations, but as a whole this is still my favorite entry in an excellent series.", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561198024985610", "username": "Ryuuga Hideki", "products": 739, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-13", "text": "The game itself is very fun, but it is a very bad port, because the controls have seperate images which corrispond, which makes it very difficult to play because you have to remember which control corresponds with which image. I wouldn't recommend the game but If you have a second monitor to display the controls on, it would be a maybe.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "noobybear", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-13", "text": "The controls were much improved from the first game, although still beyond frustrating. This game was more addicting plotwise, and I loved the more domestic aspect to it, as you could upgrade and assist the villa you live in. Basically, Animal Crossing with more brutal murder! Exactly the same. Yes.", "hours": 37.4, "username": "sarasansh", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-13", "text": "AC2 improved its predecessor's combat system by adding more variety in weapons, armor upgrades, and more special maneuvers; however, enemy AI is very much the same, resulting in an easier game from the get-go. Missions and side-missions have been made less repetitive. There is significantly more character development this time around and less down-time is spent playing as Desmond.", "hours": 23.5, "username": "Chrome", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-12", "text": "Straight from the depths of Rennaissance-era Italy, Ubisoft brings us the second, and by far best to date, entry to the Assassin's Creed franchise.  This is a game about options, usually.  Most of the game allows the player to roam freely and choose to complete the game in either a stealthy manner or an openly violent and crazy manner.  The mechanics are good through most of the game, though there are moments where the game tends to cause issues like having trouble seeing or reaching objectives.  Ironically, most of these problems arise during a sequence in which you play as Altair from AC1.\nOverall, though, the game works.  I give it 4/5 Florins for being mostly functional and fun, despite a few gameplay issues.", "hours": 55.0, "username": "INVICTUS", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-11", "text": "GTA : Italy", "hours": 38.9, "username": "Cactus Jack", "products": 267, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-11", "text": "Uses uPlay...\nbad, bad, bad.\nSo much of a f#ck arround.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561197967400447", "username": "shadow_walker007", "products": 191, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 429, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-10", "text": "Ok, by far this is the best Assassin's Creed game I've ever played. Why? Well, one reason is because the storyline is personally my favorite as it features a very atmospheric touch to it, and the missions aren't 5-10 minutes long. You have to spend some time on the game if you want to get the very best rewards the game has to offer. Also, if you pay attention to the dialogue and read the subtitles, you may learn a little bit of Italian. Lastly, even though the game was made in 2009, it offers pretty good graphics and shader quality. All in all, this is truely the best Assassin's Creed game so far, and I'm excited to see what else Ubisoft has to offer in future AC titles.", "hours": 17.3, "username": "Mr. Cow cs.money", "products": 115, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-09", "text": "Good game,", "hours": 54.2, "user_id": "76561198039267440", "username": "jnm_tt", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-09", "text": "Just as awesome as u could expect!", "hours": 81.1, "username": "Bitcorpse", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-09", "text": "Mario becomes an assassin. That's one plumber I wouldn't mess with. The prounce his name wrong though. Thanks Ubisoft for trying to be  steam; I bought this on Steam so I could deal with your crap. :)", "hours": 39.3, "user_id": "76561198058256546", "username": "CoolJ S.A.S.", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-07", "text": "This was my first Assassin's Creed game, and I beat it on console before buying it for PC. Great fun, open world, decent storyline once you suspend that disbelief.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "[CSH]altodor", "products": 615, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-06", "text": "Absolutely loved this game, miles more in-depth and immersing than the original AC. Brilliant story line, somewhat improved controls, and much more longevity given the amount of side-missions available.\nFar less in-and-outing of the animus, something I found incredibly annoying in the original, and when you are out, you actually have things to do as opposed to listening to someone speak, 'sleeping', then waking up and getting back in (AKA pointless time wasting to make the game seem longer).\nThe fact that you can live Ezio's life, by making money, speaking with family members, using different character types to assist you in missions, means you become more invested in the game. If I had one gripe about a certain character type it would be that the courtesans automatically leave you to 'distract' gaurds when they're near one, even if you didn't want them to and you were only passing by. I find thieves to be the most effective distraction personally, even if they do accidentally die falling off rooftops a lot.", "hours": 157.2, "username": "ch3shirekitty", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-04", "text": "The best Assasin's Creed episode so far", "hours": 64.7, "username": "Havohej", "products": 278, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-03", "text": "I love the Assassin's Creed line.", "hours": 39.2, "username": "DESYNERGY", "products": 504, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-03", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is a major and in-depth step-up from the first game. The nonsensical hack-and-slash has given way to a faster, more controllable and ultimately deadlier combat style. The so called \"stealth\" missions of AC I where you could kill an entire army in the city square and then \"stealthily\" assassinate your target that was covering nearby have given way to a game style where, if you so choose, you can actually play as a stealthy assassin. Guards continue to be impressively stupid and short-sighted but their AI has been increased significantly and they act more reasonably and faster, adding a bit of extra realism. The blending feature, the game economy, the rebuilding of Monteriggioni, the purpose of having something other to do than just kill people all add to the depth of the game.\nLastly - I will mention the story. A deep, gripping, emotional story of loss and tragedy, beautifully woven from two brothers contesting in rooftop races to the evolution of a master assassin. You feel like you are fighting for something, that you are connected to the game world and that you want to do anything in your power to keep your family safe and your enemies at bay.\nCherries on top - better controls, side missions that are more manageable in size and do not distract from the game and an awesome rendition of major 15th century renaissance Italy cities.", "hours": 60.4, "user_id": "76561198057575998", "username": "Pandelis", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-02", "text": "3/5", "hours": 4.7, "user_id": "76561197998887299", "username": "Sniblet", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 430, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-01", "text": "nice game", "hours": 13.6, "username": "MilanHash", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-29", "text": "what a perfect game.... 4those that dont ply this before its like gta with parkur, sooo fun to ply...", "hours": 36.3, "user_id": "76561197996243887", "username": "Cyka Blyat Man", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-28", "text": "This time the history gets better and there are many new things. A little less boring than the first game. I felt like it treats the player as a noob, many times, not believing in it's capacity. Anyway, a good game too.\nRecommended.\n8/10", "hours": 36.5, "username": "Scarecrown", "products": 564, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-27", "text": "Gorgeous, fun game that I honestly enjoyed.  I'll focus on my criticisms: the player is invincible.  Getting \"caught\" is no punishment as enemies wait patiently to attack you one by one, meaning you'd really have to suck to get killed by them.  The plot goes in a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 direction.   I hate the plot twist and I absolutely hated the ending.  I don't see how the whole Animus thing is really necessary anyway, why can't I just be an actual guy playing a guy in renassaince italy instead of actually being a pretend guy pretending to be a guy whos pretending to be that guy? \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s easy but fun.  7.5/10", "hours": 28.5, "username": "Thundahcat", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-26", "text": "A colourful, vibrant Renaissance Italy that will keep player hooked with its badass-casanova Assassin, secret dungeons, and courtesan for hire", "hours": 51.0, "user_id": "76561198084090055", "username": "Juu", "products": 210, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-25", "text": "My All time favorite game. An absolutely incredible game thats so stunningly crafted throughout that it's blown my mind through the years. Story is very well crafted with fantastic progression. Three beautiful cities to explore as the greatest character of all time (Ezio). Everything from the graphics, story to the gameplay is top notch. The music from Jesper Kyd adds so much to the atmosphere of the game that it's unbelievable. The attention to detail in the game is mindboggling. Ezio's and Desmond's storyline gel together brilliantly. This is the Dark Knight of a sequel. This is not just Ubisoft's crown jewel, it's the industry's finest piece of art ever created.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "KarthikSub", "products": 720, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-23", "text": "Everyone who said this one was better than the first was correct. However, it still had a couple fairly major issues. Because of the pseudo-platforming, there were times when Ezio would get somewhat out of control. I get that it was supposed to be to make the game playable while very cinematic, but too often it had the opposite effect. He would miss a jump that would have been very easy with manual control. The other issue is the game just wore out its welcome. I found the story quite compelling, but it didn't need to last 24 hours without even collecting the feathers. A game half as long would have had a larger impact with less filler to dilute it. Now I need to decide whether to fight the temptation of jumping to III and skipping Revelations and Brotherhood.", "hours": 24.6, "username": "Yoshi", "products": 699, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-23", "text": "i got this game with a humble bundle. it's \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing boring, you always do the same thing and you want to gouge your brain out soon after the first hour. ubisoft suck\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and their uplay is cancer", "hours": 16.0, "username": "Oscar Giannino", "products": 276, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-23", "text": "Play for second time. Still masterpiece game for me. Excelent!!", "hours": 21.3, "username": "TON", "products": 383, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-22", "text": "Amazing how Ubisoft managed to take a poor game and turn the sequel into something great.\nThe environments and animations are still spectacular, but II also has a very likeable protagonist, an engaging story, slightly better controls, an upgradeable base, better voice acting, and much, much more varied gameplay.\nIf the first AC is a 6/10, then II is a 9/10.", "hours": 45.0, "username": "Fred2000", "products": 601, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 431, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-22", "text": "i cant play it because it wont give me the activation code", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561198097310852", "username": "stoner kitty", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-22", "text": "Amazing how Ubisoft managed to take a poor game and turn the sequel into something great.\nThe environments and animations are still spectacular, but II also has a very likeable protagonist, an engaging story, slightly better controls, an upgradeable base, better voice acting, and much, much more varied gameplay.\nIf the first AC is a 6/10, then II is a 9/10.", "hours": 45.0, "username": "Fred2000", "products": 601, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-22", "text": "i cant play it because it wont give me the activation code", "hours": 0.9, "user_id": "76561198097310852", "username": "stoner kitty", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-21", "text": "Theorically a stealth (yes, really. No, I didn't invent that, check wikipedia) game with freerun elements. In practice it's a despicable console port with the worst maniability I've ever witnessed in a freerun game.\nSince the maniability is so bad, it quite logically severly impairs the stealth gameplay. But that is not all, the stealth gameplay itself is utterly sabotaged by awful level design coupled to incoherent AI behavior, going from allies and ennemies alike randomly jumping - and therefore, dying - into water (Ezio - the main character - is the only human who knows how to swim) to ennemies never detecting you when they should, but detecting you when you're not moving and hidden.\nNow, the freerun aspect is far from being spared in this havoc, being worsen not only by the shameful maniability, but also by a very buggy detection collision.\nIn the end, it is a much greater chore than the first: they didn't learn from their mistakes, they did add more mistakes instead. Also, unlike the first one, this one looks like a playmobil\u00ae game; has a very boring and overplayed story to the point where you want to skip almost all cutscenes (but, of course, you can't; even when you have to replay the same bit from last checkpoint dozens of times) and plot elements.", "hours": 54.3, "username": "7heo", "products": 1415, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-20", "text": "the serevers arent working WTF!!!!!", "hours": 0.3, "username": "T-BO", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-20", "text": "Right after AC1, AC2 continues the great saga of assassin's, instead of \"missions\" like in AC1, AC2 ads an history beind Ezio, the new protagonist, game is more detailed them AC1, and keeps the fun, speed, fights, etc... that made me love the 1st game.\n9/10 Very good game", "hours": 8.5, "username": "PunK'", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-19", "text": "AC 2 is definitely one of the best i've ever played", "hours": 35.8, "username": "THPOONS", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-04-19", "text": "Uplay doesn't work...", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198116544003", "username": "RusskiHershell.Make.Russia.Great", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-19", "text": "This game is pretty fun, I just think it drags on a little long. After the first 20 hours of playing it, I thought I was near the end and tried to hammer out the rest in a day. I ended up playing another 20 hours in the course of a day or two, thinking I was near the end, which made it feel like a chore to complete. Otherwise, I'd say that this is one of the best Assassin's Creed's, probably after Black Flag it takes second place. Definitely recommend, but don't make my mistake and try to beat it in a weekend haha.", "hours": 49.5, "username": "kukokekaki", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-16", "text": "Enjoyable to play and interesting plot.", "hours": 75.6, "username": "Steel_Tech", "products": 96, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 432, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-16", "text": "The best in the series. Don't bother giong further than this game though. The newer ones are pretty lame and repetative.", "hours": 68.6, "username": "Emhotep", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 433, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-16", "text": "Assassins Creed 2 is probably one of the best games to ever be created.\nIf you like exploring tombs, killing guards, an amazing storyline, and speaking to Leonardo D\u00e1 Vinci while he upgrades and makes you weapons then please get this game.\nI could go on and on about how good this game is but I will be here for ever, only thing is, that Assassins Creed IV: Black Flag is probably just about beating Assassins Creed 2 as in its graphics and story-line. Get this game first before you buy Assassins Creed: Brotherhood, otherwise the story will not make much sense.\nGet Assassins Creed 2.", "hours": 16.9, "username": "Flender", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
