{"product_id": "33230", "page": 439, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-16", "text": "Ubisoft did a bretty good job with graphics, and the design of each city.\nIt felt like I was in italy during the reniassance period, but as far as it goes for the story then it gets boring at times.\nThe problem with this is that it isn't addictive, I had to take a break every 5 hours of gameplay.\nAs for the game mechanics, I liked them. Ubisoft did a good job with this one.", "hours": 53.2, "username": "\u00c5hay\u00e5", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
