{"product_id": "33230", "page": 442, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-06", "text": "Unfortunately I have to be critical in my review here, but let me make something clear; as a game AC2 is good, but not as a product. At least, not in my experience. Having purchased through Steam, I was forced to use uPlay. This was broken from the off as I could not play the game with an online connection-searching for a server or whatever- and so I had to disconnect uPlay.\nThe game did not run well either, but I won't whine about why it should. My PC will run games such as Crysis, BF3 and Skyrim fine on moderate settings, but no matter what I tried AC2 just ran poorly. I accept this is sometimes the way with PC gaming, but I felt it was just another nail in the coffin.\nMy recommendation here is 'no' simply because I have been put off playing what I purchased by the sheer hassle I encountered.", "hours": 2.8, "user_id": "76561198023542535", "username": "Astandane", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
