{"product_id": "33230", "page": 444, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Go away Uplay, nobody likes you. Really. Uplay has ruined this game. Really, i've owned this game for a while but i've yet to actually play it. You see, when i launched the game, it booted up all of that Uplay crap and  made me make an acount, only for my password not to work (and yes, i had the right password). so i attempted to get a new password. after doing their stupid \"i'm not a robot\" test, which was a pain, i finally DIDN'T get an email to reset my password. in fact, no matter how many times i do it, I never get an email (and yes, i have the right email). So thank you Uplay for taking my money.\nPs. nobody loves you either, Uplay.", "hours": 28.0, "username": "lexicon", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 444, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Because I was so underwhelmed by how monotonous 'Assassin's Creed' was, I approached 'Assassin's Creed II' with much skepticism. I was pleasantly surprised by how much more likeable Ezio Auditore was as a protagonist, how the story was more captivating, and how the movement and combat systems were more refined. In short, 'Assassin's Creed II' was everything that the first game should have been! (The game would have been just fine -- nay, even better -- without the embedded Desmond Miles storyline, too.)", "hours": 44.0, "username": "CharlieLima79", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 445, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "I play through AC2 for 2 times, first time I followed the plotline and the second i try to diggout all side -quest, hidden stories, hidden place, view-point, tombs codex and so on,  I rly find finish the plotline is just a start for this game, there are so many factors for you to explore, if u are a action game fan and are addict in doing puzzles, exploring in the open worlds and searing in maezs, this is the best game for u. and the story of Ezio is also very attractive. The controls of AC2 is humanized and ez to get familiar with(count out the direction button, only about 4-5 buttons are frequently used in game), and I play it using a PC with i5 core, 6G ram and there is no lag and frame loss. I bought ACB and ACR for a better view of the whole story of Ezio, also the story of the combat between assassians and crusade", "hours": 75.5, "user_id": "76561198103319055", "username": "missLyn", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
