{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-25", "text": "Uplay is just\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and im so dissapointed. Their downtimes are horrible and my saves are in the cloud, so when they are down 24/7 its hard to actually play this game. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing hell. Good game, but \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing hell with Udon'tplay.", "hours": 11.7, "username": "ixzap", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-25", "text": "I've spent a whole lot of time on this game, and it was 100% worth it. Great story and great physics, probably one of\nmy favourite games of all time.\nDefinitely worth getting.", "hours": 42.6, "username": "enSce", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "GREAT game. much better than the first game and has a great story line. I found the controls to better than the AC3 controls and has great missions that include sneaking into restricted areas WITHOUT being detected and most of them were really challenging. I think this is the best AC game ive played so far and i hope the developers don't ruin the future AC games as i would love to enjoy them as much as this one.", "hours": 47.6, "username": "CptnMilk", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Doesn't work with eyefinity at 3600x1920 after claiming that eyefinity was supported.  Could not play it.", "hours": 35.3, "user_id": "76561197970322674", "username": "Lomohai", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Finally got around to playing this in depth after some starting and stopping. I really love the period so getting to roam through Florence and Tuscany during the Renaissance is an incredible experience. The combat is what it is as it's largely you waiting for countering opportunities but there are a variety of moves you start and continue to accrue. Graphics can show their age as they weren't amazing for the time but it's immersive and (seemingly) historically accurate. The tasks can get a bit repetitive but you can always just delve into the story and lore a bit since there's a ton of history to read about. Definitely recomend if you have played another game in the series or are even looking for a good starting point.", "hours": 39.2, "username": "NeoShweaty", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "So after a long install process, I expected to open the game and get playing almost immediately.\nInstead, I was greeted with the Ubisoft launcher and it's inability to connect to the internet, effectively shutting me out of the game.\nI spent hours searching for fixes online, but nothing I could find helped me to play the game I purchased and should be able to play.\nLuckily, I only wasted five dollars on this broken piece-a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nDo not purchase this unless you want to take a chance with the various 3rd party patches, because clearly Ubisoft isn't gonna release one themselves.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Squigly Battle Opera", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "the best ASSASSINS CREED", "hours": 61.4, "user_id": "76561198041738648", "username": "\u5927\u513f\u5b50\u738b", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 446, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "I'm not sure. Bought it because it was on sale and I've never played Assassin's Creed games before.\nNo idea wtf this Uplay is or why I need it. I get points on it but okay. I guess that's the world we live in.\nThe game itself is pretty meh. It feels like a copy of Tomb Raider with a different motif. Very awkward controls that often just feels like button mashing. I've spent a good 45 minutes trying to pass a single quest jumping off buildings and stuff. It's a timed quest and one single mistake means you have to start over. Not really that big of a deal, but when I make a mistake right off the bat, there's no way to \"restart mission\" that I can find. So I have to sit there for 60 seconds waiting for the time to run out so I can start over.\n5/10 - Stick it on the back shelf and maybe play again", "hours": 11.0, "user_id": "76561197988532231", "username": "X-75", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "i have spent 43 minutes trying to get it ready but it hasnt worked. i know that the game doesnt support game controllers but whem i start the game the keyboard goes completely dead and desmond cannot walk. PLEASE FIX", "hours": 3.8, "user_id": "76561198081826128", "username": "avlik3", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "I was pretty happy with this purchase until I saw it requires the DRM-tumor Uplay after installation. An absurd and jarring experience that left me with buyer's remorse and a newfound hate for Ubisoft. Valve should not allow this nonsense to go on sale in their store. DO NOT BUY", "hours": 4.0, "username": "aczid", "products": 482, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "<h1> Simply a great experience</h1>\nAssassin's Creed was a great game. Assassin's Creed 2, though, was more than that. With it I truly got invested in the series. The game is set in Renaissance Italy and portrays that setting masterfully - from the political fights of the Medici to the bustling streets with vendors. Also, a high accent has been placed on the artwork of the period which is a nice touch to the overall experience.\nIf you liked the first AC, you'll love the second one. If you never played it, it's still a good point to start from!", "hours": 6.8, "user_id": "76561198110920999", "username": "Deathshead", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Can anybody explain me why i \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing can't play this awesome game? Every time i trie to launch the game, it shows me tha i have some network conection problems?! Please anyone know some solution? thanks", "hours": 44.0, "user_id": "76561198081327319", "username": "Rolland", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Incredible places, very beautiful houses and wonders, landmarks, landscapes... Why you have not bought yet?", "hours": 46.4, "user_id": "76561198039204919", "username": "F Sawasaki", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "This game is a good example of a developer knowing the flaws of the first game, and fixing them.\nHere one can find everything in the story: from major drama through comedy to love affairs (not like AC3).\nAll characters are made belivable (again, not like AC3), at least distinct from each other, and the historical fiction is executed\njust great. And the gameplay? It's not obfuscated by unnecessary stuff, it's not trying to be a clone of other game\n(AC1 felt like a Zelda clone Imho <spoiler>Final Battle was just like Gannondorf forest temple boss</spoiler>, AC4 feels like Zelda: Wind Waker Clone imho).\nThis game and Brotherhood are the only two games in Assassin's Creed series worth playing.", "hours": 24.6, "username": "duobix", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 447, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Amazing! I really need more of this!\nFirst I didn't think I'd like this game, now? Can't get enough of it!\nThanks to my friend! <3", "hours": 53.3, "user_id": "76561198057644040", "username": "@ngryPuss", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
