{"product_id": "33230", "page": 449, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "Awesome game! Even better if you're a student of history like I am. Love the Renaissance. Ezio is a fabulous character. Play it or quit gaming altogether.", "hours": 39.3, "user_id": "76561197980569989", "username": "Cutter", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 449, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "Why I wouldn't recommend Assassin's Creed to even my worst enemies: \"Hmmm, there are 4 places to jump, one of which is right in front of me. What to do? Oh, I know, suicide!\" Even if you ignore the fact that the Assassin Creed series is hopelessly repeatative to the extent of being downright boring, it is impossible to ignore that for an open world game that bases it's gameplay on freerunning, Ezio has a nasty tendency to always choose the wrong path, because hey, let's put \"intelligent\" targeting into this\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 The result of which is that he ends up either running into things, fall off things or just simply derp around like a headless chicken. If you want assassins, play Dishonored, if you want running play Mirror's Edge, if you want open world fun play Batman. Just stay away from this hunk of junk. Unless you like spending hours swearing at the screen. And no, the story is not genius, sorry, but if you really want an over-the-top conspiracy story, play Metal Gear Solid.", "hours": 37.8, "username": "Fatali", "products": 360, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 449, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-19", "text": "Only played 39 hours on steam, but i would guess about 500 hours all in all, played through 17 times so far. the best game i have ever played. Hands down ruined my life for 2 years.", "hours": 43.3, "username": "The Untalented Dane", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 449, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is great. It's so much better than AC1; the missions are more interesting, you don't climb as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing slowly as Altair does, the storyline is more interesting, Ezio is a more interesting character, Renaissance Italy just seems so much more interesting than Third Crusade Middle East... a lot of things have improved between AC1 and AC2.\nI do admittedly have a quibble with the replayability; you don't really have the option to replay missions, which kinda sucks.", "hours": 56.1, "username": "Wintermute", "products": 190, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 449, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-18", "text": "Assassin/10", "hours": 26.9, "username": "Allwise", "products": 133, "early_access": false}
