{"product_id": "33230", "page": 451, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "Great game. Many useful additions, open world, long game with a great plot, lots of things to find and collect.\nTotally worth it. But first start by the Assassin's Creed I.", "hours": 86.6, "username": "Milton", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 451, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "My personal favorite AC game and the only one so far that I've seen to be a true sequel to it's predecessor.\nWarning: Contains spoilers to ACII and it's story.\nSTORY: This one continues right after the first game. Desmond has uncovered the location of \"The Apple\" a rare piece of eden that has the power to manipulate and enslave other humans. Desmond escapes Abstergo with one of the workers who reveals herself to be an Assassin named Lucy Stillman. After they escape Lucy tells Desmond their struggle against the templars and they're losing, with Desmond she explains it'll help their and for him to become one of them he has to go through \"training\". With that he must go through another of his ancestor's and one of the best main characters in AC to date: Ezio Auditore Da Firenze, an Italian noble starting his journey as an Assassin in 1476 at the age of 17. Desmond also meets Shaun and Rebecca, Rebecca provides the animus 2.0 and gives tech support to desmond while Shaun provides historical information, people, events, letters, etc to Desmond while he's in the animus. What can I say about this story....holy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 not only is this story long but it's both edge of your seat exciting,scary,funny,saddening and all in one package.....except the dlc. 9.9/10\nGRAPHICS: The graphics in ACII are surprisenly better here than the first one. Ubisoft did a good job in caring for the PC version like the consoles. There's some added graphic features and it makes it all the better sweeter. 9/10\nGAMEPLAY: WOW WOW WOW! Ubisoft how much did you put in this game? The hidden blade as it's own weapon? Two hidden blades? More weapons and customization features? Side missions that are more enjoyable than the first? Sign me up! Ubisoft put everything they got into this sequel by innovating so many ideas and it freaking worked! I didn't feel at all hindered by this game and I always kept smiling everytime I kept playing. Again thank you so much Ubisoft for putting in so much effort into this sequel. 10/10\nCONCLUSION: This is the definition of sequel, with an amazing story, surprisenly better graphics, and so much gameplay changes and ideas that worked. The only con I would put in would be the dlc as it either shouldn't have been made or it should of been included in-game. Thank goodness I got deluxe edition.:)\nBUY RANK:1", "hours": 43.0, "user_id": "76561198028032411", "username": "Claylex", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 451, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "Ezio fighting", "hours": 28.7, "username": "437.Tuna", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 451, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-11", "text": "great game. nuff said", "hours": 23.2, "username": "CreepyPanda", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 451, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-11", "text": "A very human main character and an exceptionally strong story make ACII quite remarkable. Exploring Florence and Venice is also a great delight and a visual feast. Overall, there is a good 30 hours of top-notch assassinations, intrigue, and exploration. Add in the fun meta-plot about mysterious symbols and powers and you have a winning combination.\nThere are two main downsides. First, there\u2019s the repetitive nature of the exploring, unlocking viewpoints, and notoriety system. The repetitive nature perhaps indicates the game is a bit too long, with too many similar missions that could have been trimmed to tighten up the flow of the game. Secondly, the combat system is a boring affair, with overly long kill animations and dumb AI that waits its turn to die.\nOverall, there\u2019s a reason why people say ACII is the best of the series. It is a wonderfully realized sequel worthy of praise. Running around rooftops slicing criminals up is always fun, in the game too.", "hours": 37.5, "username": "Brumbek", "products": 596, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-10", "text": "More of the same, for better much more so than for worse.\nI'm not an AC vet. I played the first for a few hours, likewise here. I had no gripes whatsoever- the combat was some of the most engaging I've ever sampled, the story pulls you straight in, the setting is beautiful (I'm of Italian descent so I'm going to pretend I know\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 and in general there is absolutely nothing wrong with my experience, there are simply times when a part of my brain that enjoys games just says \"AT CAPACITY\" and some games I played at that time are never returned to, this was unfortunately one of them, maybe some day I will have at it properly though. Until then, please check it out yourselves- I doubt you'll be disappointed.", "hours": 5.5, "username": "hammer326", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-10", "text": "After playing both Assassin's Creed III and IV I decided to go back to what is known as the Assassin's Creed-franchise's best game. I had played a little bit of Assassin's Creed II earlier, but I got bored pretty fast because all I wanted to do was to run around killing guards. When I fired the game up again 1 year later, my goal was to finish the game without losing interest. And thanks to Ubisoft's amazing story and interesting setting I did just that. When the end credits rolled I had one thought: This was a damn good game!\nYou play as Desmon Miles, a bartender who in the first game was kidnapped by Abstergo Industries to explore the life of Altair Ibn-La'Ahad, Desmond's ancestor. In the sequel you have escaped Abstergo and seek to train to become the ultimate Assassin by visiting another ancestor, the Italian Ezio Auditore Da Firenze. Though Desmond you follow Ezio on his quest for revenge upon the ones who betrayed him. You visit four beautiful cities that you can explore as much as you want to, and there are tons of side activities if you somehow get tired of playing the incredible story.\nFor a 2009 game, the visuals are still a joy to look at, especially at the highest settings at 1080p, but the game is nowhere near as beautiful as Crysis 3 or Battlefield 4. The gameplay is also great. It's a bit more challenging that the newer games, but that is not a bad thing. After playing a lot of Assassin's Creed III and IV it was refreshing with a more difficult experience.\nAssassin's Creed II is definitely the best game in the franchise. The story is gripping, the protagonist is interesting and the setting is full of good experiences and fun side activities. You absolutely have to pick this game up during the steam sales where the price drops down to 2.50\u20ac or your local equivalent, but the game is worth it at full price as well. Highly recommended!", "hours": 20.6, "username": "Moden Canady", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "Beautiful...", "hours": 60.7, "username": "Bill Nye", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "Following on from the first Assasins Creed, I had extremely high expectations for the second, however i'm afriad to say that it just simply did not live up to the expectations. The game spends far too long on building reputation and gaining skills and after a few hours of gameplay, the game itself just becomes intensly boring. Also, due to the graphic levels of the game, which admittedly are good, the game has to run on a very good quality PC/Laptop in order for the game to run will without sufficiant lag iin the gameplay. I would definately not reccomend this game, even when it's on sale.", "hours": 1.5, "username": "MillMill07", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-08", "text": "10/10\nRe\ncommended", "hours": 35.0, "user_id": "76561198073371498", "username": "Nooty", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-08", "text": "I really recommend playing this if you liked the first one. The story is much better and there are so many things to do. The characters are great, and the city's feel very natural as well. The new notoirety system is cool, and so are the platforming puzzles in the assassin tombs. The game looks amazing and detailed, and everything is made more fluid. The fighting system is waaay better, but keyboard controls REALLY suck, just use your xbox controller though, and everything will be fine. Overall a really good experience and therefore rating 8.5/10.", "hours": 49.9, "username": "Samma12", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 452, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-07", "text": "I really enjoyed playing ACII! Great new side characters and a marelous story that provides several hours of fun. Greatly created scenes that really gives off the vibe of Italy. Marvelous music and a great story. The only bad point I found in the game  that it's too short. Be prepared for an thirst for more.", "hours": 65.1, "user_id": "76561198090351297", "username": "Alida", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
