{"product_id": "33230", "page": 453, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-01", "text": "AC2 is more of an interactive history lesson than just a game, optional as it may be. If the history interests you it's there in large amounts and you will likely learn a lot along the way. That aside the game is fluid and easy to enjoy. It's only downfall is that a Uplay account and a login is required, painful if you prefer single-player games and aren't always connected to the internet. I'd still give it 5 stars out of 5 especially for the price. Controller recommended but by no means required.", "hours": 7.1, "username": "ninjaholic", "products": 426, "early_access": false}
