{"product_id": "33230", "page": 453, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "As much as I love this game I have to admit: I HATE how much this game has platform jumping missions. I hate them.\nStill, plot is amazing and I really love the series. This game is about Ezio becoming assassin. Must play.", "hours": 29.0, "user_id": "76561198041614281", "username": "Marbyg", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 453, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-30", "text": "A great game thats made a \"Lot\" of improvments then its predcessor. It has a good story,fun gameplay but combat got boring after awhile, and the missions were mostly fun. Id give it an 8/10", "hours": 56.8, "user_id": "76561198017134699", "username": "Cdc1893", "products": 391, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "Second game in the series and by far the one with the best story. Family, loyalty and justice are just some of the main themes in the game and they are very well executed! Has some repetition but all in all a great game!", "hours": 28.1, "user_id": "76561198040221705", "username": "bumph18", "products": 464, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "one of my favourite games of all time and it is absouloutely fantastic!!!!!!!", "hours": 55.4, "user_id": "76561198119587023", "username": "Shurikenger", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "Having improved vastly over the first entry, AC2 can last anywhere from 12 to 18 hours depending on skill and completion status.  This game rarely seems to drag on and when it's in full swing, you won't notice just how long you've been playing.  Everything in this game is better than AC1 from the climbing mechanics, to the scenery, story, and gameplay overall.  Anyone who ever tried Assassin's Creed and liked it even the smallest bit would enjoy this game and the story is clear enough for newcomers to jump right in.", "hours": 19.8, "username": "Bigredkj", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-28", "text": "1 of The best assasins creed i have played :-)", "hours": 7.5, "username": "J\u272aker\u2122", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "So my story with the Assassin's Creed franshise is that I have started with Assassin's Creed Revelations to Assassin's Creed 3 to Assassin's Creed Black Flag then Unity and then Assassin's Creed II. And Honestly I enjoyed the Ezio Auditore Saga than the other Assassin's Creed games. What Assassin's Creed II offers is that it is an open world game with around 4-6 cities to go to in the 15th century Italy. The age of the Renaissance. This game offers one of the greatest cast in an Assassin's Creed game waay before Black Flag. You get to meet Leonardo Da Vinci, the Pope and Machiavelli. The details in the cities is so good even though this game was around 7-9 years ago. It is so impressive to see the landmarks that the cities had to offer. Now the important things that I look for in games is the display, the gameplay and the customization. The graphics are okay for a 2009 game, the colours are vibrant and they look really great. In terms of gameplay it seems it takes more time to defeat and enemy than the current Assassin's Creed games from Brotherhood - AC4 even though Assassin's Creed Unity's combat is much more complex. But it seems a little more easier still. Customization is a little lacking, but you do get a couple of costumes in the game which is an awesome thing as well. The length of the story is so much longer if you want a story driven game that makes you connect more with Ezio and the other characters as well. Theres not much more to say about this game but I highly reccomend this game as it is one of the best ones in the franchise. This game deserves a 9/10", "hours": 55.4, "user_id": "76561198054564148", "username": "Boba Fett", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "This game is almost unplayable on Mac. It has no support for 3rd party controllers such as logitech game controllers. it requires the use of the entire keyboard to play, and the controls system is completely un realistic for a normal human being to be able to comprehend like that.\nI discourage any Mac user from buying this game.", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561197990112035", "username": "Majorloco", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 454, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-26", "text": "Pros\nAmazing large world to play in. Excellent story: unlike previous game player takes on main protagonist from the beginning of its assassin's livelihood and purpose.\nThe story has lots of humor to it, keeps thing fresh through the game.\nBetter Combat system from previous game\nVisually impressive for its time\nGame runs smooth.\nPlenty to do, side missions are fun, big variety in assassination missions.\nCons\nUbisoft DRM\nBad controls, game does not give any indication of hotkey during the game, have to go to menu to look them up, It assumes game runs with xbox controller, definitely bad port.\nGame map is lagging, no idea why.", "hours": 29.7, "user_id": "76561197971293271", "username": "KRostik", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
