{"product_id": "33230", "page": 455, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "So far my review is a first impression for my first two hours of gameplay. THe story so far seems alittle linear but with a pontentiality of branching off. The environment even for todays time is still beautifull for thosse who know graphics don't make up for anything. My biggest problem for the game wasfiguring out the controls at first. Having colored icons for pc controls absolutely did no elp but once you mentally map the controls it goes pretty flawless. THis is my first Assasins Creed and starting with the second one doesnt leave you too much out of the plot. The combat can be alittle strange somewhat similar to Batman Arkum Asylum. It is just a matter of getting down the timming and process of getting the most efficient kill. SO far te game is very good and has a potential to either crash in flames or do good.", "hours": 8.4, "user_id": "76561198058593212", "username": "PolyglotPolak", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 455, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-20", "text": "Probably the most amazing of the Assassin Creed Games I have played. Highly recommend!", "hours": 35.6, "username": "[KG] Wintermute", "products": 288, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 455, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-20", "text": "Superior to its predecessor in almost every way. More engaging story and cast of characters. Improved and enriched gameplay. More ineresting missions and side missions. Better and more varied treasure hunts with tangible rewards. Overall a game worth your time and money.", "hours": 43.0, "username": "MarheF", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Assassins creed 2 is one of the games you have to get.\nThe story is perfect. It links the tutorials well with the game.\nAssassins creed 2 has outstanding characters with amaing\npersonalities and details.\nDefinitly will bring you into the series!", "hours": 41.2, "username": "Potassium Iodide", "products": 210, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is an amazing game. The story is very intriguing and will throw you for all kinds of twists and turns that you won't expect. The weapons are all incredibly fun to use, with a later add-on becoming incredibly helpful if lacking in the stealth department. The parkour aspect is really helpful since you can get to areas faster. However, no game, especially not this one, is without it's flaws. Stealth missions can become the bane of your existance, especially in the last hour of the game. Tailing missions become a problem when you have to make sure not to lose your distance. Some of the things the game wants you to get can become incredibly hard to find, especially when there's so many of them. Also, the game feels pretty easy. Aside from falling or failing a mission, it's really hard to actually die in this game since the combat mechanics give you such an easy way to keep yourself from getting hurt. Still, I highly reccoment this game. I haven't played the other Assassin's Creed games (yet) but if you're going to start somewhere, this wouldn't be a bad place. 8/10", "hours": 55.7, "username": "Maverick Hunter X", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Really really really nice. History tells.", "hours": 75.5, "username": "Caro\u00e9", "products": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-18", "text": "A great followup to AC 1, the city design again impresses, though not as much as the first.\nI like how characters were a bit better developed and the villa upgrade system works. There are also a few good WTF moments that are comical.\nLike in AC1, I didn't care for actual missions *especially* the slow walk follow people missions.\nI played this game in 2011 and completed the main storyline.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "Findaer", "products": 492, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-18", "text": "The Assassins Creed series has thrived ever since the beginning of the game. In this title, you play as Ezio, who is in the search of the people who killed his family. Assassisn Creed II is an amazing game if you like stealth games, but this one is much less modern so you deal with knives, swords and guns that supposedly invented at this time period.\nYou will love this game if you like to complete missions dealing with assassination, stealth and the storyline. This game as a rich storyline and will tempt you to buy the other titles like Brotherhood, Revelations and Black Flag.\nMy only Problem?\nYou have to download and run U play in order to play this game, which is the most annoying thing to deal with. U Play failed to save my work in this game 5 times in a row, which is why I have more playtime in this game than usual. However, look up some fixes for that as you can fix it yourself.\n8/10 (9.5/10 without U Play)", "hours": 44.8, "username": "Johnny", "products": 213, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 456, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-16", "text": "Amazing... a huge improvement over the first game", "hours": 70.9, "username": "Roxxen", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
