{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-09", "text": "This is the best game of the series. I think of these titles as the modern prince of persia games and lets face it who doesn't like assassinating people in games.", "hours": 32.6, "username": "MyopicMuppet", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-09", "text": "Score : 9/10\nA great RPG open world game.\nu can obtain money for improve ur armor and weapon.\nFurthermore, u can renovate ur town for more passive income.\nA lot of quest that's very great.\nGreat fighting and free running system.\nFantastic story that u shouldn't miss.", "hours": 49.8, "username": "Iwantto Playagame", "products": 785, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "Very very good.\nIn Assassin's Creed II you play as the Assassin from Renaissance Era Rome, Ezio Auditore (Da Firenze)\nEzio is an interesting character that sets out to seek revenge on the Templars who set a conspiracy against him and his family.\nThe gameplay is much better than the first entry in the game and overall much more improved.\nThe port is good and the story is amazing.\nGreat game.", "hours": 52.9, "username": "Vionic", "products": 282, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "Great Game, Bad PC Port.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "Texas Tim", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "This is the first Assassin's Creed that I have tried and I chose this one based on what seems to be popular opinion.  I was excited to try it for myself.  The game is terrific but getting the download to launch was inconvenient at best.\nThis game requires Ubi Soft's Uplay software to launch.  After downloading Assassin's Creed II from Steam, the software will install itself and attempt to launch the game.  I don't know if this works for others, but it did not work for me.  I uninstalled the Uplay software that Steam installed and downloaded a current version directly from Ubisoft.  I registered an account on Uplay and then relaunched Assassin's Creed II from the Steam client.  This worked and I was able to play.\nThe content of the game itself is very good and the extra steps are worth it.  Popular opinion wins.", "hours": 46.0, "username": "sack of kittens", "products": 1140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "This game is stuffed to the brim with random pointless things it really wants you to do without giving any reason to ever do it, while the core mechanics are deeply flawed, annoying and just plain unfun. This controls horribly on PC, you might often find yourself getting frustrated with just trying to jump off a railing into a street and run along it, while Ezio will repeatedly jump across to some other perch or try to run up every wall and cling to every little thing when you need to hurry somewhere. You also use the same button to grip stuff and let go, how stupid is that?\nThere don't seem to be any engaging missions in the story, it's usually something completely trivial, sometimes forcing you to utilize a mechanic you wouldn't otherwise even remember exists, and usually requiring you to do some navigation over the same old boring identical rooftops or streets. Combat is easily cheesable and tedious either way, stealth is disfunctional, climbing is too clingy and unreliable at the same time.\nI honestly enjoyed the first one much, much more. I would recommend this one only if you are genuinely a fan of the renaissance Italy setting, which I personally am not. Although if you are interested in the overall story of the series, you might have to play through this one anyways.", "hours": 32.1, "username": "Antroid", "products": 515, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 458, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-07", "text": "The game is crashing and has many errors if you have money to spend buy it BUT if you dont want to waste your money into a game that is impossible to play without having any errors dont..", "hours": 26.9, "username": "MrMeatSlapper", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
