{"product_id": "33230", "page": 461, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-02", "text": "Second game created in the Assassin's Creed series.\nPros:\n+Good storyline\n+New weapons\n+New characters\n+Variety of missions\n+Retains original Templars vs Assassin's War\nCons:\n-Somewhat complicated mechanics (you can't air assassinate a person 2m away and high from you)\n-Way too much water\nin Venezia\n-You don't go out of the Animus a lot\nConclusion:\nThis game is really fun if you enjoyed the previous Assassin's Creed game with Altair. Ezio is the Assassin for this era, and the fact he has more weapons (gun blade, poison blade, second hidden blade, smoke bombs, etc.) means there are more ways killing people.\nRated M because of perverted scenes that are censored.\n9/10", "hours": 33.1, "username": "Prezler", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
