{"product_id": "33230", "page": 464, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "My absolute favorite of this series. This was the game that got me into the Assassin's Creed Franchise. Ezio Auditore fighting the templars for vengance then turns into fighting to find answers as to what the templars are upto. The storyline and gameplay is really cool and fun to get into. It may have been because I just got out of an Art History class that made me get into the game even more. Since they used historical buildings, paintings, and people in this game. I would suggest this game to anyone who likes Action Adventure in anyway.", "hours": 8.8, "username": "MastaTGT", "products": 971, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 464, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "Improves upon the classic Assassin's Creed gameplay. Good story, large map with different locations and lots of sidemissions. I also like the RPG elements like buying weapons or armor.\nIt is not as repetetive as the first game, but it has some flaws. For example the fight system is fun, but it's still too easy. I should also mention, that this game uses Uplay. It can be annoying if uplay updates otherwise you hardly notice it.\nAll in all you can have a lot of fun in this game, but if you look for a challenge you'll be disappointed.", "hours": 40.4, "username": "core", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 464, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "Ubisoft asked their customers to choose their favorite Ubisoft game of the past decade. They chose Assassin's Creed II, and for good reason.\nThis is definitely one of the most fun games I have ever played. It is absolutely in my top five favorite video games.", "hours": 3.5, "username": "Beast89", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
