{"product_id": "33230", "page": 464, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "loved it", "hours": 38.6, "username": "M3GAD3TH", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 464, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-29", "text": "Sinking tons of time into this game. Absolutely amazing. Incredibly fun.\nEDIT: I would like to come back to this review and give an honest opinion on what I think about the game. I originally made the \"review\" above when I had only a few hours of game time.\nI'm going to say it right now, this is probably my favorite game in the series, or at least top two, as of August 9th, 2014.\nTo start off, the story of Assassin's Creed 2 is above and beyond what I would have expected after playing the first game. It's not just a linear \"go kill this person and come back\" type of story this time around. There are genuine reasons for killing the people you kill, the cutscenes have many, many times more emotion than in the first game, and the voice acting is superb. In the first game, Altair's voice is monotone the whole way through. You could chalk this up to his serious personality, but if you have ever played games showcasing Altair later, such as in Revelations, you'll know this is not the case. It shows that Ubisoft really put many more hours of effort into making the story in Assassin's Creed II the best it could possibly be.\nNow, as far as content goes, the overall content in Assassin's Creed I can be smushed into 15 hours at max, and 8-9 hours if you just play the story. However, as you can see, I have 50+ hours in Assassin's Creed II as of the time this review is being written. I have replayed the game once now, but many hours were spent dicking around in the unique environment that is Renaissance Italy. There are endless possibilities for things to do in Assassin's Creed II, even after finishing the story. The best part is though, that even after finishing the game, I can start a new game and not be bored. That's the beauty of this game to me, and all of the Assassin's Creed games really.\nOverall, this game is worth the money twice over, and if you're thinking about buying it, you really should. I can honestly say that you'll have a hard time regretting it if you give it a chance.", "hours": 52.4, "username": "Svetroid", "products": 440, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 465, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "The controls in this game are really second to none in terms of usability and comfort.\njk\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665unplayable with a keybaord+mouse", "hours": 0.6, "username": "anger management rex", "products": 256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 465, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "Terrible port.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "vanillathunder", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 465, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "I wasn't expecting much when I picked this up in late 2013. Still I really loved the italian setting and the depictions of these places were more accurate than I had expected. The freerunning parkour-esque way of navigating around the world was a nice change even though it takes a while to cover greater distances. And the jumping puzzles are a lot of fun too.\nThe story was allright though I feel like it probably leaves a few too many open questions and uncertainties (Seems like brotherhood ties a lot of these up however). The only other thing I can complain about are the silly default controller keybinds. Check the community hub for a fix. But even with said fix it's still pretty awkward when buttons like'RT' are visualized as random icons during tutorials and crucial moments.\nBut overall a good bang for your buck!", "hours": 41.6, "user_id": "76561198018960615", "username": "Spaceship", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 465, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "Spectacular game with history context. Story of Eyio Auditore is fantastic and it will totally consume you. 10/10", "hours": 26.1, "user_id": "76561198047933953", "username": "Omni", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
