{"product_id": "33230", "page": 466, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "Although the controls leave something to desired (actually, they leave a lot to be desired, and can be really frustrating at first), this game is an overall excellent combination of great story, nice graphics, great ambience and soundtrack, etc. The gameplay itself is top-notch and the mechanics are awesome and really entertaining. If you were turned off by the first Assassin's Creed, this is definitely an improvement, including a better setting (15th century Italy).", "hours": 67.5, "username": "Boristrop", "products": 149, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 466, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "This game is amazing great plot and gameplay there is but only one bad thing it requires to high a graphics card as i can run the latest batman game (arkham origins) better then i can run this game which is abit sad, still great game!!", "hours": 4.8, "username": "Dylan the Weak and Powerless", "products": 338, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 466, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "God damn it, Steam. I really wish you'd list when a game has an extra layer of DRM that I have to jump through to play the game. I had heard a rumor that Ubisoft had dropped Uplay from their games... so I took a chance and bought Assassin's Creed 2. Didn't see anything about Uplay listed on the store page. Unfortunately, it still fires up that crapware and makes me register with them in order to play the game.\nMy mistake for trusting a Ubisoft game and giving them a second chance... but I really wish you would mention this stuff on the store page. I seem to remember that you used to.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "Booger", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 466, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "After the \"bad\" first part I was just amazed what THIS game had to offer for me. I had hours of hours fun and the story is also awesome! Give this game a chance, you wont regret it! =)", "hours": 99.1, "user_id": "76561197960976761", "username": "Alex Sanderson", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
