{"product_id": "33230", "page": 466, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "The only thing this game has managed to do so far is updating (and attempting to update) the mandatory uplay client multiple times, timeout its servers for uplay login, and hang up in a screen that says \"Establishing network connection...\" when attempting to start the game itself.\nGranted, the game was relatively cheap during Holiday Sale, but if all I wanted to do was to stare at the abovementioned sentence ad nauseaum, I'd fire up notepad, write it down and look at that until the cows come home, for an agreeable cost of $0.00", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Kristian", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "Assassins Creed 1 was a great game but ended up being too repetitive and at times a little lackluster persay. AC2 Fixes these problems and has produced a much polished game. The story is more exciting and driven and the characters have good development. This is the best AC game to date and Black Flag does not compare to it.", "hours": 38.8, "username": "Hoovy Prince", "products": 191, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "good", "hours": 22.6, "username": "WOMFN", "products": 286, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed game? Just buy it and play, you won't regret it ;)", "hours": 9.6, "user_id": "76561198095795949", "username": "Dragonborn", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is probably the most accurate update simulator up to date. Not only do you have to wait for the steam install first, but after that it prompts a weird Launcher Updater after which a slightly less weird Ubisoft launcher updater appears, only for an Assassin's Creed II update window to appear (It might have happened multiple times, waiting for it took a bit of time so I don't remember) after which yet another update window appeared for the Uplay store.\nHave almost an hour on it on steam at the time writing, have yet to play it! 10/10", "hours": 17.3, "username": "Fucking Loser", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "I started playing the Assassin's Creed games with this one. I saw many people talking really good about it and I was a little curious about the gameplay and the story.\nI never regret buying it!\nThe game has good graphics and a good gameplay (when you start, you can feel a little confused with all the commands, but you will get used to it).\nThe story itself values the money you spend in this game, in the end, I was like: wow, that was astonishing.\nI recommend it for everybody looking for a surprising and wonderful game to spend you free time hours.", "hours": 41.7, "username": "Bela Chan", "products": 184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 467, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "After I finished this game I am intersted in the series. Took me 31 hours to complete the main mission. Even more playtime if you do side missions and Assassin Tombs. 9/10", "hours": 31.7, "username": "Ogi_Bang", "products": 221, "early_access": false}
