{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "Ha, I'm a bit late with this one.\nThis is the first game in the AC series I've ever had, and with just about 5 hours of gameplay I'm enjoying it immensely. Graphics are very impressive considering it's a 2009 release, and doen't make my system struggle at all even though being a port. The historical effort put into this game shines through - Story outweighs other factors quite a lot. :)\nOnly negative point is that the head, fists, leg etcetera symbols seem pointless, I'd much rather them be keyboard or mouse keys, as in quicktime events I just dont know which button it wants me to press.\n4/5 overall review.", "hours": 6.5, "username": "[DC] PimpOn", "products": 189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is great game with interesting story. Gamplay is a good improvement over the first Assassin's Creed.  With the addition of non-linear story quests, which was a problem with Assassin's Creed prievously. If you like a game where you can staby, staby, killy, killy of everyone I recommend it.\n9/10", "hours": 139.5, "username": "ArFo", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "So much history packed into this game. One of the biggest reasons I love it.", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Apple Giggles", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "This is easily one of the most amazing games I have played. And I am an avid gamer.\nThe environments, the voices, the music, the story, the combat, the thought-provoking intellectualism, the conspiracy theories, the free-running, everything about this game is extraordinary. Years after I have played it, I still come back to it and marvel at it's beauty. They just released Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag, and this game still beats that.", "hours": 55.7, "username": "True Human", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "The story of Ezio's life begins here. This game have so epic storyline sequel that i just can't get enough of it. This with Brotherhood and Revelations are best Assassins games so far. You bassically live entire Ezio's life from moment when he is born to the moment of his death in Revelations. There is no doubt if you like storyline games especially sequels this is the game you need to get.\nAssassin Creed games after Revelations are just wrong, from ac1 to revelations is timeline which just continue, the sucky thing in newer AC games is that the Desmond dies (imagine that) lol and just not worth getting.\nBut let it go, we are talking about AC 2 now, so yes grab it ASAP you won't regret it.", "hours": 21.9, "username": "phaze _made+m1stake -r", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "Controls for PC are a little confusing at times, and menus in game have habit of popping up with the graphics for the console version, but the game plays fairly well, and it was nice to not have to play on a console to get to begin Ezio's story. Loved the game, loved the story. Enjoyed the extra content that the Deluxe Edition allowed me to play with.", "hours": 83.5, "username": "DarkestMercy", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "This game might be a couple of years old, but it's probably the best episode of the Assassin's Creed series.", "hours": 43.1, "user_id": "76561198032652733", "username": "dark", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "There is so much to like in this game, a lot of things to explore and enjoy.\nThe Main Character is really cool and following him over the course of years and witnessing his personal growth is a very rewarding experience.\nThe Gameplay is much more varied than in AC1. Especially when you enter Venecia, it evolves again in a lot of ways that you didn't expect.\nThe Story is one of vengeance, thus it already is cool by definition. You follow Ezios quest to avenge the demise of his family, while rebuilding an existence, it just draws you in.\nHowever, there are points in this game, where I was just frustrated.\nThe side characters are fine, as long as you're presently interacting with them. When you're finished with their quests, they simply vanish, only to be seen again at the end, at which point I was actually asking myself, who were these guys again? So yeah, rather forgettable and especially annoying in the case of your uncle Mario (who has the funniest line in the game), who basically gives you his house to live in and is never seen again.\nThe controls are mostly fine, but there are points in this game, for example when you're supposed to follow a fleeing templar and kill him before he alerts his mates, when you just want to curse and throw away your controller, because Ezio just made another jump into the unknown depths of wherever you did not want to go. As I said, for the most part, it's fine, but it gets annoying sometimes. Another nice example is trying to tail someone unseen, on the rooftops, like a cool assassin, trying to drop on a ledge below, instead jumping on the person you were supposed to follow.\nBut the thing that annoyed me most was the fact that this game just... does... not... end.\nIt's really excessive in it's length, towards the end, there are at least two hours of storyline that give nothing to the story and in parts consist of extremely annoying quests. When I came to Venecia, I figured I was about halfway through the game, I had my Villa all set up, was at maybe 60% with the sidequests. Actually, it was maybe a third, and not all of that rest of the game was good.\nStill, I recommend the game to anyone, it is a lot of fun and has really cool moments.", "hours": 47.5, "user_id": "76561198044970982", "username": "Gumba23", "products": 445, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "it incredibal ofr it price and it very close to brother hood", "hours": 23.0, "user_id": "76561198107208184", "username": "alreadytagged", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 470, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "I bought this game and i think \"yeah Assassins creed for 4,99 \u20ac \" but after i installed this game i need to install Uplay (Steam from ubisoft) Ok, i started  this game and then i create a Uplay account. After the login usually i got logged in BUT here not (-.-) I tried to log me i but after 5 min i closed the game.\nMy Conclusion is : Don't buy this Game cuz it doesn't work for this time -.-", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Schaltgetriebeauto", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
