{"product_id": "33230", "page": 473, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-13", "text": "Well, uPlay managed to be marginally less obnoxious than whatever broken DRM they had in AC1, so I actually got to play this one. Decent enough, but way too long even doing only partial collection stuff. The game was certainly ambitous but it also seemed pretty stale/uninspired in some areas, especially combat and the rather uninteresting use/non-use of stealth. I'll be curious to see where the series goes though.", "hours": 37.3, "user_id": "76561197970549991", "username": "RedFox", "products": 461, "early_access": false}
