{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "Great game, graphics and all. Exactly what you would want out of Assasin's creed. Hands down one of the best in the series. If you are having trouble with moving in the first scene on a mac try reinstalling it. It will fix it!", "hours": 5.3, "username": "Wanda", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "An amazing improvement over the original, AC2 brings better gameplay, interesting characters and locations, all with neat info on their real world history making it a much better game than the original and a lesson on how sequels should be.", "hours": 44.0, "username": "Samuringa", "products": 578, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "In my opinion this is the best Assassin's Creed game out of the franchise, i recommend this to people who want to drop themselves into the Assassin's Creed universe!\nPros:\n+A lot deeper character design\n+A lengthy game with plenty of collectibles and side activities\n+Immersive world and story\n+New economics system\n+One of the best soundtracks ever\n+Less repetitive\n+Ezio has more personality than Altair\n+Customization\n+Memorable moments\n+Ezio can swim!\nCons:\n-The economics system will make you rich too fast\n-You can't replay missions\nScore:\n10/10", "hours": 6.9, "username": "Scyrenus", "products": 1934, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "The second game in the series (previous game: Assassin's Creed, next game: Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood), this has several graphical and control style updates over the previous game.  In addition, currency and purchases for upgrades are added, and you have a villa to renovate as well.  All in all a solid game in a solid series.  Strongly recommended to play with a controller but easily playable with keyboard and mouse as well.", "hours": 81.5, "username": "Thortok2000", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "If you're looking into getting into the series and for whatever reason refuse to play the first game, this is your only chance. One of the main characters was different in the first game so you won't lose a mountain of back story but you might feel a little confused sometimes when past events are mentioned.\nAny games released after this (Brotherhood & Revelations), before Assassin's Creed III are essentially pure story. The gameplay and setting are very similar but story keeps on going. This series is a like a book in game form. ACIII has different main characters than the games before it and the setting was changed as well.\n----[Rating weighted based on the genre]----\nStory: 5/5\nGameplay: 4/5\nChallenge: 2.5/5\nDiscovery: 3/5\nReplayability: 3/5\nAesthetics: 3.5/5\nVisuals: 5/5\nAtmosphere: 2.5/5\nMusic: 4/5", "hours": 42.1, "username": "Demian", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "This is one of the best AC series ever, it's worth it to buy this game, and follow up the other series of this game!\nI haven't played this much on PC, but I finished the game on my Xbox 360", "hours": 1.9, "username": "ohmahgawd.", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "1 was great 2 was better 3 meh 4 awesome for story.  Watch Canadian TV back story show. Just don't care what happens to desmond.", "hours": 75.9, "user_id": "76561197972795151", "username": "\u2660RP\u2660 Rage Quit", "products": 757, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Really hard to play this game blindfolded.", "hours": 14.3, "username": "matt", "products": 745, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "After playing the masterpiece that was the first game I never imagined how could a game improve so much in the sequel. I was wrong, and this is the game that AC wanted to be. Taking the main story to the Renascence introduced Ezio, who might be less interesting as a character, but the future story arc more than makes up for it, not to mention the improved gameplay that resolved most of old issues. Dropping the DX10 engine can't really hurt the brilliance of this game.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "somini", "products": 469, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 480, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "this game is SOOOOOOOOOOO fun! i definately recommend you play it :3", "hours": 63.4, "user_id": "76561198062227373", "username": "Hubblydot", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Still the best in the series for me. The setting is perfect, you truly feel like walking the streets of Florence, it all feels alive. Don't skip this one!", "hours": 42.3, "username": "mrbay", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 was the evolution of a great game that could have been incredible, but was held back by broken mechanics, cardboard characters and clunky controls. Assassin's Creed was great, and Ubisoft immediately learned that to improve the series, they'd need to sideline Altair, the protagonist. They demonstrated a drastic shift in setting and tone, and with that showed the series' flexibility, as they moved the entire series in a new direction- The setting changed from the Holy Land to Italy, and with that we were introduced to a new legend of gaming- Ezio Auditore. Charasmatic, funny and lethal, Ezio is regarded as one of the best developed characters in gaming, and this is partly due to the fantastic writing and story of the game- Bringing in historical elements and characters such as Leonardo DaVinci and the Borgias, aswell as exciting, epic moments chasing through the rooftops of Florence and the canals of Venice. Ezio's story of revenge brings him through the lands of Italy, and the game shines greatly in its setting and story. Thankfully, the Desmond backstory was not hugely developed yet, and most of the aliens and mumbo jumbo of the later games were spared, the game's main focus is Ezio, and Desmond really does fit in where he should, he's not shoved down your throat with all his conspiracy theories, *cough Assassin's Creed 3 cough*\nGraphically, the game was good, but not inredible. Faces were realistic but at the same time off somehow, hair looked like an error all the time, and in typical AC fashion, ragdolls and derpy physics were plentiful, but yet somehow, the beauty of the cities and the landscapes made the game look and feel incredible.\nThe gameplay evolved upon the epic foundation left by the first game, making combat and freerunning seem accessible for everyone. New elements such as rowing a boat on the canals and hidden pistols, made by DaVinci himself, add alot to the gameplay, and the combat was made incredible. The inclusion of dual hidden blades, more weapons, easier controls and the multitude of guards made each city a playground- As sadistic as it is, I found myself in glee at diving off a rooftop to dual assassinate afew guards, and then take on another half a dozen before getting overwhelmed- The difficulty was perfect, and the combat provided a challenge, which is something the later games failed to provide. Missions and assassinations themselves were given a facelift too, with added mechanics, which gave a nice balance between handholding and freedom.\nI loved the mission structure of the original Assassin's Creed, and sadly this was not included, rather than given a target and a sandbox to kill him in, you are given routes and ways to kill him, which does allow for epic moments attacking targets on castles and towers, but lacks the satisfaction of figuring out the perfect route to go.\nOverall, AC2 remains probably the best in the series, and the most original game of its type in its time. It was revolutionary, innovative and inventive. Plus, who can beat punching the pope in the face? If I had to rate it, I'd give it a 9.5/10. Buy this game, it's cheap and there's no excuse. I got it for \u20ac10 or something, trust me, it's worth it. Even if you haven't played the original, this is worth a shot. If you like it, try the first, if not, you're probably a nazi.", "hours": 62.0, "username": "elmodonnell", "products": 387, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "In my honest opinion, start with this game of the series, because they made huge improvements from the 1st game that really make it a much richer and more fun experience.\nThe story is alright, but the gameplay is amazing, and I can't wait to experience the rest of the series.", "hours": 26.9, "username": "Matzimazing", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "This is a pretty fun game.  It is fun to leap around buildings and fight off groups of soldiers with a little button mashing.  At the same time, it does start to get a little repetitive.  Still, it is an improvement over the first game.", "hours": 145.1, "username": "NerdCoreRocks", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-22", "text": "The basic idea behind the game is awesome, it looks ok still even by todays standards (2013) but it has the crapest keyboard controls known to man, you must over come this to play what is truley a masterpeice.\ndont stop at 2 just keep going cos it just keeps getting better and better trust me this is one of the all time greats and is upthere with others such as Mass Effect / Deus X / Dead Space", "hours": 105.6, "username": "DonkyBoY", "products": 338, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-19", "text": "The final boss is a boxing match with the pope and that's just the raddest thing.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "Spenny", "products": 368, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "For me the Ezio's story still the best. I love Ezio, so don't talk to me about Connor, because I really dont care.\n\u2606Assassin's Creed II is much more complete, the story is better, the characters are more charismatic.\n\u2606 The scenario of Florence is beautiful, I love Italy.\n\u2606 The graphics and gameplay are good, but if you've never played AC before, you can take time to adapt. However, I think the fighting and missions are easy.\n\u2606 In the moment when I started to play I lose the time in my mind, but it's tiring to collect all objects..\nI only give advice to you, GAME, just GAME IT.\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u26055/5", "hours": 120.6, "username": "\u019dayuki \u52c7\u6c17", "products": 283, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "It's really good! Spend at least 20 hours on it to really appreciate what the game offers.\n9/10", "hours": 20.5, "username": "Ashes.", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 481, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "Truly the best Assassin's Creed experience. This game was a mindshock for me back when it came out, and no other AC can even compare to it. The story, the characters, the feeling of living and breathing in Florence and Venice is just...unique. I recommend you all to put 20 hours of your life into this unforgettable experience which will surely stick with me for decades.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "BNS Marko", "products": 400, "early_access": false}
