{"product_id": "33230", "page": 484, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-25", "text": "My favorite Assassin's Creed involving Ezio. Beautiful, touching, magical. Great soundtrack, great everything. This game is a quantum leap from its predecessor. A must play.", "username": "Chris", "products": 1233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 484, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-25", "text": "I ended up unloading a lot of time into this game. The world is big and plenty of things to do. In 2013 the graphics and the world are dated but still holds a fine beauty and thrill. The game play is solid for the most part. There were many frustrations at times with the controls on a KB/M (a game pad would probably be a wise decision for this game) that drove me up the wall at times but about 80-90% of the time playing it worked alright. It works perfectly fine with a KB/M but a game pad would be recommended if you have one. Story wise this is an absolute treasure to have been told. If you have a few bucks to spare I'd say it's a fine investment of a game that took me 19 or so hours to beat without doing many of the secondary objectives. I focused primarily on the story and it's a large one that will be fun to experience.", "hours": 18.2, "user_id": "76561197962089604", "username": "Nickmadkiller", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 485, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-23", "text": "Good gameplay, catchy story, noted improvements from the first one. the change from medieval theme to renassaince wasnt much of a joy to me, but still, a very very enjoyable game.", "hours": 21.4, "username": "Mclaird", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 485, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is so different from AC that you could easily say that the current franchise began with this second game. Ezio is your typical charismatic bad-boy, and playing as him throughout his great character arc is very satisfying. The combat, while not as ridiculously easy as it is in later titles, is very different than it was in AC, and the varying styles of the missions keep the game interesting for more casual players. The story is interesting, but much less profound and contemplative than AC's, but the game's many other qualities (especially the visuals) more than make up for it.", "hours": 91.8, "user_id": "76561197977766807", "username": "Julian", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 485, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-16", "text": "Renaissance Italy, Best Period For Secrets And Mysteries.", "hours": 83.6, "username": "UN1V3RZUM", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 485, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-15", "text": "It's my favourite Assassin's Creed  game to date. It has wonderful Italian setting, interesting characters and exciting story full of adventures, drama, mysteries, and unexpected twists.", "hours": 20.8, "username": "MCofDiablo", "products": 712, "early_access": false}
