{"product_id": "33230", "page": 486, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-05", "text": "Assassin\u2019s Creed 2 is one of the best games I\u2019ve ever played and definitely the best part of the series. It\u2019s more varied than the first part and the characters are simply awesome. The game has brought a lot of innovations into the series, such as a new main character, a lot of novel weapons and armors and the ability to swim. There is a giant new world to explore and the story is thrilling till the end. Finally, I can\u2019t tell you anything bad about the game, I mean even the soundtrack is great. So if you like Action-Adventures like this, buy the game, it\u2019s still worth the money.", "hours": 54.7, "username": "Rhox", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 486, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-03", "text": "Davon die ganze Kollektion.", "hours": 36.2, "user_id": "76561198016591900", "username": "Butta", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 486, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-31", "text": "Well,I needed toilet paper anyway.", "hours": 1.5, "user_id": "76561197972729524", "username": "Perus_TC", "products": 433, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 486, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-26", "text": "A huge step-up from the first game and actually making the present day characters interesting was a bonus. Ezio Auditore has become one of the greatest protagonists in video games for his charm, wit and brute force. The masterful writing in this sequel solidified the AC series as a successful franchise that Ubisoft has clearly played with.\nThe graphics? Stunning, even years later. The gameplay? Perfected swordfighting. Some might disagree, but it was so fluid and seemless in a number of the fights. The story? Remarkable. The writers have done their research and not only created characters, but also used historical characters in the correct context. This game is just fantastic.\n9.7/10", "hours": 59.3, "user_id": "76561198009430218", "username": "JacoRay", "products": 774, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 486, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-23", "text": "Do you constantly brood over your unfulfiled fantasy of becoming Da Vinci's greasy jabroni roomate who is also an exceptional pro-kebaber?\nIf yes, I got some good news for you.\nTake control of Ezio \"The Situation\" Auditore da Quatrto Stagioni as you carve your way into Jersey Shore's underbelly, dispatching legions of tanned italian mobsters as you reach the game's highly climactic finale wherein you punch a chubby old guy.\n(5 euphoric fedoras out of 5 for being able to fight the Pope!!)", "hours": 42.0, "username": "Hallovin", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
