{"product_id": "33230", "page": 494, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-14", "text": "Ubi finally nailed AC with this entry. An interesting character with an interesting story in an interesting time. The game doesn't take itself too seriously \"It's a me, mario!\" anyone? It's still not perfect but damn if this game isn't something special.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561197970329460", "username": "Aeneas2020", "products": 542, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 494, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-08", "text": "Finally finished this game on PC. It is a dramatic improvement upon teh first AC. There are many more missions to do, the story is easier to follow, and the gameplay mechanics are much smoother overall. There are many more tricks Ezio can perform that you wished Altiar was able to do in the first AC. Highly recommend you picking this one up and playing if you are an AC fan!", "hours": 40.0, "username": "defiance5050", "products": 607, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 494, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-07", "text": "These games are all the same, so my recommendations will all be the same.\nThe world we get to assassin in are quite nice and great at representing these ancient cityscapes. That said, the storyline is bad in every game, and the games try their best to make them as historically inacurate as possible. PC port is terrible - fair at best. Just don't buy them.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Graeme", "products": 1044, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 494, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-07", "text": "Far better than Assasins's Creed 1. Most of people say its best of the series. I really enjoyed with this game. Its long game i finnish it after 27 hours.", "hours": 27.7, "username": "Elrond9", "products": 1167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 494, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-05-03", "text": "Undeniably a great game and an excellent sequel, bringing much needed spice to the monotony of the first title. That being said however, I still much prefer the look, feel, and protagonist of the first.", "hours": 33.8, "username": "Geo", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
