{"product_id": "33230", "page": 496, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-05", "text": "It's as rich, interesting, and cool as AC1 and includes one of Jesper Kyd's best soundtracks to date. My only real gripe with the AC series would be the occasional quirky movement controls which can either make or break a mission sometimes. Also, it helps to play the previous game in the series to get the full story.", "hours": 55.1, "username": "Wraz", "products": 715, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 496, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-04", "text": "The second installment of the most awesome franchise ever.The new ancestor of Desmond Miles is Ezio Auditore,which would easily be my favourite Assassin <3\nThis game is definitely recommended,it has stronger emphasis on open-world exploration and interaction, non-linear gameplay and greater mission variety compared to the first Assassin's Creed. The game was also credited with improved non-player character AI and combat mechanics, and its new economic system allowing players to purchase accessories, armor, and improved weapons through the course of the game.", "hours": 19.7, "username": "Nour - \u5149", "products": 273, "early_access": false}
