{"product_id": "33230", "page": 498, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-15", "text": "Ezio is one of the best written characters in gaming. I love every god damn moment with that  charismatic son of a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. The entire game is worth going through to see his story unfold, and his character grow. It's a damn shame nothing happened with him in Brotherhood, and we saw the end of his story in Relevations. I'll take this dapper Italian over some halfbreed native american any day.", "hours": 51.8, "username": "Manooz", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 498, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-14", "text": "So much better than the first AC in just about everything.... it's a must play, maybe the best so far, the gameplay is still pretty easy and the upgrades system unbalanced, but Ezio is a great character and the plot and the places are awesome with amazing environment.", "hours": 68.7, "username": "njb", "products": 778, "early_access": false}
