{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-04", "text": "THIS GAME IS JUST BEAUTIFUL. NO WORDS TO DESCRIBE IT, NEED I EXPLAIN? YOU PLAY AS A SEXY\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ITALIAN MOFO WITH MORE CHARM THAN A CEREAL BRAND THAT PERPETUATES IRISH STEREOTYPES. AND YOU GO AROUND, MAKING THE WORLD A BETTER PLACE BY DOING AWAY WITH BAD PEOPLE. NOT ONLY THAT BUT LEONARDO DAVINCI  IS YOUR BRO. AND MAN, I'D BE DAMNED IF HE'S NOT THE BEST BRO EVER. BEAUTIFUL SOUNDTRACK TOO, ENGAGING STORYLINE, JUST PLAY IT FOR CHRIST'S SAKE.", "hours": 49.0, "username": "Tyrannosaurus Lex", "products": 618, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-03-03", "text": "Im always years late to the party on AAA titles. But thats cause I pay $5 instead of $50.....anywhos.  WOW.  What a stellar \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 game.  Great graphics, awesome story and super fluid gameplay and battle mechanics.  Everyone tells me Brotherhood is the best.  If so, its gotta be one of the best games ever made cause this thing was a masterpiece.  9/10 all day long.", "hours": 44.0, "user_id": "76561197978259323", "username": "ulasamosa", "products": 457, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-27", "text": "I thought it'd be more or less the first one. It's not. Story, my main complaint from the first one, is actually better here, played by voice actors who actually feel like they care about this game. The fighting system has improved slightly, though it's more or less still the same. Lot's of buildings to climb, plenty of action going on, tombs to raid. It's just overall a great game. Thought it was weird that they implimented side-quests at first, but it works to it's advantage here. Can't imagine a better way to play it.\nIf you liked the first one, you are going to love this one. If you hated the first one, you may think this is a step in a better direction.", "hours": 25.8, "username": "RexOrchid", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-24", "text": "Huge improvment over the first game, and the main protaganist isnt a complete \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.", "hours": 63.4, "username": "CrispyNoodle", "products": 450, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-23", "text": "Definitely a stepup from the previous game. Not a whole lot of repetitiveness this time around, especially because of the new character and new age.\nIf you're playing backwards (III -> Revelations -> Brotherhood) you'll probably feel gameplay gets progressively harder especially in the movement and fighting factors.  The introduction of chain killing in Brotherhood as well as the kick skill made that game fairly easy to complete.  Without it, AC2 can prove to be a challenge in its own right.", "hours": 21.4, "username": "Advarcher", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-21", "text": "Better than the first Assassin's Creed, in both plot and variety (though I honestly kind of prefer the Crusade theme over the Italian Renassiance...), AC2 is a pretty fun game, with some fantastic graphics and gameplay.\nHowever it does start to outstay its welcome about a dozen hours in or so, especially when you realize the game has a ways to go in its convoluted story, and isn't going to introduce much new, other than the occasional \"use once, and forever ignore\" gadget.  And honsetly, the game should be called \"Dueler's Creed\", because you do a lot more of that than assassinating...\nRecommended for those who are either hardcore completionists or gamers with patience.", "hours": 33.0, "user_id": "76561197962135950", "username": "Little Wastrel", "products": 291, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed can be vaguely compared to the concept of 'The Matrix' in which you play a protagonist in the 'real world' who becomes someone else inside a 'virtual world'. It tells a fictional story of a war between Assassins and Templars - and spans across several real life historic periods. The franchise is one of few - which tells a massive story back-to-back instead of switching main characters half way through or making massive time jumps. Awesome franchise!", "hours": 45.1, "username": "Vendrium", "products": 819, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-19", "text": "A lot better than the first Assassin's Creed by far... I'm not sure how they did it but the makers managed to wrap religion, science, past, present, and future plus a whole lot more into the storyline of this game. Combat is great and there is a fair amount of upgrades and other items to purchase. The only downside is all of the running around gets to be annoying.", "hours": 40.3, "user_id": "76561198058226508", "username": "smokefroge", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-18", "text": "I was skeptical at first but this game is honestly amazing. The platforming and assassinations are so satisfying.  The story is great, Ezio is a awesome protagonist. Leonardo is awesome too! I recommend this if you like open world, action, or a game that has a ton of stuff to do!", "hours": 49.1, "username": "Xan", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 499, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-16", "text": "You can`t play the game when steam is on off line mode!!", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198081721695", "username": "CHMM", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 500, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-02-12", "text": "I like to imagine I'm murdering the distant Italian ancestors of the Jersey Shore cast. It removes all moral ambiguity from my actions", "hours": 28.7, "username": "GuruDingo", "products": 250, "early_access": false}
