{"product_id": "33230", "page": 502, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-12", "text": "If you thought the first Assassin's Creed was good, this is even better. A great work from the developers; you will be able to find 4 huge cities to explore, while you see Ezio's grow from a common citizen to a an \"armed to the teeth\" assassin.\nThere are lots and lots of stuff to do in this game, the story is quite enjoyable and is fun to get out of Abstergo using Desmond. Graphics are really good and pretty detailed too; oh! well, you should be able to tell by now that I enjoyed the game a lot!... believe me I did, very much... and if you enjoyed the first, most likely you will enjoy this one even more...", "hours": 37.2, "username": ".: D :.", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 502, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-11", "text": "It's been a long time since I've played Assassins Creed 1 on Xbox, so I'm trying to catch up on the series. Haven't played the 3 newer ones yet but I really enjoyed this one and feel like it may be the most developed and interesting of all of them. Plot twist at the end was NUTS and had me hooked on playing the next enstallments.", "hours": 36.2, "username": "The Lone Wanderer", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
