{"product_id": "33230", "page": 503, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-04", "text": "Really good game. Really addictive. It is literally breathtaking to stand on the top of a tall building of Renaissance Italy. I've played twice because it's so good.\nBut the keyboard controls are not good enough and some parts of the game are overly irritating because of that.", "hours": 89.2, "user_id": "76561198001584035", "username": "BobMammoth", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 503, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-03", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 has brought me nothing but thrills. The combat is exciting, the graphics are solid, and the story is so good. Even though the newer AC games have more features, I still see my self coming back to this one. If you played the first one and liked it, I don't know why you wouldn't have this one. If you played the first one and liked the gameplay but wasn't fond of the story, don't worry it gets so much better in this one. Buy it.", "hours": 144.0, "username": "Rube", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 503, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-03", "text": "TThe best open world action game I've ever played. Immensely satisfying experience all-around, with a tremendous variety in gameplay. Plus it starts the arc of one of the best protagonists in recent gaming memory: Ezio Auditore. Do yourself a favor and buy it.", "hours": 29.1, "username": "JustJim89", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
