{"product_id": "33230", "page": 504, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-26", "text": "The game is good but ... With the amount of bugs, I do not know if it's a bug in the game or a game in the bug :S for fun, I approve (y)", "hours": 67.9, "username": "Sniper Stalker", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-26", "text": "An all-around \"good fun\" game, plenty of side-missions to keep you occupied for hours, an expansive story across 15th century Italy, and characters that you can get involved with emotionally.\nDefinitely a game i would recommend to those who enjoyed playing Prototype, it's a massive open-world game with fun parkour/free-roaming and an arsenal of stealthy weapons to keep you happy.\nThere are some minor annoyances, so i'm going to give it an overall 8/10.", "hours": 35.8, "username": "Reack", "products": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-26", "text": "9/10", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561197987836161", "username": "PatientLandBeaver", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-24", "text": "New face, New character, New skills, New Assassin.\nMeet the newest character to the Assassin's Creed Franchise\nEzio Auditore da Firenze, italian born, living in the Renaissance age. Young and _______________ Woops I almost mentioned \"Assassin.\" Well just for kicks, you're gonna be blown away by the new contrnt this game brings than that of Assassin's Creed, The same assassination keep going but lets just say they're more \"Diverse.\"\nThe new content brings a revolutionary new weapons at you're disposal of course. in this age, we'll be seeing new, and using new arsenal at you're expense.\nForget the old missions you were drudging upon when you were Altair, your facing a new enemy, new Bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Main character.\nAssassin's Creed II comes with another new addition, puzzles.\nSolving them will be a tedious task, racking your brain not like how Portal did, but with a new method, called \"history alteration.\" A sad code-name I named, I know, nevertheless I think it fit's quite well, to Ezio, help the poor man along with these puzzles, and you'll receive something worthwhile.\nMissing Altair? Don't worry, by the time you're into ACII you'll realize you love him more than Altiar. Maybe.\nAlthough, I wouldn't be so quick to judge on this one, I encourage the still faithful fans and fellow assassin's to try this new addition to the AC world.  And for newcomers, prepare to be blown away by the sheer depth of an original classic filled with action and addiction like never before.\nAnimus 2.0 Re-initialized. Just for You Desmond.\n9.4/10", "username": "DetectiveFail", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-20", "text": "Assassin\u2019s Creed II is one of the great games of our time.  The developers have created a flawless blend of adventure, combat and fantasy.  The game entangles the player with a brilliantly developed and enticing story.  The mystery and allure of the characters and the plot create a game experience like none other.  Astonishing action sequences engage all your senses for a mind blowing experience.  Assassin\u2019s Creed II is more than a masterpiece, it is the perfect game.", "hours": 74.1, "user_id": "76561197964026918", "username": "Roman Bylar", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-18", "text": "Un Assasseno Molto Silencioso", "hours": 102.5, "username": "Th3HavocK", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-18", "text": "Just like the first game, A Le Parkour enthusiast larks about on impressive historical architecture. Fans of the first game will find a familiar gameplay but with some additions. While there are many improvements at the core, other elements are annoying. While death side soliloquies are mostly gone, you will find that the game can\u2019t make up its mind if it wants you to stab people or be an RPG where you race people and complete silly side quests. While the Voice actors chew the scenery with gratuitous Italian accents, AC2 still has decent character development and depth. Complaints aside, it is a good addition to the franchise.", "hours": 140.3, "user_id": "76561198052778925", "username": "Eohseax", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-17", "text": "This game is MUCH better than AC1. In fact I would skip it completely and just play this game. I'd give it 8/10", "hours": 158.6, "username": "sonderkraftfahrzeug", "products": 538, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 505, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-17", "text": "This sequel takes the same style of play from the first game and builds upon it, adding new abilities and slightly better controls. An awesome game.\n9/10 - Pure fun.", "hours": 55.2, "username": "\u26a1", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
