{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-22", "text": "Intially I was turned off at the beginning due to the differences from the first, which I finished a few months before (namely having to buy health and having to shop), but after going back to it I was able to get into it within an hour or two and really ended up enjoying it.  It ended up being a lot more fun then the first, although I would have liked a more compelling story.", "hours": 86.7, "username": "ComputerAbuser", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-20", "text": "Probably the best Assassin's Creed game to date. It made huge leaps from its predecessor, in every area. The graphics are still very good, even though this game came out a few years ago; and as usual, music and voice acting is superb. The story is probably the best of all the other games in the franchise, simply because Ezio actually has friends and family around (other games depict him as more solemn person who works alone). It's very immersive, the crouds felt very real and the enviroments were lifelike. As always, combat is very fun (again, it probably beats the other games; the first was very hard while the rest are very easy).\nBuy this game now! It's very cheap on sale, and gives well over 20 hours of gameplay.", "hours": 35.5, "username": "MacroPower", "products": 1351, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-17", "text": "The strongest of the AC series (so far).", "hours": 69.8, "username": "Darkstar", "products": 3280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-13", "text": "\u0418\u0434\u0435\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0438\u043c\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0442\u043e\u0440 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0430/\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0441\u0430. \u0421\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u0440\u0443\u0442\u043e\u0439 (\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u0432\u044b\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0430 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b) \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0438, \u0443\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0438 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0433\u0435\u0439\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0435\u044f, \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u044f\u0441\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0439, \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435\u0439 \u0434\u043e \u0433\u043b\u0443\u0431\u0438\u043d\u044b \u0434\u0443\u0448\u0438 \u043c\u0443\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u044f\u0441\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0438\u0445 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438, \u0442\u0430\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0424\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0435\u043d\u0446\u0438\u044f, \u0424\u043e\u0440\u043b\u0438, \u0422\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430, \u041c\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0434\u0436\u043e\u043d\u0438, \u0412\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0438 \u0420\u0438\u043c - \u0432\u0441\u0451 \u044d\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0440\u044f\u0441\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0435. \u041e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0438\u0433\u0440 \u0436\u0430\u043d\u0440\u0430 GTA \u0438 \u0432\u043e\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435 \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0438\u0433\u0440 \u0434\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u044f. 9,5/10.", "hours": 50.3, "username": "Soapy", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-12", "text": "People familiar with the first game will enjoy this game from the beginning. The visual quality and details are outstanding and the storyline much more deeper this time.  Still you need about 45-50 hrs to finish the game. Enjoy !", "hours": 44.8, "username": "AleksR", "products": 658, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-07", "text": "awesome game, great story!  It's a must play!", "hours": 73.6, "username": "LcG.Nerpol", "products": 265, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-27", "text": "\u041d\u0430\u0433\u043b\u044f\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043c\u0435\u0440, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b - \u044d\u0442\u043e \u0434\u0435\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e \u0438\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0441\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e. \u0422\u0430\u043a\u0436\u0435, \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u0441\u0430\u043c\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0443\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0445 \u043f\u0435\u0441\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0446.", "hours": 50.2, "username": "Deus348", "products": 409, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 510, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-26", "text": "yea breh breh this one much better than the first you play as dat \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 ezio and you be \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665in \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665es cause he a true playa pimp you be pick pocketin \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s and take they guap and if they wanna start some\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665after take they guap beat they\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and let \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s know you don't play play breh", "hours": 35.8, "username": "stackaye", "products": 1049, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-24", "text": "Okay... this one is a bit of a mixed bag, and since I haven't played them I wont compare it to its sequels.\nRuns fine on 3.2ghz*6, HD6850, 8gb RAM machine, no performance hiccups, nor did the uplay launcher cause issue.  Graphics wise I have no complaint.  Locales are detailed sufficiently to put you the setting, a few building interiors are nice but nothing  wowing.  Game plays 90% fine on a keyboard.\nGameplay wise, it improves a bit over its original in options and combat, as well as platforming, but the fastwalk dual-mapped to pickpocket, grab / release on hand, and jump / sprint being overzealously applied is quite frustrating at times.  Some enemies are immune to smoke bombs, being shot, backstabs, etc for no real reason other than plot armor, which feels stupid.  The inclusion of the Hidden Gun feels like a nod to the frustration of catching running enemies, but bugs the camera.  Enemy soldiers still pose 0 threat.\nStory and characters are much better, even if slow to start.", "hours": 29.5, "username": "I'm Not Sue", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-20", "text": "\"Recommend\" is an awfully strong word. I like this; it's a strong game and a clear improvement over the first game. It's beautiful. The story is well told, but its Italian revenge story doesn't always mesh well with the pseudo-sci-fi trappings. The polish and detail is incredible, but the pacing is way off. You have all your abilities perhaps a third of the way through the game. This results in a lot of repetition as the game wears on. Side quests that don't have any real weight to their completion and a host of coincidences and false endings that undermine the far tighter first half of the narrative just add to the sense of \"My God, when will this game be over?\" This game does what it does incredibly well...ad nauseum. !!!!!A note on UPlay: turn off the online synch when playing. It has a habit of loading cloud saves that are days old and overwrite your hard drive saves. Turning off the online synch solves this!!!!!", "hours": 49.8, "user_id": "76561197982626784", "username": "Basilicus", "products": 657, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-10", "text": "Excelente juego", "hours": 109.9, "user_id": "76561198019953437", "username": "WhiteVolpe", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-04", "text": "A new Assassin, a new period. The same war. I fully recommend it", "hours": 80.8, "username": "Sovereign [CHL]", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-04", "text": "This game is so good! It has a good story (plus side quests), great gameplay, great soundtrack and great graphics. It has beautiful places of Italy like the Tuscany region (Florence, Monteriggioni and San Gimignano), the Apennine Mountains, the Romagna region (Forl\u00ec, Venice and Rome. Specific landmarks include St Mark's Basilica, the Grand Canal, the Little Canal, the Rialto Bridge,Santa Maria del Fiore, the Sistine Chapel, Santa Croce, Palazzo Vecchio, Ponte Vecchio, and Santa Maria Novella.\n9/10", "hours": 58.9, "username": "[MGSFC] R1SK", "products": 933, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-03", "text": "Great fun. The combat mechanics aren't the best, but the rooftop jumping in old Italian cities is wonderful and the assassination missions are a mix of quick reflexes and stealth. A definite buy.", "hours": 27.4, "username": "Supercoil64", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-02", "text": "Awesome game, such a massive difference from AC1 but IMO this is much better for it. The sheer amount of content and attention to detail in this open-world game is astonishing. And no repetitive \"help-save-the-damsel/commoner-in-distress\" side quests from AC1!\nHighly recommended overall", "hours": 61.4, "username": "\uff24\uff21\uff39\uff2b\uff33", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-31", "text": "Wow!! Incredible game!!", "hours": 421.8, "user_id": "76561198045571261", "username": "Digital Femdroid", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-28", "text": "I loved the first assassins creed and I also love assissins creed revalations (Both played on PS3). But I did not like this. But I don't believe its the actual game that is the issue. I believe that it is the fact that it is a terrible console port. Games made for console should stay on console, the transistion never works out well. My recommendation dont buy this on PC. Get it on PS3 or XBOX.\nSee also:\nThe other Assassin's Creed games\nAny other shameless console port", "hours": 35.6, "username": "[RIP] El_Droidio", "products": 1162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 511, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-22", "text": "A violent, fun, and epic adventure through reniassance Italy\nEpic tale of revenge\nGreat combat\nAwsome Freeruning\nA lot to do after you finish the main quest\nOverall, a great game that everyone should play\n9.5/10", "hours": 41.0, "username": "VEGETAL", "products": 431, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-21", "text": "Bellissimo gioco, migliore del primo. E' meno ripetitivo, c'\u00e8 una pi\u00f9 vasta gamma di quest e cose da fare, pi\u00f9 armi (forse troppe, ne avr\u00f2 usato una met\u00e0). Purtroppo Desmond \u00e8 meno presente del primo, compare solo in 3 occasioni (all'inizio, a met\u00e0 e alla fine), ma almeno si scoprono molte cose riguardo alla situazione attuale. La giocabilit\u00e0 \u00e8 decisamente migliore del primo. Altair tuttavia mi \u00e8 piaciuto di pi\u00f9 come personaggio. Mentre in lui si vede molto il conflitto interiore, Ezio mostra solo il desiderio di vendicare la sua famiglia, come un automa, poco pi\u00f9.\nLa grafica \u00e8 spettacolare, le espressioni facciali sono venute veramente bene. Musiche un po' ripetitive ma gradevoli. Molto bella quella dei titoli di coda. Sia la trama di Ezio che quella di Desmond vengono sviluppate bene e in giusta misura. L'ambientazione si sta delineando sempre di pi\u00f9, si va approfondando nel fantascientifico, ed \u00e8 sempre pi\u00f9 interessante.\n10/10", "hours": 42.0, "username": "Aniu Proserpina", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-20", "text": "Okay, so this game takes things to a new level. It isn't as repetitive as the first, and still has a great follow-up story that surprises you since it's a sequel. The soundtrack is absolutely amazing, and the entire feel of the game is like a really awesome movie. New features in this one: Swimming, using a canoe in the style of the era in Italy, guns are now involved, you can use more items which are all found in your inventory, health potions, poison coating for your wrist blade(s), upgrade your weapons and armor. If you thought the first game was too repetitive, try this one, because it's not. A word of warning, however: This game's controls don't always seem to REACT as they should.", "hours": 43.7, "username": "TheKittyPeach", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-20", "text": "Stabby fun and a huge improvement over the original. Ubisoft's deplorable DRM aside, there is plenty of fun to be had with AC2. The world feels full of life (and death) and Ezio is a far more likeable character than Altair ever was.", "hours": 41.1, "username": "Antipunk", "products": 1290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "A big change from its predecessor for the better. The story feels deeper and the game is much less repetitive. Gotta play it!", "hours": 35.9, "username": "BLATSPLAT", "products": 917, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-17", "text": "We work in the dark, to serve the light. We are Assassins.", "hours": 16.3, "username": "Jackass", "products": 1054, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-17", "text": "Good game if you like climbing in windows :P", "hours": 36.3, "username": "Stroke41", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-15", "text": "On top of the gorgeous visuals and beautifully orchestrated score, Assassin's Creed II boasts plenty of refinements and additions that not only make it the best in the series thus far, but one of the best games in recent memory.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "Asai Nero Tran", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-13", "text": "Really great and stylish open-world action game.\nHad I known it was such an awesome game, I would have played it years ago.", "hours": 65.3, "username": "Fart of Presto", "products": 4802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-11", "text": "Way better than Assassin's Creed, the missions are more interesting, different and complex. There is more humor and Ezio has more character than Alta\u00efr. Playing this on PC was challenging at first because the button signs are head, armed hand, hand, legs etc. instead of numbers or other things. Tip: get a PC controller, makes all the running WAY easier :)", "hours": 38.8, "username": "salriella", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 512, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-10", "text": "So much better than the first! When I first started this one I was disappointed that it wasn't as dark as the first and seemed light-hearted and goofy. Then I realized that that was the point, and the end was plenty dark and spectacular. Gameplay still is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed in terms of controls, but it's something you get used to and can cope with. It doesn't subtract from the game too much. The music is really good and immersive. The voice acting is sooo much better than the first. All around, this is a great game. And everyone says the series gets better and better so I bet Brotherhood is going to be amazing! 9/10", "hours": 19.3, "username": "-=TheDoctor=-", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-11", "text": "Way better than Assassin's Creed, the missions are more interesting, different and complex. There is more humor and Ezio has more character than Alta\u00efr. Playing this on PC was challenging at first because the button signs are head, armed hand, hand, legs etc. instead of numbers or other things. Tip: get a PC controller, makes all the running WAY easier :)", "hours": 38.8, "username": "salriella", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-10", "text": "So much better than the first! When I first started this one I was disappointed that it wasn't as dark as the first and seemed light-hearted and goofy. Then I realized that that was the point, and the end was plenty dark and spectacular. Gameplay still is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed in terms of controls, but it's something you get used to and can cope with. It doesn't subtract from the game too much. The music is really good and immersive. The voice acting is sooo much better than the first. All around, this is a great game. And everyone says the series gets better and better so I bet Brotherhood is going to be amazing! 9/10", "hours": 19.3, "username": "-=TheDoctor=-", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-09", "text": "its like the fisrst one but u took all the bad and made it not as bad and put in rpg elements so you can make lods of emone but ezio still tries to run up walls and jumps off buildings at bad times", "hours": 44.3, "username": "Zess", "products": 374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-08", "text": "Its fun, and all the stabby-stabby you could ask for. The story even gets pretty interesting, if you can let your brain get past how ridiculous it all is.\nYou should probably play Assassin's Creed 1 first, you should definitely play Brotherhood next, and you should most certainly SKIP the hell over Revelations.\nEven if you find yourself growing invested in the story, seriously jus skip Revelations. Believe me when I say nothing important actually happens in that game.", "hours": 30.4, "username": "Six", "products": 520, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-08", "text": "Compared to first game, better playibility, music and finally a better story awaits you! Unlike the first one, there are quite a few different missions. A journey from a ladies man to legendary assassin. I am sure that Ezio Auditore will entertain you a lot. You know, jumping over rooftops, assassinating \"bad\" people and stuff...", "hours": 26.1, "username": "mupheminsani", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-06", "text": "EPIC", "hours": 86.2, "username": "luenyar", "products": 334, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-06", "text": "Arguably the best game in the series, at least prior to Assassin's Creed III release.\nAlmost every aspect of the first game was improved. Assassin's Creed II starts right where the first one ends, exploding with an astonishing whirlpool of events, only occasionally slowing down to let the player take a deep breath before diving back in. Newly introduced puzzles with hidden secret messages that explain and connect our world's biggest mysteries in a very surprising and clever manner make the story feel dreadfully real and even more fun to explore. And just when it feels the game has already exhaused all of its ways to surprise, it blows the player away with its amazing ending.\nAssassin's Creed II is a large step ahead of the first game. But don't forget this is a second episode in the story of Desmond Miles, and it is highly recommended that you start with the first game where this story begins.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Toff", "products": 3154, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-06", "text": "Playing the Assassin's Creed-series in a totally non-chronological way (AC, AC: Brotherhood and now AC 2), I easily find myself comparing Assassin's Creed 2 to the follow-up, Brotherhood. And yes, in many ways, they are totally identical (graphics, controls and gameplay), but shockingly, I still find AC II to be slightly more fun than Brotherhood. Yes, I loved Rome (I have history with that city) and the whole assassin training deal, but AC II, with it's straight revenge and rebuild story just feels more personal to me. And the fact that you move from Firenze through Monteriggioni (your own hometown) to Forli and Venice (a city I now totally love and a huge reason why I started playing AC 2) gives the game a bit more variety. And with the \"historically accurate\" political intrigue of Reneissance Italy, what's not to love?", "hours": 34.6, "username": "[LUC] Chride", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-04", "text": "Best Assassin's Creed ever.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "Hineni", "products": 306, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 513, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-02", "text": "Its always nice to see an ambitious franchise find its feet. AC2 is a huge leap forward from its predecessor, incorporating more varied combat and mission objectives, larger cities to explore, a more engaging protagonist, and a handful of secondary mechanics that give you more reasons to complete side missions and search for hidden objectives.\nIts not a short ride, either. 100% competion took me about 56 hours, and I imagine a bare bones playthrough would require at least 12. You'd be missing out though, because the charm of this Renaissance romp is in the out of the way details.", "hours": 54.6, "username": "Simian Deity", "products": 449, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-28", "text": "\ub808\uc54c\ucd5c\uace0\uc5d0 \uac8c\uc784\uc774\ub2e4", "hours": 42.1, "user_id": "76561198057569877", "username": "Guilty ON", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-27", "text": "Best whirlwind tour of Italy i've never been on, and at a good price too!\nSeriously though, my favorite AC title so far, before Ubisoft got into the multiplayer aspect and added the mini-micromanage-things-you-couldn't-care-less-about games. Great location variety, memorable characters, and a kick\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665storyline to boot. Buy it!", "hours": 0.0, "username": "Fogmoz", "products": 577, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-26", "text": "Don't judge the series off the first game. They improve the formula in almost every way in this sequel. Quite excellent.", "hours": 80.7, "username": "Laughaholic", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-26", "text": "Third person jumpy stabby climby grabby. Huge leap forward (ahem) from the flawed promise of the first installment. And you can play it entirely in Italian. Eeeeeeezio!", "hours": 11.5, "username": "AOLetsGo", "products": 323, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-23", "text": "I was going to give this game a positive review, but Uplay ruined it for me", "hours": 73.2, "username": "Caaaaww\u2122", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "probably my favorite game in the series, has tons of missions and is a game that will give you plenty to do", "hours": 18.5, "username": "Bowie Sensei", "products": 490, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "If you're a Prince of Persia or just a straight up parkour fan, I highly recommend this game. I would also recommend skipping the first game and going straight to this one and onwards. Assassin's Creed II is the most fluent game I've ever played, with a very rich story that never fails to deliver emotions every time you play it.", "hours": 63.6, "username": "RiddlerFoto", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "You play as oblivious Desmond again but this time he\u2019s playing \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing Cool Ezio Auditore da Firenze as he sorts some\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665out against some templar\u2019s that killed most of his family and with some help from Uncle Mario (Not THE Mario but might as well be).\nYou run around as desmond for a bit but all he can do is jump and run and get the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665taken out of him by the british guy and his lesbian friend. Considered the best in the franchise but it is Ubisoft so don\u2019t get your hopes up.", "hours": 3.9, "username": "Luke Rising", "products": 391, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "Out of the games currently released in the series, this one is by far the best. Storyline, pacing of plot, gameplay -- gorgeous.", "hours": 215.3, "user_id": "76561198034230631", "username": "Anaze", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 514, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "It's my fix of the day if I'm feeling particularly ninja-ish. =D", "hours": 8.8, "username": "digitalchocolate", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "Out of the games currently released in the series, this one is by far the best. Storyline, pacing of plot, gameplay -- gorgeous.", "hours": 215.3, "user_id": "76561198034230631", "username": "Anaze", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "It's my fix of the day if I'm feeling particularly ninja-ish. =D", "hours": 8.8, "username": "digitalchocolate", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Alongside brotherhood, this game is the best in the series. Like Mass Effect 2, taking the greatness of the original game and matching it up with new and great content has proven amazing. The conclusions of each game can be a little wacky but I've never accused the series of being realistic, to say nothing about video games in general. Another must have.", "hours": 36.8, "username": "MagikalKraker", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Any game where I can leap from a roof top, ram a hidden wrist knife into my target's neck, and then escape by climbing up another building, has to be great. It's assassin's creed 1 with less crap, and way more awesome.", "hours": 25.3, "username": "Delius", "products": 527, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Parkour through the beautiful streets of renaissance Italy... while murdering hundreds of men!", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Sonoshee", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-20", "text": "Just being present in the Renaissance cities of Firenze and Venezia is awe-inspiring. Ubisoft should get even more credit for creating an excellent game. The first Assassin's Creed had good gameplay, but became very tedious and repetitive (though had a great story, an introduction to the eternal conflict between the Templars and Assassins). Assassin's Creed 2 built upon the first and introduced so many new gameplay elements to make this version so much more enjoyable. Ezio also seems like such a relatable character compared to Altair...and you literally follow Ezio from his birth - which makes this game a novel of Ezio's life. That combined with the fantastic intrigue and historical roots of the Assassin's Creed plot, as well as the wonderfully believable settings in Renaissance Italy make for a game, nay a series, worth playing.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "GenXopherus", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-19", "text": "Is entertaining.", "hours": 66.9, "username": "Erionnes", "products": 374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "When you find yourself still awake playing this game at 6 in the morning you realize that the game you are playing is addicting.  With almost 17 hours of gameplay right now and not even halfway through the game I would recommend this game. However it is kinda frustrating trying to kill a gaurd and a musician comes right in front of your face and instead of kill a gaurd you kill the musician.  However that is just a small complaint, 9.5/10", "hours": 67.4, "username": "Sabecius", "products": 281, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "Very slick platformer with an engaging narrative and fantastic scenery to explore.", "hours": 1.4, "username": "Cigol", "products": 805, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 515, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "VERY FUN good storyline", "hours": 139.8, "username": "DAVIE THE WHITE", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "Holy cow, e' veramente divertente..!", "hours": 96.1, "username": "gioaudino", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "This is utter crap - once the game launches in OSX, the keyboard is no longer recognised. As you need the keyboard to play, that means you can't play the game. I'm using a non-customised 2010 iMac with the Apple wired USB keyboard. Pretty standard stuff. I really do not recommend this.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "Skiamakhos", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "My praises toward the Assassin's Creed series may be starting to sound a bit fanboyish, but what can I say?\nI reviewed Assassin's Creed a while back and there wasn't much I didn't enjoy about the game. Given it felt repetitive at times and the controls weren't best suited for pc.\nAssassin's Creed II looks and feels a lot like its predecessor; the game mechanics are pretty much the same. There are a few new attacks and movement altogether feels slightly improved. It might be just me though.\nUbisoft has done a great job improving both gameplay and the atmosphere.\nThe plot is now more compelling and even the cutscenes are fun to watch.\nThey've even managed to keep the amount of collectibles reasonable this time.\nAs for criticism; the game kind of feels like a facelift. The environment, mechanics and objectives are so similar to Assassin's Creed that even though the story is interesting and different, it feels like there could've been more to it.", "hours": 31.6, "username": "\\CCC\\ Procyon", "products": 331, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "A huge improvement from the first one, from gameplay to lasting appeal AC2 is another great installation of the Assassin's Creed series. The characters are interesting and add mysteries as well as conflict, and set the stage fro various missions as well as side missions, which unlike the first game, aren't repetitive. Collecting diamonds is a fun way to just explore any of the cities available. A particular mission and future memory is the funnest thing in the whole game for me, involving Da Vinci, nighttime and a whole lot of fire....just a couple of hints. This is the game that truly makes the series and gives ti a notable reputation. Brotherhood and Revelations can never top the plot and gameplay of AC2, even with multiplayer. This is a worthwhile buy for any fan of the series or any fan of Ubisoft's games. It combines freeroaming with stealth, a gripping storyline and memorable gameplay.", "hours": 41.9, "username": "Gamer", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "beautiful game.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "[FL]Shift", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "<3", "hours": 42.2, "username": "Kenka Banch\u014d 6: Soul & Blood", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Everything about this game is fantastic -- the story, the gameplay, and especially the characters. The gameplay can take several hours for the really dedicated going immediately between the main storyline missions, but the time can be stretched indefnitely by the size of the sandbox, and the number of side missions (races, assassination contracts, ect). I absolutely love it, and it Assassin's Creed is easily my favorite game series.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Erubees", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "It's not good. Controls are terrible. Tutorials give commands for xbox so you have to look up each one in the menus, which also are terrible. Can't skip cutscenes. Pass this one up.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "Mister Eel", "products": 241, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Complete sense of independence and amazing detail. Definitely a keeper.", "hours": 81.0, "username": "Masterfold", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 516, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "awesome the camara can be a bit of a pain in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665at time but over all fun and worth the money for many good hours of game play", "hours": 34.4, "user_id": "76561198010540441", "username": "Metalsage", "products": 342, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 517, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "one of the best in the sieres!", "hours": 24.1, "username": "No$kill_Bravo", "products": 121, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 517, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 takes the best aspects of the original Asassin's Creed and perfects them, creating a masterpiece.\nYou now have real open world gameplay, the story is more humane and emotionally engaging, and you get to visit beautiful cities of Renaissance Italy.\nIf you didn't like certain aspects of the first title, you'll love this game; and if you're not a fan of the AC series, now is the time to start.", "hours": 46.7, "username": "CrimsonEdge", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 517, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "Awesome music, great character arc of the main character, and overall great asthetic to the whole game. Played it start to finish 3 times back to back.", "hours": 110.4, "user_id": "76561197995171287", "username": "Snowed In Wolf", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 517, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Very well done. The history in the plot line and setting is a plus. I like the variety of complex assasinations you can choose from. The story line is unique. two thumbs up!", "hours": 35.1, "user_id": "76561198018499540", "username": "Milinex", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
