{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "The game itself is great, but the Mac port is pretty shoddy. It will frequently not launch at all.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "hoserama99", "products": 2130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "As much of a leap in entertainment that AC:1 was, AC:2 makes the same leap forward from that. Combat is less repetitive, environments draw you in, and an arsenal of new weapons make this game as fun as playing AC:1 the first time.", "hours": 79.7, "username": "Fanboat", "products": 642, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "It's-s game-a, with Mario! and killing doodz.", "hours": 49.8, "username": "Sam Ecorners", "products": 1202, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Pretty darn awesome. Takes the best parts of AC I and improves upon them. Great action matched up with a facinating storyline.", "hours": 30.0, "username": "Johntoxable", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Nice Game", "hours": 44.8, "user_id": "76561198052868417", "username": "Slutty Nurse", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "AC2 discards everything tedious, boring and annoying about the first game and instead improves massively upon the good things. Assassinations out the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 upgrades out the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 gorgeous cities out the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665- it's just wonderful. This is the first game in ages I got 100 % in while actually enjoying it. The story's also engaging, even though it's your typical conspiracy BS and the moral ambiguity of the first AC is largely gone (really the only part that I missed). So yeah, play that\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 You won't regret it if you like some of that assassin business.", "hours": 64.1, "username": "Ryokucha", "products": 393, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 518, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Perfect in every way. I'm admiring developers in Ubisoft for a great work of rebuilding renessaince Venezia and other cities.\nNothing is true, everything is permitted. =)", "hours": 22.2, "username": "50 Shades of Dany", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Molto bene!", "hours": 94.6, "username": "James", "products": 401, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Calm down and stab some templar... ^^", "hours": 41.6, "user_id": "76561197996024893", "username": "SilentAndY", "products": 366, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "If you didn't like Assassin's Creed 1, I recommend giving this one a shot. It removes the annoying and repetitive sidequests, and throws you into a much more expansive and detailed world.\nPlus you can cut someone's throat with a broom.", "hours": 48.4, "username": "chainsaw quest", "products": 591, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-09", "text": "HUGE improvement over its predecesor. Even better graphics, refined gameplay, great storyline (with many side missions), and even deeper gameplay make this Assassin's Creed one of the finest installments of the series.", "hours": 43.4, "username": "Hellspawn", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-09", "text": "One of the greatest games ever made, i'm super serial, a true masterpiece. Jesper Kyd's soundtrack is sublime, I like it bigbig as well as all the other\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 I completed this and all the others on OnLive, I bought this version as it's the Deluxe Edition but I've not played it yet, loool.", "username": "Dekion", "products": 452, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-08", "text": "parkourparkourparkourstabparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourstabstabparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourparkourstabparkourparkourparkourparkour.", "hours": 5.6, "username": "Charlie W", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-08", "text": "Fantastic game", "hours": 30.3, "username": "The Earthyn", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-07", "text": "The sequel to Assassin's Creed begins a new story from Desmond's genetic memories of a young Italian nobleman named Ezio Auditore da Firenze. The second game greatly expands upon the original in terms of gameplay as well as storytelling. Using a number of historical figures, Assassin's Creed II (AC2) successfully immerses you into historical fiction with a sci-fi twist and will leave you wanting more. Overall, AC2 offers a more open experience and allows you to customize your version of Ezio while also stemming away from the original's narrow/linear gameplay. AC2 is a must for fans, but it should be noted that AC2 require Ubisoft's Uplay as the game's launchpad.", "hours": 34.0, "username": "Hairbautt", "products": 674, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-06", "text": "Despite a slightly ridiculous overarching story, the narrative following Ezio Auditore de Firenze in his fight against the corrupt Borgias in a beautifully rendered Italy makes this game a great play. The only downside is some faults in actual gameplay, controls are clunky, the camera hates you, and combat is dull. However, it is worth looking past these faults for a great story", "hours": 82.3, "username": "royalGambler", "products": 399, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 519, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-06", "text": "Amazing game, amazing story.\n9/10", "hours": 64.4, "username": "M@rty\u2122", "products": 573, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-06", "text": "Despite a slightly ridiculous overarching story, the narrative following Ezio Auditore de Firenze in his fight against the corrupt Borgias in a beautifully rendered Italy makes this game a great play. The only downside is some faults in actual gameplay, controls are clunky, the camera hates you, and combat is dull. However, it is worth looking past these faults for a great story", "hours": 82.3, "username": "royalGambler", "products": 399, "early_access": false}
