{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-24", "text": "IMO is the best of the games in this series; really, this is the one that should be played.  the story is gripping, passionate, and will pull you in regardless of any skepticism... some flawed gameplay mechanics (as in need additional tweaks), but nothing that breaks the game itself.  Beautifully done, a much better game than its predecessor", "hours": 1.8, "username": "ivansword", "products": 1898, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-23", "text": "*-*  100% Sync", "hours": 64.6, "username": "XeLaphim", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-22", "text": "Much slicker and cleaner than the first. I have issues with the way camera control was handled in that it frequently switches from 3rd-person to platformer in mid-leap. Ezio is much more fleshed out as a character than Altair was, the missions are somewhat repetitive (find your target and kill him), but Renassance Italy has been very well crafted and it's just a lot of fun to run around in. A good variety of side missions and enough \"Da Vinci Code\" kind of stuff to satisfy the most die-hard conspiracy buffs. One early mission is especiailly hinky in the Steam version, but once past that, it's very smooth.", "hours": 212.9, "user_id": "76561198032084191", "username": "marstinson", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-18", "text": "Mejora todo lo visto en el primer AC. Ezio tiene mucho m\u00e1s carisma que Alta\u00efr.", "hours": 38.0, "username": "GavoKaotik", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 520, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-12", "text": "i was a excellent game with a storyline to match, i recommend this to anyone who likes killing people and having some fun while you do it!", "hours": 35.3, "username": "SniperKnighter", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-11", "text": "I wish i could do all that parkour!", "hours": 29.2, "username": "~IAmDeth~", "products": 190, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-05", "text": "...", "hours": 31.4, "user_id": "76561198042282293", "username": "K\u00e1\u010dko", "products": 198, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-29", "text": "Inspite of Ubisoft's sketchy and poor DRM. This game is just brilliant with an epic long story filled with action.\nIn the first 3 sequences, I found myself a little bit bored untill it started getting more exciting.\nI liked the fun free running and the smooth gameplay in this game. However, the camera angle goes wrong sometimes, but it's still amazing.\nHighly enjoyable and recommended to play.\n9/10", "hours": 36.8, "username": "Heisenburger\u2122", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-28", "text": "The end boss is the pope. You can headbutt the pope.", "hours": 80.6, "username": "\ud83d\udc0d\ud83d\udc0d unicode snake \ud83d\udc0d\ud83d\udc0d", "products": 337, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-27", "text": "Travel back in time and abort the designers of Assassin's creed 1 before they are born and can hoist their garbage upon the world. Meet interesting characters such as Machiavelli, Leonardo, and Evil Pope.\nAC2 improves upon the first in every conceivable way, but still has too many \"Follow the target without being seen\" missions.", "hours": 25.2, "user_id": "76561197978131107", "username": "Superbeef", "products": 1376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "One of my favorite games", "hours": 9.8, "username": "The Baumann", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "Amazing game, the story and environment is fantastic. It's also fairly lengthy compared to the newest iterations (Brotherhood and Revelations). This is my favorite Assassin's Creed game as well as one of my most favorite games ever. Can't wait for Assassin's Creed III.", "hours": 18.7, "username": "Kealmcking", "products": 610, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "Way better than AC1.  In fact, I can't really think of another sequel that improves more on the original than this one.  Whereas AC1 had you repeating the same types of missions over and over, AC2 has a huge variety of missions right up to the end.  Likewise, combat also has more variety with upgradeable armor, weapons, and home bases giving the gameplay a tiny bit more depth.  But perhaps best of all, while AC1's plot was silly, AC2's plot takes things to a level of complete insanity that is kind of charming in its own unintentionally absurd bat\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665way.  I can't think of another game, for example, that let's you storm a medieval castle, beat up a pope, and (mild spoilers) hob-knob with alien beings all in the space of a few minutes and all with a completely straight face. It's pure, pulp-video-game, guilty pleasure, trash--but in a good way!  Mindless fun.", "hours": 29.2, "username": "Der Ungrund", "products": 514, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-19", "text": "Perfect game! It introduced me to Assassin's Creed series.", "hours": 82.3, "username": "Michedelic", "products": 96, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 521, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-19", "text": "Solid 2nd installment to the series with only one aggrevating flaw. The game will cut off at random intervals. Sadly its not just me, talked to others and they had the same issue. Aside from that, gameplay is great, graphics are very good, and storyline is extremely immersive. Looking forward to Brotherhood, and am in hopes that it does not share the same problem.\nAMD Phenom II X6 1100T 3.3Ghz.\n6GB DDR2\n2.5TB 7200RPM, 16MB, SATA II\n16MB/s Cable/N300 Wifi\nXFX 2GB Radeon 6950\nVizio 42\" 1080P 3D LED", "hours": 104.0, "username": "Systemic", "products": 2623, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-19", "text": "It's like Assassin's Creed 1 but good.", "hours": 101.2, "username": "DroppinLoot (DavyDave)", "products": 125, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-18", "text": "Very interesting storyline.It's not repetetive like the first Assassin's Creed.  Worth every penny.", "hours": 32.5, "username": "Zeno Sama's Noob Cousin (IAN)", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-17", "text": "Amazingly fun", "hours": 30.5, "username": "4cylinder", "products": 407, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "One of my favorites in the series. I have to admit I've become attached to the character Ezio which has made me uneasy to play Revelations knowing it's the last he'll be in. All in all I feel that the story of his life has been well done and drags you into it, you meet Ezio from birth and go on to see his life unfold with a wonderful expansive environment to explore and great characters to get involved with.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "Aracnel", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "\u0420\u0435\u0434\u043a\u043e \u0432 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0438\u043d\u0434\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0430\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0435\u0439 \u0433\u043b\u0443\u0431\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u043b\u044f\u044e\u0442 \u043e\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0438\u0442\u044c\u0441\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0445\u043e\u0442\u044f \u0431\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044e. \u041d\u043e Assassin's Creed II \u044f\u0432\u043d\u043e\u0435 \u0438\u0441\u043a\u043b\u044e\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435! \u0427\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0443 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0443\u0442  \u0442\u044b \u043f\u043e\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0435\u0448\u044c \u043a\u0430\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0438\u0433\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0440\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0434 \u043e\u0448\u0438\u0431\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0441\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044e \u0441 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c\u044e. \u0417\u0434\u0435\u0441\u044c \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043d\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0451 \u043d\u0430\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0430\u043d\u0447\u0438\u0432\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0444\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u0441\u044e\u0436\u0435\u0442\u043e\u043c, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u044b\u0439 \u043f\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u044f\u0432\u043b\u044f\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0433\u043b\u0430\u0432\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043a\u043e\u0437\u044b\u0440\u0435\u043c \u044d\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b. \u0418\u0437 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u044b \u0443\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0441\u043a\u0443\u0447\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043c\u0438\u0441\u0441\u0438, \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 \u0437\u0434\u0435\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0430\u0442\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0443 \u044d\u043f\u043e\u0445\u0438 \u0432\u043e\u0437\u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0438\u0434\u0435\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e", "hours": 55.2, "username": "St_Flash \u2764 Mass Effect", "products": 703, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-27", "text": "Huge improvement on the first game's formula. It still has some cracks and imperfections, but overall a worthy sequel to the somewhat bland first outing. And would you look at that, it's a nice PC port too.\nI would recommend a gamepad, as the PC controls are a bit icky.", "hours": 36.1, "username": "Karth Komputer 2.0", "products": 322, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-26", "text": "Engrossing gameplay, decent graphics, and a farfetched but entertaining storyline, this game is worth playing. 8/10", "hours": 21.5, "username": "zark", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-17", "text": "Way more varied, polished and forgiving than AC1. The initial charm is later poisoned by non-detection sneaking and tight countdowns.", "hours": 32.1, "username": "Chordian", "products": 266, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-13", "text": "One of the most beautiful games I've ever played. The plot is much better and gameplay is not as repetitive as in AC1. Gamepad is recommended for better experience.", "hours": 55.8, "username": "Von the Wat?", "products": 1177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 522, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-10", "text": "cool", "hours": 30.6, "user_id": "76561198059750566", "username": "Electivire King", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-03", "text": "This is the first Assassin's Creed I ever got, and I got it first on the Xbox.\nThe game has a GREAT atmosphere and a great engine. This is the first episode from Assassin's Creed where you meet Ezio Auditore.\nIf you are into Assassin's Creed, and you don't have this, its a must have!", "hours": 44.9, "username": "TwistedRaven", "products": 538, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-02", "text": "Would've been great if they cut down on the recycling of areas and timeline leaps. More of Desmond and more present day non-combat storytelling would've helped to break things up. Overall though it's a lot better than the original. Requiescat in pace.", "hours": 26.8, "username": "\u300clandwhale\u300d", "products": 967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "Definitely an improvement over the first one.  Missions are more varied and the game has a larger sandbox element.  The main thing I didn't like about it was learning the controls, since you have to check the controls in the options menu in order to figure out what the symbols mean.  The locations were really cool, and I really liked the jumping puzzles in the assassin tombs.  Game could get frustrating at times cuz Ezio would do the wrong move and that would ultimately end in your death, but it was a fun game overall, definitely worth playing.  It took me 30 hours to finish it 100%.", "hours": 41.8, "username": "[\u2665] OMFGeoff", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-30", "text": "If you have never played Assassins Creed, This is a hook line and sinker. i never finished the 1st one, but this one inspired me to finish the rest, and i was damn glad i did!", "hours": 29.1, "username": "mAngO", "products": 250, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-29", "text": "Good graphics, epic story, cool combo moves. This game is really good and i really recommend it, to be honest it is a begging game of a trilogy, but an epic beginning, if you start playing, you won't be able to stop ^^ soo. if you like GTA, and like fighting, this is your game", "hours": 22.9, "username": "\u272a wild", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-28", "text": "Very good game! It's more than I expect for! The history is great! Grafics could be better, but way u play is more important than grafics.\nI recommend!", "hours": 63.3, "username": "Lucas", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-27", "text": "Played 'em all, and I think this is still the best AC game. Compelling story takes you throughout Ezio's life, rewards throughout the game shake things up a bit, and the varied and beautiful settings put its predecessor and even its successors in some ways to shame. Don't play this first, of course ... but be sure to play it. :)", "hours": 118.8, "username": "afinati", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-19", "text": "A massive improvement from the first game.. thats all\nBuy it", "hours": 46.7, "username": "IAmTheTrueDuck [Matt]", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-09", "text": "Wow. Better than first one in every conceivable way. Play is FAR LESS linear and the cast of memorable characters is much broader. Addition of the \"database\" makes keeping track of the vast amount of historical and character information presented manageable. Be sure to play the first one before this, or you may not want to go back! A+", "hours": 22.8, "username": "Tabulation", "products": 467, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 523, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-04", "text": "TL;DR: BUY THIS. NOW. DO IT, ASSHAT.\nLonger review:\nWide open world? Check, with three main cities (Florence, Venice, Forli) and a lot of open space (Apenine Mountains, the Tuscany and little towns of San Gimignano and YOU'RE OWN FREAKIN' VILLAGE Monteriggioni).\nSidequests: Check, most of them are really fun to complete and give you insigths on life in the Renaissance. You don't have to complete them though, but many are rewarding. Restoring your town to its former glory for example, and seeing it slowly grow more prosperous with people visiting and the run down walls and buildings repaired.\nCharacters: OH GOD YES. No offense to Alta\u00efr but he is as charismatic as a block of wood. Ezio feels like a real person, whom we see grow over the years from a brash punk into a wise man. And the enemies are great! Which brings us to...\nStory: The story of the first Assassins Creed was a little rushed and offered no explanations to what the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 was happening. They fixed that here. First, you have a codex that you can read for reference on the time period, people and buildings you visit giving much needed context.\nSecond, the grand scheme of things is set, the events that happen in the past and present make sense and leave room for interesting mysteries and developments and COMPLETE THE SUBJECT 16 QUEST FOR EXTRA MIND\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.\nOverall: Very few flaws, my second favorite game of the series!", "hours": 55.7, "username": "Drunk Russian", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-03", "text": "One of the most beautiful games ive ever played, and everything else is pretty damn good too. I love the story line of Ezio though i tihnk alot of people would agree that its been a little played out, but its still a great game none the less. Buy!!!", "hours": 12.1, "user_id": "76561197987509829", "username": "BrAxY", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-27", "text": "If you played Assassin's Creed or any of the other sequels but skipped this one, don't skip it any longer. They improved on much from the first game as well as it's length. Each time I thought I was nearing the end there was more to do. Plenty to collect, plenty of optional missions and plenty of people to kill. If you like action games ala Tomb Raider, Splinter Cell etc, I'd recommend this game. While they might be more \"shooting\" it's still similar in some ways. The stealth isn't quite splinter cell and the jumping and climbing isn't quite Tomb Raider but combined it's something different and great all it's own. I'm looking forward to playing the other sequels for more assassin goodness.", "hours": 34.8, "username": "AvidWriter", "products": 1094, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-23", "text": "WOW, This story just gets better and better! Even though i loved Alta\u00efr, Ezio is a legend. Words can't describe how beautiful and how detailed his story is. The way they portray his life and the path he takes is truly a masterpiece and work of art. The personality and charm of Ezio is a hard one to top.\nResponse to beating AC1 = SERIOUSLY?!!;\nResponse to beating AC2 = OMGOGMGOMGOGSDJKDSKGJDJGHSDG WTF. NEXT ONE NOW!\nThis series is off to an amazing start and i look forward to the next one anxiously.\nOverall Rating: 10/10.\nOne of the best games I have played.", "hours": 59.8, "username": "Demadizzle", "products": 473, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-21", "text": "lots of fun and good story line", "hours": 151.9, "user_id": "76561198005978519", "username": "Outlaw Pimp", "products": 339, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-20", "text": "Hey it's the sequel to climbing. In this title you climb, and you climb some more. You also climb with a time limit. I hope you dont waste your time with the feathers because climbing is JUST SO \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING FUN.", "hours": 20.8, "username": "not okay", "products": 955, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-19", "text": "This game is so involved, so in-depth, that if you don't play it... you must be brain dead. The graphics are amazing, the controls are fluid, and over all story are just incredible.", "hours": 41.7, "username": "Haphdamned", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-13", "text": "If you like lonely italian men playing with swords, buy this game.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Merk Murica gret once more", "products": 376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-12", "text": "\uc7ac\ubc0b\ub2e4\ub2a5", "hours": 55.3, "user_id": "76561198052793732", "username": "LaughMan", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-07", "text": "An artistic masterpiece, providing an incredibly deep and immersive storyline. The character realism was fabulous. The voice acting is outstanding. Ezio feels like Antonio Banderas combining a romancing charm with his cold-hearted killer instincts. The fundamentals of the original game have been vastly improved upon. Many of the finishing moves are just spectacular to watch; the double switchblade faceplant always brings a smile to my face.\nStraight up combat is still a weak point in the game, but they increased the fun factor by providing more means to avoid it like hiring thieves, using smoke bombs, creating a distraction by throwing money, strategically placing corpses, and assassinating targets from distance with a pistol.\nAt ~30 gameplay hours, Assassin's Creed II was an amazing experience.", "hours": 30.2, "username": "JonesR", "products": 1346, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 524, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-07", "text": "Still the best Assassin's Creed I've played. Everything comes together so nicely, and just fits.", "hours": 1.3, "username": "Sarah", "products": 942, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 525, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-07", "text": "An artistic masterpiece, providing an incredibly deep and immersive storyline. The character realism was fabulous. The voice acting is outstanding. Ezio feels like Antonio Banderas combining a romancing charm with his cold-hearted killer instincts. The fundamentals of the original game have been vastly improved upon. Many of the finishing moves are just spectacular to watch; the double switchblade faceplant always brings a smile to my face.\nStraight up combat is still a weak point in the game, but they increased the fun factor by providing more means to avoid it like hiring thieves, using smoke bombs, creating a distraction by throwing money, strategically placing corpses, and assassinating targets from distance with a pistol.\nAt ~30 gameplay hours, Assassin's Creed II was an amazing experience.", "hours": 30.2, "username": "JonesR", "products": 1346, "early_access": false}
