{"product_id": "33230", "page": 525, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-12", "text": "Oh Ezio....never having played AC1 I must say I am in love with this serious and looking forward to continuing on in the next installment.  The fighting is fun and can be as varied as you want, and the rooftop running can be fun, or can leap off at 180\u00b0 from where you intended plunging you to your death!", "hours": 47.0, "username": "Banzai5150", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 526, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-07", "text": "great story , perfect gameplay , great atmosphere, really one of the best games ever made", "hours": 96.8, "username": "\u00a4 Din", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 526, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-07", "text": "My first AC game that did not disappoint me.\nThe story hooks you in and keeps you playing. If you like open world areas and exploration in games with stealth/combat on the side, this game will be perfect for you.", "hours": 26.8, "username": "namsookee", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 526, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-06", "text": "Much better than the first game and beautifully crafted. More weapon variety and a massive cities. Worth playing in order for enjoyment of a well-written story.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "BlowitAllUp", "products": 403, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 526, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-05", "text": "The controls can take a little bit to get the hang of. Otherwise it is a very entertaining game with lot of freedom.", "hours": 101.1, "username": "Ori | Meldon", "products": 175, "early_access": false}
