{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Renaissance setting, music by Jesper Kyd and a great story make Assassin's Creed II a mothercussin' badass of a game!", "hours": 16.4, "username": "WaveMaster", "products": 742, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "AC2, really immersive. The exploration and story  aspect of the game is fantastic, definitely worth a buy.", "hours": 38.3, "username": "Reo", "products": 416, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "The sequel to the excellent Assassin's Creed game, it builds upon its predecessor in many ways, improving upon the few faults of it. Set in Renaissance Italy, the visuals and story of this game are both stunning. This is a game well worth buying.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Regime", "products": 1157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Possibly the best of all Assassin's Creed games.\nAssassin's Creed Brotherhood felt like an add-on.\nAssassin's Creed Revelations felt like it had a very thin amount of story content, and the changes (such as faces) made it feel unfamiliar, the art is very nice, but ACII seems to be the best game still.", "hours": 36.7, "username": "Flame", "products": 457, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Outstanding game. Better in some ways than AC: Brotherhood. A really solid title, I can't recommend it highly enough.", "hours": 32.4, "username": "Clyde Chestnut Barrow", "products": 349, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Assassins Creed II is such an improvement over the original game which, while fun to explore and leap around, had not much to actually do except the core assassinations.\nThis adds apart from new weapons and an obvious new era to go around in, a good set of side missions and extra things to do. I explored everything and it was amazing fun for moderate periods of time. You can make things more difficult with self-imposed ways of doing the missions too. There are also additional tombs you need to complete which usually are much more about jumping then combat or stealth.\nThe fighting is pretty reasonable; timed counter moves, varieties of weapons. Still pretty easy and no difficulty select anywhere to be found.\nThe improvements to the writing are also welcomed since there are a ton of cutscenes. Bad guys are villianous and evil! Good guys are nice and humorous! You can ignore it being \"a recreation of the past via. DNA\" if you so wish. Seeing historical figures talk is great fun!", "hours": 44.3, "username": "Finaldeath", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 529, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Great game, and adds an interesting twist.", "hours": 8.8, "username": "Alypants", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Assassins Creed II is such an improvement over the original game which, while fun to explore and leap around, had not much to actually do except the core assassinations.\nThis adds apart from new weapons and an obvious new era to go around in, a good set of side missions and extra things to do. I explored everything and it was amazing fun for moderate periods of time. You can make things more difficult with self-imposed ways of doing the missions too. There are also additional tombs you need to complete which usually are much more about jumping then combat or stealth.\nThe fighting is pretty reasonable; timed counter moves, varieties of weapons. Still pretty easy and no difficulty select anywhere to be found.\nThe improvements to the writing are also welcomed since there are a ton of cutscenes. Bad guys are villianous and evil! Good guys are nice and humorous! You can ignore it being \"a recreation of the past via. DNA\" if you so wish. Seeing historical figures talk is great fun!", "hours": 44.3, "username": "Finaldeath", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Great game, and adds an interesting twist.", "hours": 8.8, "username": "Alypants", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "This game is just the right combination of fun, humor, and AUGH, WHY, GAME, WHY? Really enjoyable.", "hours": 75.4, "username": "machinette", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Awesome gameplay, stunning graphics and really intruiging plotline. It improves on the first game in every single way.\nYou have to play the Assassin's Creed games in your lifetime.", "hours": 25.1, "user_id": "76561197970797937", "username": "blackwiddow", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
