{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "If you like freedom of movement, you'll like this game. It enables you to run through renissance Florence and Venice, streets or rooftops. Cities are accurately made, only smaller.\nThe story follows Ezio, who after loosing his father and brother finds out that he is a descendant of the family of assassins. He than begins his revenge with some help from Leonardo da Vinci himself.", "hours": 44.0, "user_id": "76561197968554856", "username": "kerberan", "products": 303, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "This game had nothing to do with Creed from The Office!!!", "hours": 45.6, "username": "I buy airlines", "products": 184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Best game I ever played. The only thing I've couldn't done was one of the tomb mission. That was my bad I think :D", "hours": 59.2, "user_id": "76561198049327013", "username": "\u03c0", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 530, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "A sequel that improves a lot on the original. Amazing fun.", "hours": 35.7, "username": "CJWilkie", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Part 1 of the Ezio trilogy, AC2 takes the stellar foundation established in the first Assassin's Creed and refines both the gameplay and the personal narrative to astounding results.  This is the game where the series found its legs.  Saying that out is s must have is an understatement.  Play this game.", "hours": 44.2, "username": "Stunt Rush", "products": 735, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Best game I've played in years.  Engaging story with characters you actually care about with brilliant and varied gameplay.", "hours": 25.9, "username": "Speetr", "products": 602, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "A good, sound follow up to A/C 1, you will now play as Ezio; Desmond's Renaissance-era Italian ancestor. Building off the combat system from A/C 1, the finishers are just as satisfying, with some new weapons added for a bit of diversity (and an option other than throwing knives for ranged). If you're in to upgrading property and collecting items, you can spend a long while following side quests and receiving different rewards. The Armour of Altair is well worth getting (because its the only armour set in the game that doesn't require repairing after combat). The story itself is quite entertaining and  the ending is pretty weird. Good fun! ****", "hours": 27.4, "username": "Adeptus Ineptus", "products": 644, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-26", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed in the series", "hours": 10.1, "user_id": "76561197970538831", "username": "WiLdMaN107", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-24", "text": "Words can't describe how amazing this game was on release. It was such a vast improvement in relation to the original title that it even went so far as to make the first game feel terribly uncomfortable to play. The visuals are beautiful, the combat is more brutal and fluid, there have been countless gameplay additions and tweaks, the AC story goes deeper down the rabbit hole, and we get a protagonist that isn't as flat as a cardboard cut-out (sorry Altair lovers). A nigh perfect game.", "hours": 41.9, "user_id": "76561198006893472", "username": "Fear2288", "products": 418, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-21", "text": "The man who made this game, the plot and  created the general idea behind the story-line has to be a genius and nominated for a Nobel-prize..... Awsome gameplay and thrilling action", "hours": 106.3, "username": "snwpaul", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-06", "text": "Very good single player game, i love it! amazing fighting, this is definetly a game i'd reccommend to anyone.", "hours": 6.5, "username": "Decrepified", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "This builds on the previous game, and becomes so much better!  You may find the early parts of the game frustrating, while you go through the whole retraining.  Get used to it:  The game will toss you new mechanics all the way till the end!  The game in general is much more forgiving... and you can swim!  Lastly, as I mentioned for the previous game, this is quite possibly the best story arc I've seen in a game.  You should really pick up all three (and soon four) and play them in otrder!", "hours": 57.0, "username": "mdwyer", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-30", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is considered to be the best of the AC series, and I would have to agree.  It has the best story and the gameplay is awesome.", "hours": 45.3, "username": "Seraph", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 531, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-23", "text": "A much better, tighter game than AC1 in every way. If you want to shank people, this is your game.", "hours": 74.7, "username": "CarlCX", "products": 2372, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-19", "text": "Intense game and I fell in love with it when I played. Definitely worth the measly $20 asking price. You won't be disappointed with it.", "hours": 32.9, "username": "Raukuu", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-16", "text": "Fluid gameplay, epic story, and plenty to do make this an instant classic. If you do not have it, buy it.", "hours": 36.9, "user_id": "76561198045872273", "username": "The Cheesinator", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-11", "text": "THIS GAME IS DA FREEKN BOMB MAN !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "hours": 152.7, "user_id": "76561198019273105", "username": "Dwayne \"The Minion\" Johnson", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-10", "text": "Continues the story of Desmond Miles, in the memories of Ezio Auditore, so if you enjoyed the first Assassin's Creed you are going to like this one much better. They explain things more, but still leave you with LOTS of questions. Improving the series as each game gets made.", "hours": 46.1, "username": "ItadakiTom", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-08", "text": "I want to crawl into this game and live in it.", "hours": 91.1, "username": "Celairel", "products": 341, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-30", "text": "Equally good looking as it's predecessor AC2 features a much longer (maybe a bit too long) and more interesting story based in medieval Italy. The basic game mechanics are the same but they managed to make the missions far less repetetive than in AC1 by breaking missions into smaller subtasks and weaving cutscenes into them. Another new thing is the possibility to equip your assassin with various weapons and accessories. If you liked AC1, you won't be disappointed with this game.", "hours": 51.3, "username": "go_oh", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-27", "text": "Awesome! Easily tops the original for creating new options for gameplay, modifiable inventory, weapons, and items. Graphics are improved just so noticeably from the original, but don't wear too much on fps which is nice. There are new ways to blend in with crowds and avoid the AI... however, on that note, the AI combat and awareness is only just barely improved from the original Assasin's Creed. This game still scores very high in my list of single-player games. You can easily spend hours playing in this sequel, thanks to new added modes in the explore style of the game, which differ from the original.", "hours": 54.1, "username": "Vern", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-26", "text": "Way better than the first one, the story continues. More action, more missions, more background plots that make you think and of course, more assassinations!", "hours": 110.1, "username": "Munchiechu", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-23", "text": "As I was finally able to play this game on a decent computer, I began to play it soonest possible. The story really succeeded to catch from the very beginning; starting out as a (somehow) normal guy with no weapons and later on obtaining more weapons as you play and collect Codex pages, with which you fight your way through several great cities, to finally defeat the Pope of Roma and thereby avenge the murder of your family.\nThis game really has amused me with both graphics, voice acting (accents!), the beautiful areas, the atmosphere, and the gameplay - sure some missions were almost identical, but you also get to do a huge variety of different tasks such as attending a carnival.\nAlmost nothing for me to put a finger on except a few rarely occouring glitches. The end is also amazing and full of beams and effects.\nTo be honest I'd call this game truly epic.", "hours": 25.8, "username": "LameHead", "products": 732, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 532, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-22", "text": "A huge step up from the first game. AC2 is a good game with absolutely loads of content. Really, there's a lot. Too much content one could argue. The best comparison I can think of is GTA meets 15th century. This is what the first game should have been. My only major complaint; Ubisoft please fix the screen tearing, it's ridiculous in this game no matter what the settings are. Kind of brought me out of my immersion. Definitely worth a play.", "hours": 21.5, "username": "Des", "products": 317, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-11", "text": "One of the best action game I've played until today. It fixed all the stuff I didn't like in the first game (like being repetitive) and gave me 24h+ of fun. Worth every minute!\n\"Nothing is true. Everything is permitted.\"", "hours": 40.8, "username": "MiKau", "products": 450, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-11", "text": "This game gave me nightmares. They really did not give a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665about the story one bit did they? So awful.\nThe gameplay on the other hand is okay... but the camera is ultra frustrating and makes some platforming elements ridiculously 1997-era. I would not recommend this game. I rarely say this as I like my games long, but this thing just drags on and on.", "hours": 14.0, "username": "federated state of trollnesia", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-11", "text": "In the beginning of AC2 Ezio looks like a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, but give him a chance - this kid knows how to kick out the jams!", "hours": 29.1, "username": "C\u00f6nstans\"lemmy\"Barr\u00f6n", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-10", "text": "Great story, great fights.", "hours": 7.2, "username": "Takishimi", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-09", "text": "Great game. Beat it in a little over 20 hours. But once you beat the missions, there is nothing to do. Little/No replayability", "hours": 35.4, "username": "Qmzp2", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-09", "text": "wonderful!\u00aa", "hours": 52.6, "username": "madkingdom", "products": 326, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-09", "text": "\u041d\u0435\u0441\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e \u043e\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0445 \u0438\u0433\u0440 \u043e\u0442 Ubisoft.", "hours": 34.0, "username": "indigo\u2122", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-02", "text": "An interesting revival of the Assassin's Creed series.\nThe storyline feels almost the same in aspects like ' someone screws up and you gotta fix the mess', but that seems like a way to explain why you have to gain your skills.\nThere are more interesting things happening in this version of Assassin's creed as new weapons are introduced and you are no longer safe in haystacks; but you gain abilities to counter all these new tricks.\nThe sequel to this game is 'Assassin's Creed Brotherhood' which continues the plot after finishing this game.  Only Assassin's Creed Brotherhood has multiplayer and that is seperate from the singleplayer.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "DarkOnistar", "products": 1130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-28", "text": "Truly a epic game series, the story will keep you coming back for more. Im over 40hours in and am still going strong in the main campaign.\nDef a must buy 8/10", "hours": 51.4, "username": "RyReZar", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 533, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-28", "text": "A VERY nice game!!!! But the sequel is even better again!!!!", "hours": 60.5, "username": "[+rep] RePLAY [DK]", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-25", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 further polishes what Assassin's Creed started. Removing the linear preparation and focusing more heavily on story helped meld this series away from a \"prep, stab, rinse, repeat\" to a much more enjoyable \"I'm doing this because I have to story.\" Free-Running is improved, voice acting is superb, beating out the rigid acting of Altair.\nIt is definitely a worthy successor that while doesn't change the formula up too much, still provides enough new to the table to justify it's price and the time commitment.", "hours": 26.1, "username": "Freyar", "products": 1368, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-21", "text": "Its not a bad game :)", "hours": 33.7, "user_id": "76561198048636630", "username": "Yoojimbo", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-21", "text": "The problem with the first Assassin Creed was that it \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing sucked huge\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 You did the same three tasks over and over until you wanted to blow your brains out. Then the controls were god awful because your stupid\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665character would jump where the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 he felt like was a good spot, which is typically into some area that leads to his death. Anyways, they luckily fixed those problems in this game and actually made a pretty decent game this time. The environments are huge, the missions are much more detailed and varied, and the game is pretty damn fun to kill people. Yeah, and this is a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing Ubisoft game too..", "hours": 64.2, "username": "Dildo Baggins\u2122\ud83d\udc49\ud83d\udc4c", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-18", "text": "Really fun, but did get tedious towards the very end. The same thing happened in the first one for me but that one got tedious at about the mid way point. So, much better than the first but still need to tweak the boring fights/stealth at the end.", "hours": 46.9, "username": "xabbott", "products": 581, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-17", "text": "The scenery and detail in this series is amazing.  Had a bad day at work?  Slip on some headphones, run across a few rooftops and climb up a tower.  The view is breathtaking.", "hours": 90.1, "user_id": "76561197995868338", "username": "Azrial M.", "products": 279, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-15", "text": "Good Game but, after story its boring :) nothing to do, no fun goind around. 7/10", "hours": 22.8, "username": "Bob", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-14", "text": "One of my favorite games of all time.\nEverything about this game is right.\nEverything glorious and amazing about the original Assassin's Creed is present in this game, and everything unfortunate, or boring about the original (there was a lot of that) was either tossed out or upgraded and reworked to be completely amazing too. On top of that, this game adds on HUGE amounts of great new stuff to the series, and the hero, Ezio Auditore da Firenze, is a dozen times more awesome than Alta\u00efr was in the first game.\nHell, Ezio is one of the most awesome characters anywhere ever.\nOne of the best soundtracks of any game ever.\nSeriously, if they kept releasing DLC for this game I'd never stop buying and playing it.", "username": "Thunderous Clockwork WarMachine", "products": 312, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-12", "text": "Outshines its predecessor in almost every way imaginable, mission structure has been refined to the point where repetativeness from AC1 is a thing of the past. Navigation and free running has become more economical and effecient, and the city has a genuine feel of a bustling society, the lifelike quality is astonishing, that there is always something interesting going on around you... and if you're like me you'll walk to your next mission, even if it's very far away, just to observe the surroundings...  on the same note, the protagonist is a much more interesting character than AC1. The one thing that really impressed me with this game is how tightly knit the story is, and it's a real staple of the series now. I very highly recommend this game, and it's successor: Brotherhood... but be aware that the series is very much story-based, and you'd be doing yourself a tremendous disservice to play the games out of sequence. This series is shaping up to be one of my all-time favorite", "hours": 155.7, "username": "[USN] MANRAY", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-12", "text": "You see me on that belltower over there? Now you don't.", "hours": 69.6, "user_id": "76561198003310804", "username": "Kyogre the Ogre", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 534, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-10", "text": "It held my interest for a while, but it really is a game about just doing the same few things over and over and over.  I never finished it.  I got to venice and just couldn't stomach it anymore.  I do not understand why some people rave about this game.  It is my first and last look at this game series.  I am glad I bought it on a steam super-sale.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "TheSilverHammer", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-12", "text": "You see me on that belltower over there? Now you don't.", "hours": 69.6, "user_id": "76561198003310804", "username": "Kyogre the Ogre", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-10", "text": "It held my interest for a while, but it really is a game about just doing the same few things over and over and over.  I never finished it.  I got to venice and just couldn't stomach it anymore.  I do not understand why some people rave about this game.  It is my first and last look at this game series.  I am glad I bought it on a steam super-sale.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "TheSilverHammer", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-08", "text": "Beautiful visuals. Very authentic and various locations (Florence, Forly, Venice). Easy and somehow fun acrobatic. Godlike music from Jesper Kyd. Too easy fights which is a bit of bad. As silver lining - animations are good. And setting and plot looks like it was taken from Dan Brown's books. Guess, it is must have. Want to take a look on Brotherhood.", "hours": 40.0, "username": "I_Ramiz", "products": 755, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-28", "text": "If you were ever interested in the rogue character class in RPGs, or ever interested in the Thief games, or dirty fighting, or anything that has to do with ninjas or hitmen or assassins, you'll probably like this game. Ezio, the player character, unravels a plot by a seemingly unstoppable nemesis. With revenge in mind and a supportive uncle, he sets out to bring his enemies down once and for all. What the game lacks in serious stealth abilities, it makes up for with special combat moves and special techniques (like distraction), as well as wardrobe customization and plenty of parkour. Solid improvement on its predecessor.", "hours": 101.9, "user_id": "76561197969900960", "username": "Gidar", "products": 312, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-25", "text": "This is what every sequel should be; better in every way. The game play was varied immensely, assassinations could be performed in a variety of ways, and continued play after completing the story wasn't pointless unlike it's predecessor. Can't wait to continue the story in brotherhood!", "hours": 40.6, "username": "DRPEPPERMAKESTHEWORLDTASTEBETTER", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-24", "text": "Haven't played this? You deserve to be assassinated. Beautiful cities, varying environments, missions, upgrades and a gripping storyline - all serve as evidence in your guilty-as-charged indictment. Begone now, lest your deprived self beckons my wrath.", "hours": 24.5, "user_id": "76561198026954905", "username": "fyroman", "products": 369, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-22", "text": "Great game, beat the core gameplay in two weeks but there's plenty of sideline content.  Definitely worth playing", "hours": 113.5, "user_id": "76561198046273056", "username": "Symphoneum", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-21", "text": "++ again nice mapping, but slightly worse than in ac1\n+ I like the new shopping and stuff\n+ and I like the new war maces etc\n+ Ezio is the better Altair =)\n-- your new medicine makes you really immortal in ac2 ... no one can beat you (only a fall from rooftops)\n--- you hardly ever need medicine cuz the fights are now SUPER DUPER easy\n-- the assassins tombs are a pain in the a**\n--- even more ranged weapons? you hardly ever use them cuz you are already half-god in close combat\npossible SPOILERS!!!!!!!!!!!!\n--- the story is now super crappy... like indiana jones 4 crappy\n--- da vinci AND machiavelli??? come on!", "hours": 30.7, "username": "kingkrabbe.#bof", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-20", "text": "The difference between AC1 & AC2 is crazy. If you liked AC1 you're gonna love this. I thought it added more into the game without taking anything away, or making you feel overwhelmed. This is my favorite out of the 3 games out right now.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Mr. Roboto", "products": 2488, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 535, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-13", "text": "I was skeptical at first thinking not much would have changed from the first game but i was very wrong. The scenery is great the story is interesting and most importantly the gameplay is very enjoyable.", "hours": 18.6, "username": "Invisible Man", "products": 514, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-13", "text": "If you didn't like assassins creed 1 due to the sheer \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ness of it. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 IT. Buy this one and prepare to bust nuts like noone has seen before. Face McStabbins", "hours": 14.0, "username": "Diazepanda", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-10", "text": "This is so much better tahn the first game it's stupid", "hours": 44.6, "username": "Gvaz", "products": 1206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-10", "text": "Game runs and looks great on the PC a reccomend. One of the best games of its time.", "hours": 40.3, "user_id": "76561198040360229", "username": "O'Maley", "products": 526, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-02", "text": "Oh, no!  Renaissance Nazzies!!!  Kill'd 'em!", "hours": 53.2, "username": "Boxcar", "products": 431, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-01", "text": "Assassins Creed II. Definately better than it's predecessor, AC2 offers a deeper and more evolved storyline along with rich graphics and dynamic game play. I'm giving this game an  8 / 10.", "hours": 61.7, "username": "Vel", "products": 532, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-01", "text": "\u5230\u4eca\u5929\uff0c\u7ec8\u4e8e\u901a\u5173\u4e86\uff0c\u672c\u6765\u5bf9\u5144\u5f1f\u4f1a\u6ca1\u4ec0\u4e48\u5174\u8da3\u7684\uff0c\u4f46\u662f2\u4ee3\u7684\u901a\u5173\u8ba9\u6211\u5bf9\u5144\u5f1f\u4f1a\u4ea7\u751f\u4e86\u6781\u5927\u7684\u5174\u8da3\uff0c\u6700\u540e\u6234\u65af\u66fc\u7684\u73b0\u4ee3\u683c\u6597\u5b9e\u5728\u592a\u6446\uff0c\u5144\u5f1f\u4f1a\uff0c\u611f\u89c975%off\u5427\uff01\uff01\uff01\n\u6700\u540e\u603b\u7ed3\u4e0b\uff0c\u867d\u7136\u5f88\u591a\u4eba\u90fd\u8bf4\u8fc7\u4e86\uff0c\u523a\u5ba2\u4fe1\u67612\u2014\u2014\u795e\u4f5c\u4e0d\u89e3\u91ca\uff01", "hours": 10.8, "username": "rainbowrocky", "products": 862, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "This game is awesome, much lenghtier and thought-out than the first game, play this game you piece of dirty\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665or I'll \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 your dad in the left nostril and keep his right nostril for grip when it gets intense", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Yer a wizard harry", "products": 413, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-30", "text": "Big improvement over the first game with tons more content while keeping true to what made the first one great.", "hours": 85.6, "user_id": "76561197999030938", "username": "Malsyste", "products": 361, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-24", "text": "Assassin's Creed II offers a lot of excellent content and an intriguing story that combines fantasy, history, and conspiracy theory.  More importantly, it expands and improves upon all the gameplay elements from the first game. You get more options in combat, more unique missions, more interesting locations, and more extras to collect. The soundtrack is also great.", "hours": 30.2, "username": "Sulfur Occult", "products": 329, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 536, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-24", "text": "Very intersting game, loved the first one and never really got the chance to get the second one until i saw the Steam sale that had all 3 for $30, and i must say that the story, graphics, and game play is pretty polished and well designed.\nThe only complaint i have about the game is that it is ridicuiously difficult to play with a keyboard and mouse, I recommend that you buy a gamepad or a pc version of a Xbox 360 controller. Overall i give the game a 9/10", "hours": 26.4, "user_id": "76561198005894381", "username": "Escurofalcon", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-22", "text": "50 Hours to complete it to 100%.\nThe game is great as a fun tale to tell and be a part of, engaging characters and some very nice effects.\nThe biggest problem is the controls. More suited to the XBox, some of the movements - in particular wall jump - really need to be revamped for PC. I actually spent 4.5 hours in the final Assassins Tomb to get the armour, because I kept falling off the ledges or doing a reverse jump into the water instead of jumping to the side.\nSome of the later missions are a real pain in the backside, as you spend ages quietly sneaking around and killing guards only to be spotted 3 feet from your main target... thereby having to restart the entire damn mission - and then once you get frustrated enough and just decide to use your sleeve pistol... the damn thing works and it only takes 2 minutes.\nI'd recommend getting it and playing it only if you have an XBox joypad hooked up to your PC or if you like very tricky controls.", "hours": 91.1, "username": "Druss - tGtribe", "products": 1256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-21", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is the sequel of Assassin's Creed.\nAfter the few years that passed, the developers created a game far more awesome and interesting than the first one.\nThe game is put on the 15th century, and the developers once again made brilliant exact copies of how the world was back then.\nVenice, Romagna, Florence are just a few of the locations implemented.\nBetter fighting system, more RPG elements, lots of side quests, awesome graphics, unique music, better climbing features (and additional sweeming abilities) and free running locations.\nAnd the storyline... oh the storyline is the perfection of the game. More interesting than ever.\nUp to every detail the game is awesome.\nRecommended for sure!", "hours": 89.8, "username": "Zweis\u2020ein ( \u0ca0_\u0ca0)", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-20", "text": "Excelente Juego sin duda de los mejores. Ezio es sin duda la mejor historia y la que mejor te envuelve en el mundo de Assassin\u00b4s Creed", "hours": 58.1, "username": "AyAkoSs", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-17", "text": "Assassins creed 1 perfected!", "hours": 39.0, "username": "General Kysieran", "products": 420, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "If you enjoy stabbin' fools in the face, Assassin's Creed 2 is for you.", "hours": 11.7, "username": "A Joker, A Smoker", "products": 416, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "Great game!", "hours": 64.4, "username": "AluminumHaste", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "I can find very few faults with the Assasssin's Creed series. All the games so far have been very well put together, on all fronts. The storyline is engaging, the gameplay is dynamic, and the atmosphere is beautiful.\nThat said, AC 2 and Brotherhood suffer from the heavy hand of Ubisoft anti-piracy tactics, especially on PC. They do, however, offer some incentives through the Uplay service in the form of ingame content unlockable through points gained from playing.\nIt really comes down to your opinion on DRM with these games. They are worthwhile investments, but if you've lost your internet connection, they're completely unplayable on PC. I can say though, owning Brotherhood on the PS3, that the console version is excellent as well, and the DRM not as draconic.\nYour choice.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "The Aughts", "products": 726, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "Everyone complains about the controls, but I promise this is a great game if you use an Xbox controler... I loved it!", "hours": 300.4, "username": "\u0291\u039e\u0273\u0622\u0288\u1e29\u0287\u042a [EN en ES]", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "Great game, buy it while it is on sale.  Give me my prize ticket.", "hours": 8.6, "username": "Walrus", "products": 396, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 537, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "Where the first Assassin's Creed succeeds this one this one excels all the more, and then proceeds to add a suite of new features and mechanics that highly impress. The locations are beautiful, and a heck of a lot of fun to run around in. The towns are alive and it is great to just \"free-run\" around and be imersed in the hustle and bustle of the cities. Free run is even better this time, with new skills to learn that will make it seem even faster and fluid than in the first game. As for the combat, where to start? The same beautiful animations and fluidity are present here, but in even greater number. Now you can not only wield swords, but also a collection of different maces, daggers, a double dual-blade, as well as smoke bombs and other nifty gadgets. There is also a whole new level of customization including a home town you can build up, different armor, and dyes. You can't lose with this awesome game, and I highly recommend it. 9.4/10.", "hours": 28.3, "user_id": "76561197972140596", "username": "Kelso", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "Some one sayed, that hitman is a stealth-action. I thought also so, till the moment i found Assassin's Creed. All the games of AC are \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing awesome!", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Baraquito", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "Great game, good evolution from game 1 and had all the things I wished game 1 had.", "hours": 41.6, "username": "Nitevox", "products": 270, "early_access": false}
