{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "Rooftop stabbings in Venice, what more can you ask for.", "hours": 87.4, "username": "Woon", "products": 133, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "An awesome game!", "hours": 11.4, "user_id": "76561198036162519", "username": "Miroslav", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "A fun sequel to the original.  Improves on most aspects, and includes many fun, albeit challenging, optional puzzles.  Definitely play through the first Assassin's Creed before starting #2.", "hours": 42.3, "username": "Haas", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 538, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 (AC2) is by far one of the best new franchises I have come across in a long time. The gameplay in AC2 is much more refined over AC1 and makes the assassin's movements much more fluid, dynamic and overall very capable. It's a powerful feeling to have control over such a versatile character.\nAs with the graphics, the story is fantastic - good script and excellent voice acting carry the narrative and make you feel for the characters.\nWith its various missions, cutscenes and sandbox nature, this is remeniscent of GTA IV for the rennaisance period - and that's not a bad thing by any means. If you enjoy single player games with deep story, believable characters and a variety of tasks, this is one hell of a bargain!\nMy rating: 5/5", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Nixor", "products": 293, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "A fun sequel to the original.  Improves on most aspects, and includes many fun, albeit challenging, optional puzzles.  Definitely play through the first Assassin's Creed before starting #2.", "hours": 42.3, "username": "Haas", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 (AC2) is by far one of the best new franchises I have come across in a long time. The gameplay in AC2 is much more refined over AC1 and makes the assassin's movements much more fluid, dynamic and overall very capable. It's a powerful feeling to have control over such a versatile character.\nAs with the graphics, the story is fantastic - good script and excellent voice acting carry the narrative and make you feel for the characters.\nWith its various missions, cutscenes and sandbox nature, this is remeniscent of GTA IV for the rennaisance period - and that's not a bad thing by any means. If you enjoy single player games with deep story, believable characters and a variety of tasks, this is one hell of a bargain!\nMy rating: 5/5", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Nixor", "products": 293, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "A classic I think. Took me some time to warm to it, but I go back and enjoy renaissance Italy from time to time. Damn, you can leave me at any spot in central Florence and I should know where I am...", "hours": 208.0, "username": "Cymbeline", "products": 154, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "I thought this might be a bit rubbish and only bought it because it was cheap, but it's actually quite good. If you like sneaking up on people and stabbing them in the throat (as I know you all do), then this is your game. I am not in any way writing this just to get in the prize draw.", "hours": 20.7, "user_id": "76561198019168225", "username": "Jagaimo", "products": 265, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "Stunning Graphics and seriously fun game play with a whole bundle of missions/quests that will keep you playing for several hours. One of the best action/adventure single players I've ever played, for sure.", "hours": 19.1, "username": "\u05d9\u266a Ron \u05e8 \u2605", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-05", "text": "Better than the original in virtually every way. Great historical attention to detail; it's great fun to explore Florence, Venice and San Giminiano.", "hours": 133.8, "user_id": "76561197979314382", "username": "swai", "products": 284, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-05", "text": "An improvement on the genre. More \"roamy\" if you feel like exploring, better feeling physics and combat, plus a top notch continuation of the story started in AC1, can't wait for the next in the series", "hours": 49.2, "username": "Oaknowledged", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "One hell of an Adventure. Ezio was the right choice.", "hours": 379.3, "username": "Bandit|MerC|", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "Ive never fallen asleep so many times playing a game. ever.", "hours": 40.4, "user_id": "76561197970921813", "username": "RJ", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 539, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "If you enjoy stealthy killer games you'll love this as you play as a guy who is very boring so he pretends to be his assassin ancestor (Ezio Auditore) in a virtual reality thingy machine because Ezio is cooler than the bland dude and gets all the ladies.\nAs (the boring Desmond guy as) Ezio you wander around and climb stuff in various places in Renaissance Italy in broad day light (alot of the time) even though you are supposed to be assassinating people with stealth. You are also able to blend in with others even though you are the only one wearing a hood and have weapons and armour hanging off you, ooh... and a nice little cape.\nBut putting all its little flaws aside this game is pretty epic. Ezio looks cool (though a bit silly in some ways), has cool killer moves and more moves than Altair, can swim unlike Altair and has a bigger variety of weapons than Altair. There is also many side missions and lots of stuff to collect aswell as the main story.", "hours": 63.0, "username": "Schnee", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 540, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "for me one of the pinacle of this series and what made so addicted to this game..\ni even reading the novel written based on this\nsummary this game is EPIC!!", "hours": 35.1, "username": "Finding Flea-mo", "products": 379, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 540, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "If you liked the first Assassin's Creed even the slightest, you'll find this one instantly appealing.  Fixing most of the major complaints about AC1, Assassin's Creed 2 also adds new depth by adding a very well-integrated upgrade system, indoor linear level design, and a more focused quests.  AC2 is wholly a superior game to the first effort, a redemption really.", "username": "Shi_Wei_Li", "products": 394, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 540, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "All the fun stabbing stealth action from the first game but now with a bit more intriguing story and more ways to go about missions", "hours": 37.8, "username": "Trash Pizza", "products": 135, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 540, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "Did not beat 1 yet, therefore I wont do the review.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "BloodCrow", "products": 246, "early_access": false}
