{"product_id": "33230", "page": 541, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Amazing. In my mind easily the best in the whole series, Assassin's Creed 2 has one of the most compelling characters and storylines without suffering from the bloat of later games in the series. Renaissance Italy has never looked so good. Also has an excellent soundtrack to accompany your acrobatic escapades.", "hours": 22.3, "user_id": "76561198007429524", "username": "[\u03c3\u03b2] nageler", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 541, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "I am absolutely stunned of amount of content Ubi did packed in almost 6 gigabytes. This game is way improved than it's predecessor. Solid 9/10.", "hours": 26.1, "username": "VashPL", "products": 385, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "If you liked Assassin's Creed, and you like games where you buy improvements, this will definitely entertain you for a good thirty to forty hours per playthrough. You can choose your weapons, refurbish a town, and even become a collector of art.", "hours": 131.7, "username": "Ibn Battuta", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Combat and missions improved from AC1, **LOTS** of main missions to assassinate instead of just 9 from AC1. The stealth missions can be hard (read: frustrating/\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665) but overall its a huge improvement from AC1. The story was the best part of AC1 and it is again here. The ending in AC1 was wtf, and this is WTF to the 100th power. Other than the bizarre/wtf endings, the story is really really good in both games.\nTL;DR: Good game, worth the price at $15.", "hours": 61.7, "username": "418", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Formulae Perfected. What more do you want?", "hours": 70.3, "user_id": "76561198004553140", "username": "Moral Wiz", "products": 479, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Join Ezio on his adventure to take down a secret society that killed his family when all he really wanted was all the ladies. Some professions just don't go well with getting some action.", "hours": 20.2, "username": "The Hidden Cost of Empathy", "products": 468, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Best game ever. Fun and immersive gameplay, awesome plot, intriguing puzzles, decent graphics, nice soundtrack and much more. And you'll end up learning more about the italian Renaissance than you did in school, lol.\n*Still as good today as the day it was released.", "username": "'C\u042f\u03bbZy! \u266c", "products": 672, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Great sequel to the previous game, with lots of content and an interesting story!", "hours": 39.6, "username": "Onyxthegreat", "products": 223, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "I'm like tha best, no doubt!", "hours": 42.5, "username": "Serpe", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Awesome game :)", "hours": 75.5, "username": "Thunder", "products": 1768, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "buy it", "hours": 29.8, "username": "Dan", "products": 791, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 542, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "A very unique game, and the most satisfying assassinations of any game I have ever played.", "hours": 35.2, "username": "MechBFP", "products": 369, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Leaps and bounds better than the original, this is pretty much one of Ubisoft's best games", "hours": 52.7, "username": "The Hitman", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Nice story, lots of sidequests and a long adventure. Much better than the first one.", "hours": 44.4, "username": "Ozgur", "products": 414, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "In ur city, killing ur d00dz", "hours": 30.0, "username": "Brinkman", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Better than AC", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Terro", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-30", "text": "Kinda like the first one, but way better. In this one, every mission is a story mission (with siome optional side stuff).", "hours": 18.1, "username": "Peewi", "products": 658, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "Just as good and better than the first game, the renisanace flare really sets this game in a different mode, the story is the best imho of any game in recent release with all the makings of a great interactive movie without any of the \"interactive movie\" \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t they have been trying to sell recently. Combat is fluid and intuitive, the PK is still top notch, a little hard to control with the keyboard (suggest a controler). Nothing says badass quite like the AC series, a dutiful sequal. ~10/10~", "hours": 41.2, "username": "DarkLilly [twitch.tv/darklilly]", "products": 1160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "79/100", "hours": 47.6, "username": "Condor Castle", "products": 2068, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-24", "text": "Fun game, beautifully detailed environment, interesting story especially if you are following the series, BUT this game has the worst save system I have ever seen in any game. While in game it keeps autosaving very frequently, but in order for the autosaves to register you need to exit the game and sync with an Ubisoft server which \"authorizes\" *cough* *DRM* *cough* the save game.\nGameplay- 8/10 lots of action, movement is fluid and controls work well once you are    familiar with them\nInterface- 5/10 the button layout displayed on the screen is ported directly from console and is more confusing than helpful at times\nVisuals- 9/10 not the best graphics, but I was impressed by the level of painstaking detail they put into designing the buildings (some were awe inspiring).\nPlot- 7/10 If you're into conspiracy theories you will love the story\nSpecial Features- 1/10 DRM that can (and has) prevent me from saving progress\nOverall Experience- 6/10 Had fun playing it until it failed to save", "hours": 39.3, "user_id": "76561198013591632", "username": "secretboggie", "products": 1743, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is exactly what a sequel should be: It improves upon everything the original achieved and adds it's own distinct identity to the series. Instead of following Altair through the holy land, this time you follow his somehow Itallian decendent Ezio from birth to adulthood. The story improves upon the first game in that the first game failed at making a Da Vinci Code knock off, where as AC2 is most definitely one! Right down to the HORRIBLE PLOT LATER IN THE GAME! But anyway, the graphics are gorgeous, the weapons are more imaginative and fun and the controls, mostly, seem tighter. The only issue I have with the controls is that AC2 demands much more precision than it's predecessor and they're just not good enough for some of the timed puzzles. AC2 also succeeds in making good use of cinematic cutscenes that add to rather than distract from the feel of the game. Most importantly, the missions are all varied and are even more fun this time around. VERY highly recommended!", "hours": 25.5, "user_id": "76561197980910801", "username": "Haute DIO", "products": 678, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 543, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-13", "text": "A great combination of stealth, action, and open-world gameplay. You take control of Ezio, via the ANIMUS system, in 1470 AD in Florence, Italy, engaged in a millenia-long struggle between templars and assassins.\nThe combat works well, and is best when you go for counter kills and disarming opponents. Mercenaries, thieves and \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s are at your disposal to distract city guards. Much of the game is spent scaling buildings and leaping across rooftops.\nLearning the controls can take some time, and straight fighting sequences (often tied to escort missions) can be a chore. However, most missions are rewarding, varied and well designed. There are tons of collectables, upgrades, and places to find. Plus, this deluxe version includes extra DLC released on consoles. With only a few flaws this is one of the highlights of the AC franchise and of open-world games in general.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "VampireStrike!", "products": 365, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-12", "text": "AC2 is almost perfection in my book. While it seems a little bit easier in combat than the first game, the story, the side quests, the customization, the dialogue, the scinarios, the controls - everything is much improved from the first game. While at first I wasn't too big on the Italian setting, it grows on you. It brings quite a bit more variety than the first game. Also the side quests are quite interesting as opposed to the first game - the game directly rewards you for doing side-quests, instead of some silly gimmick. Altiar's/Brutus' armor come to my mind. The addition of an Inventory and currency is very welcome as well... Can't wait to finish it and move on to Brotherhood.", "hours": 44.2, "username": "Skud", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-08", "text": "Following the adventures of Creed vocalist Scott Stapp in the first Assassin's Creed game, Creed must work together as a team to assassinate rival groups.  The game ends in a cliffhanger as Scott is sent back in time to 3rd century China and is forced to have a rap battle with a dragon.", "hours": 32.7, "username": "Dire Miralis", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-07", "text": "Tells a thrilling story and lays great gameplay fundamentals that are to be used in the next installments for sure.", "hours": 3.2, "username": "Roni", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-06", "text": "A remarkable sequel to a classic. It brings so much more to the assassin experience, with new weapons, new locations, and a fresh, well written story creating a well deserved sequel. Once again you take on the role of Desmond, but this time you play through the memories of Ezio Alditore. Ezio is a young lad who finds out his father was an Assassin all along, not a banker, and everyone else seems to know it but him. He finds out after a tragic turn of events, and now he's on a mission to get revenge. Little does he know, there is a force pushing him along behind the scenes. It's a beautiful game, and quite fun at that. Buy it, play it, love it.", "hours": 28.1, "username": "ManyNekoZ", "products": 1241, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-06", "text": "Excellent game though some assassin's tombs made me pound my fist to table until it hurt. I think i played it through in ~ 34 hours, and in three days time :)", "hours": 35.3, "user_id": "76561197999478853", "username": "[FC] KrazyK", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-05", "text": "It was a great storyline, with a good amount of history and rich character development. Just challenging enough without being excessively hard. Using the controversial timeline of Florence's history was ingenious on behalf of the writers. The ending was awesome and completely worth it. All in all a 10 out of 10 on my personal scale. Definitely a game I will remember for a long time to come. Can't wait for the third installment, AC 3 Revelations.", "hours": 73.1, "user_id": "76561198024392763", "username": "Arcsrazor", "products": 677, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-05", "text": "Beste sofort kaufen.", "hours": 19.7, "user_id": "76561198038822431", "username": "Hauptmann", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-04", "text": "Pros: Impressive architectures and environments, fluid city atmosphere, city building minigame, plenty of side missions (especially for completionists), funny jokes, choice of minigames\nCons: Ubisoft account registration, console-port menu, clunky AI, sub-par facial animations, clunky/buggy controls, button mash combat, holding 3 buttons to run, graphical glitches, glaring/white screens, boring storyline, glyph minigames, and the tomb missions.\nGet this on sale. Recommended strategy: get all the codex and tombs, and complete your city asap before you power through the main missions.", "hours": 28.4, "username": "Winter [Wild Hunt]", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-02", "text": "Following its predecessor, Assassin's Creed II improves everything from graphics to music and combat. Assassinating has never been easier with improved killing moves; is your target next to the ledge you're currently hanging from? Stab him and throw the body below! And with two Hidden Blades equipped, double kills are possible and satisfying.\nThe ending is even better than the first one.", "hours": 25.9, "user_id": "76561197985160995", "username": "J-Dub", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 544, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-01", "text": "Exelente juego, buenos graficos, buenos movimientos, la verdad, lo recomiendo. El unico problema que tuve fu\u00e9 un bug que encontr\u00e9 en una mision, en la cual se me friza la pantalla y no puedo avanzar, aun no le encontr\u00e9 solucion , creo saber cual es, pero necesito descargar el game de vuelta :P", "hours": 29.9, "username": "checho.-", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-31", "text": "sick!", "hours": 11.3, "username": "Cheesy Bean and Rice Burrito", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-29", "text": "This is how the first one should've been in the first place. The graphics are great (except for the faces maybe) and the gameplay is fun. There are more diverse missions this time around and you get to spend more time in the Animus instead of walking around in 'real life' with Desmond. Go get it if you like third persion action games, this one is a must (and after that play Brotherhood).\n[Rating: 90/100]", "hours": 9.3, "username": "mark | dj.", "products": 3577, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-29", "text": "Good story, lots of activities, big world.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "digibluez", "products": 583, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-29", "text": "AWESOMENESS", "hours": 57.5, "username": "Big Cum 61", "products": 240, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-24", "text": "Simply put, the best game I have ever played. Ever.\nI've played this game three times through, and I will often boot it up just to run around Venice or Florence and drop down on some poor unsuspecting guard.\nAs the franchise has moved on and combat mechanics have evolved to become faster paced and more dynamic, going back to AC2 can be a bit like going from a Ferrari to a Ford Focus. Still a solid game, but the combat can be tiringly slow as this was the last game in the series before they introduced kill streaks.\nVisually this game holds up very well. It is surprising to thik that this was a game from the earlier part of the last generation of consoles given how well it has dated and how good it really does look.\nThe sound in this game is simply phenominal. The soundtrack is the best in the series by a long shot, and the satisfying *squelch* when you stab a guy in the back is some kind of peverse pleasure.\nThe story is probably the smartest thing about the game. After you play you might fo to Wikipedia and look up the characters only to realise that, with the exception of the Auditore family, they were all real, or at least urban legends of their day. The way the Pazzi family are finished off is true to the history of the time in terms of locations and scenarios, and the way the game is blown wide open about half way through makes it a great plot with more and more to keep you guessing and trying to understand what is going on.\nAll in all, this game is stellar. If you haven't played an AC game yet this is as good a place as any to start. Fully recommended.", "hours": 162.4, "username": "hobnob", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-20", "text": "Better than the original, and though I was late at trying out Assassin's Creed because of it's multi-core processor requirements, I would have considered it worth the expense and a little more cutting edge, had a bought it when it was new.", "hours": 34.5, "user_id": "76561197970480286", "username": "Wh1ppet", "products": 653, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-14", "text": "So there's this guy named Dermont or something like that and some guys in white lab coats strap him down BDSM style to this table and make him relive his ancestor's past. His ancestor being a not-so-stealthy assassin in Jerusalem who is on a holy mission to find a globe.\nSo now, Part II takes place in Italy and you're the mayor of kill town. Gameplay mechanics have been cleaned up a lot, which had the unfortunate side-effect of making the combat a lot easier. The idea is to remain stealthy but if you're caught you can pretty much take on all of the world's guards with relative ease.", "hours": 32.4, "username": "Great White Flame", "products": 502, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-12", "text": "Awesome \u2014 from start to finish, its near perfect.", "hours": 176.1, "username": "S. Horton", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-12", "text": "Continuing the awesome Assassin's Creed saga, the second AC fixes pretty much everything the first AC's gameplay suffered from. Easily, one of the best single player game out there. If you dont own this game, you're missing something great in your life.", "hours": 35.6, "username": "Suiqr", "products": 587, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 545, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-09", "text": "Assassin's Creed... What else do you need to know to buy this game? :)", "hours": 56.4, "username": "JUK", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-08", "text": "O primeiro AC \u00e9 bom apesar de ser bastante repetitivo, mas este segundo game da franquia conseguiu ficar muito melhor, o jogo \u00e9 enorme e cheio de conte\u00fado, uma \u00f3tima hist\u00f3ria...\nAdorei esse game e recomendo com todas as for\u00e7as, podem comprar que n\u00e3o v\u00e3o se arrepender, estou ansioso para jogar o Brotherhood e o Revelations.... Assassins Creed \u00e9\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665...", "hours": 108.4, "username": "bubsylopez\u00ae", "products": 786, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-06", "text": "It's like there is a party in Italy and I can't stop attending.", "hours": 61.0, "username": "Felix", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed II follows the storyline perfectly, and adds a whole new twist to the story, which brings the emersive storyline and amazing gameplay to an entirely new level. I'd recommend this series for anyone who's looking for an amazing game that will keep you captivated for days on end.", "hours": 38.1, "username": "Apathy", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-22", "text": "In one word:stellar.", "hours": 106.0, "username": "M89", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-13", "text": "AC2 takes all the cool stuff from AC1 (the historical scenary, stealth aspects, etc) and further distills them into a digital drug that's hard to resist since it's now tempered by a much more varied gameplay (and a story that doesn't leave you with more questions than answers).  The current 30EUR pricetag makes this a must-buy if you like stealth/action games.  Personally, I could do without the \"Tombraider\" moments during some sequences in the game (where the awkward camera angles makes some jumps much harder than they should be), but they do offer a reprieve from all the disemboweling :P", "hours": 49.7, "user_id": "76561197970959678", "username": "t_therkelsen", "products": 865, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-11", "text": "dope game", "hours": 91.1, "username": "booty commander", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-09", "text": "Desmond Miles is back in Assassin's Creed II with another ancestral memories. This time it's Ezio Auditore da Firenze, the nobleman from Renaissance Italy. Desmond will explore the life and history of his own ancestor and learn to be an assassin. Ezio is cool and interesting new character. Gameplay is improved with diverse missions and game mechanic. There are new weapons and gadgets built by master inventor, Leonardo da Vinci. Ezio's life is quite drama and adventurous. Conspiracies behind the whole story is quite compelling. Game visual is great and those large Italian cities is really beautiful. Improve in almost every aspects, Assassin's Creed II shows what a good sequel should be.", "hours": 30.2, "username": "Aquamarine[TH]", "products": 913, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-28", "text": "This is a awesome game that really makes you feel like your an assassin that that era. Its fight style is very fluid and consistent. The graphics are wonderfully beautiful and very well done. The buildings in the game are very detailed. The story continues from Assassins Creed. It has new moves and new ways of getting around that really make the environment enjoyable to go around. Its a must have for any adventure lover! If you like the medieval era then this game would be a dream come true. Its a must have and a must play game. Its very hard to put down. I love it!", "hours": 30.7, "username": "NorkDorf On Twitch {Live}", "products": 8235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-27", "text": "A video game where you control a guy controlling another guy in a video game. Stars Nolan North, Veronica Mars, and Leonardo da Vinci.", "hours": 24.7, "username": "NotYou", "products": 269, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 546, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-24", "text": "My favorite game", "hours": 49.4, "username": "Gobbu", "products": 379, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "Jumping around the rooftops of Italian cities in the 1400s like a ninja and stabbing people in the face. Good times :D\nFirst game in the series was pretty good, if a little repetitive. This one improves on it in pretty much every way. Story is pretty good, combat is much improved, controls are about the same. Unfortunately that means the the controls vary between making you feel like a total bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665jumping from roof to roof, and making you scream \"EZIO! Y U NO JUMP WHERE I SAY!\"", "hours": 40.9, "username": "Lord JoJo T.", "products": 970, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-21", "text": "Say what you will about the repetition, Assassin's Creed has always been about highly refined movement and control, crisp aesthetics, and a somewhat risky plot, by today's standards.  Assassin's Creed 2 improves on the original exponentially by adding useful collectables, an upgradable home and town, and a twisting narrative, while preserving the same great gameplay from the first game, with a few surprises.  While the assassinations themselves are still a little disappointing, the architecture and setting makes for some of the most fun exploration you'll get out of any game. One of the few games I've been driven to complete 100%!\n9/10, easily.", "hours": 86.3, "username": "Pheener", "products": 562, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-18", "text": "I recommend it.", "hours": 187.8, "user_id": "76561198023019965", "username": "Pablo", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-12", "text": "Great game. However, support for Xbox 360 wireless controller is broken. Fortunately, there is a community patch that you can download to get proper support.", "hours": 41.4, "username": "Raistlin Majere", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-09", "text": "While the first one was good [If a bit repetitive]\nAC2 has been filled with even more story, I did not get bored at all playing this one.\nAnd I am looking forward to the next installation.", "hours": 24.7, "username": "Katheb", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-05", "text": "Great Game! Recommended for everyone!", "hours": 48.3, "username": "NetWalkerBR", "products": 688, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-02", "text": "Awesome Vertical gameplay, good story and graphics try it !", "hours": 45.9, "user_id": "76561198037245047", "username": "--<<JEZZAREAPER>>--", "products": 424, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-26", "text": "The continuing adventures of Desmond in the form of Ezio of Firenze, set in 15th century renaissance Italy, you must hunt down those who killed your father, meanwhile back in the present day you also come closer to the truth.... fantastic, well made game that just looks beautiful", "hours": 35.6, "username": "Nanaki", "products": 669, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-25", "text": "This is everything a sequel to a promising but flawed game needs to be. Assassin's Creed 2 improves on the free running strengths of the original while fixing the weaknesses of repetition. The change from the Crudsades time period to Renaissance Italy brings a fresh look that is rarely seen in video games. It's not quite a rigorous stealth game, a presicion platformer, or a stylish beat'em up but something inbetween that works well. Sadly, there is a very obtrusive digital rights management solution that requires a constant internet connection from the user and an online Ubi Soft server.", "hours": 44.3, "username": "Enner", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 547, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-22", "text": "\u30ad\u30fc\u30dc\u30fc\u30c9\u3067\u3084\u308b\u306e\u306f\u304d\u3064\u3044\u306e\u3067\u30d1\u30c3\u30c9\u63a8\u5968", "hours": 38.3, "username": "EDILTE", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
