{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-11", "text": "this game is  quite  easy,   no challenge at all'   no dificulty.   The graphic engine  is rather buggy,   even  with    Sapphire Radeon  5870 HD    x 2    ( CROSSFIREX )\ni wont get  Smooth fps  ingame,  with maxed out everything  1680x1050  120 hz.  which is disapointing.", "hours": 88.6, "user_id": "76561197975989943", "username": "Nikola", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-10", "text": "Very fun game!\nThe controls can be a bit hard to get used to at first (if you haven't played much of AC1). For the most part, the movement is fluid, but a few times Ezio got stuck or made a weird decision to leap off the side of a building for no reason...\nMuch better than what I glimpse from the 1 hour or so I've played of AC1, though the combat is still quite slow and focuses on counter-attacks.\nCampaign does look to be about 20 hours long, though if you do all the side missions and object hunts, it might push 35 hours. However, don't make my mistake and try looking for all the treasures BEFORE finishing the campaign, because that really make you tired :P\nBiggest complaint I have is that, for an assassin, Ezio is too strong in normal combat. Sure, he should be good, but there really is no incentive for staying in cover, except that it doesn't waste your time. I'd like to see battles that I know I will lose if I fight, but right now a 1v8 fight is actually a 1v1 fight 8 times.", "hours": 35.0, "username": "gNatFreak", "products": 616, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-09", "text": "Nicely addictive story based to Renaissance Italy and the scenery is simply stunning and environment is perfectly alive and there is plenty of to explore.\nHighly recommend to everyone who loves to have some adventure x)\n-Tero/Terry-", "hours": 13.2, "username": "Fedaygin \"Shai-Hulud\"", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-08", "text": "There are three games I will certainly remember for the rest of my life because of their breath-taking graphics, deep and intriguing plots, and fresh and exciting gameplay. Two of these are Bioshock and Mass Effect 2 (the latter of which I cannot review because I don't own it on Steam). The third is Assassin's Creed II. I'm personally conflicted on whether or not to recommend the first one. The original Assassin's Creed had some of the most bland  and repetitive gameplay I've ever witnessed. The sequel improves on EVERYTHING and tacks on tons of new feature. The only reason I'd have to pick up the first game is for the story. Whether you're a fan of action, puzzle, or story, this game has it all.\nGrade: A+", "hours": 38.7, "username": "DaNCeSWiTHBuLLeTS", "products": 1967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-07", "text": "An open world game NOT set in the US, and in a historical setting to boot! Big Thumbs up..", "hours": 39.1, "user_id": "76561197960708321", "username": "Alex2000", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-07", "text": "The far improved sequel to one of the best games of this generation. Simply compelling. Oh, and now that the DRM won't kick you out of your game if you lose your internet connection while playing, it's much easier to recommend.", "hours": 54.7, "username": "Morganagod", "products": 287, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-06", "text": "\"We're sorry, but feral cannot be here to recommend this game, as he is suffering from a seizure of this games pure awesome.\"", "hours": 64.4, "username": "FeralWolven", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 550, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-06", "text": "With cities like Florence and Venice renaissance period reproduced on this scale it's fun to just walk around and read about the buildings etc in the database(for me anyway, lol). Improves on Assasins Creed 1 in every way. Some of the best mini game puzzles I have ever encountered in a game too. Well worth picking up for the price.", "hours": 54.0, "user_id": "76561197965928460", "username": "starwatcher", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed II contiues the story of Desmond Miles through the 15th century assassin Ezio Auditore da Firenze.  Every aspect of its predecessor has been improved in this sequel, not to mention an ending that is one of the most memorable this generation.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "King Zudeous", "products": 722, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-03", "text": "very good game, more missions then the xbox version for some reason too.", "hours": 38.5, "user_id": "76561198015562210", "username": "Bullseye", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-02", "text": "Assassin\u2019s creed 2 is one of the best stealth games I have played within the last ~4 years. If you like action-stealth games you should play Assassins creed 2. If you hated the first Assassins Creed you really should play Assassins Creed 2. This game has done what the first assassin\u2019s creed fail to do; polish combat, customization, and side content. The combat now feels way more believable because enemies actually simultaneously strike you, unlike the first one where they took turns. The variety of weapons and items available to use also increase the \u201cfun\u201d factor in this game. I feel like a ninja when I use my smoke bombs to evade my enemies. I feel like a modern assassin with my throwing knives, and I feel like bat man when I use my flying machine. Lots of content to be had, I\u2019ve been playing for over 2 dozen hours, and still haven\u2019t beaten this game to 100% completion yet. The historical realism in the storytelling also makes the game very believable. Good Game. BUY", "hours": 89.2, "username": "amBADatgames", "products": 5168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-01", "text": "Because it has free roaming, Animus using, lake swimming, artwork purchasing, codex collecting, feather finding, horse riding, NPC hiring, money bribing, poster tearing, villa upgrading, dual blading, escort saving, Altair's clothing, knife throwing, crowd blending, rooftop jumping, corpse carrying, money chucking, tower climbing, Leonardo da Vinci meeting and beak doctors!", "hours": 35.4, "username": "Rivent", "products": 804, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-01", "text": "You need to play the prequel to understand how amazingly better this game is.", "hours": 3.1, "username": "Captain Kawaeho \ufed0", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-01", "text": "Brilliant cinematic feel to this game - from the voice acting to the camera angles to the overall archetectual design. A slight learning curve will lead to some wonderful gameplay. Worth my hard earned cash", "hours": 41.7, "username": "Fartemis Owl", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-31", "text": "Takes all the good things from the first game, and leaves (most of) the bad things. The action flows quite well, but it's unfortunate that (to give the game name credit) seemingly all you do is assassinate people, with the occasional mission to run around for a while.\nGuard behaviour is at least greatly improved over the first game, and guards won't go running after you just because you're in a hurry to get somewhere.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Sadface", "products": 677, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-31", "text": "If you like stabbing fools, buy this.", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561197995413354", "username": "codeLlama", "products": 694, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 551, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-31", "text": "Great game wih a full cast of characters and enviroments. While the side quest can still get repetitve and the the game is a little too easy. All and all it's well worth a playthrough.", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Alexzandar", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
