{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2 is probably the best game I played in 2010.  It far exceeds the first one, and is as \"complete\" a game experience as I've ever had.  There's almost nothing I would change or add to the game.", "hours": 67.0, "username": "Sweetz", "products": 356, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "Awesome Storyline, Innovative Gameplay, Great music fits the setting.", "hours": 267.3, "username": "Revassin", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "Buy it. One of the best games of the year.", "hours": 79.4, "username": "Neon", "products": 762, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "If the first one was an ugly prototype in stealth-based open world gaming, this is the production model: both flashy and functional.  There's more to do, more to see, and the counter-kills are as gleefully savage as ever.", "hours": 28.6, "username": "BurningHeron", "products": 170, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-06", "text": "This game has really pretty grafics, a jaw dropping storyline, awesome assassination possibilities and authentic buildings from 500 years ago. The crowd is the most interactive crowd i have ever seen in a game! i can spend a lot of time just messing around with people. GO BUY assassins creed 1 first, because that game is almost as awesome as this!", "hours": 126.1, "username": "Repsack", "products": 502, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-05", "text": "Yeah, first i thought its some tombrider BS, but its actually p. awesome. with a nice story, and nice balance, nice graphics. yeah, its p. awesome.\ni would suggest to play it with a gamepad.", "hours": 40.5, "username": "Doctor Yootz", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-25", "text": "Well worth the investment if you have a reliable connection. Where the first game seemed great in theory, but fell flat in practice with monotonous gameplay/missions, this game excels in sandbox-y excellence. Even if you didn't like the original, I urge you to give this a try.  I'm enjoying it immensely.", "hours": 28.4, "username": "Calcographer", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-24", "text": "Exceeds the first game in all the important ways, it's gripping, exciting, tense, and has improved combat. The puzzles can be frustrating and there is one nearly impossible mission, but overall this is an incredible entry in the Creed.", "hours": 46.2, "username": "DyeHardFan", "products": 231, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-24", "text": "Gondolas and courtesans.", "hours": 24.6, "username": "Bees?", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 553, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-23", "text": "Stabbity stab. Jump jump. Hookers.", "hours": 34.7, "username": "Fungineero", "products": 186, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-20", "text": "Brilliant RPG - on a par with Mass Effect 2 - the concept of the game is a clever vehicle for any historical game play theatre they can think of.  I'll be getting \"Assassin's Creed 2 : Brotherhood\" for sure.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "causticspit", "products": 564, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-20", "text": "(It's glorious)", "hours": 54.3, "user_id": "76561198007139654", "username": "MeMEME", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "Great story line that leaves you wanting more, and great lure and extra content makes the story even more desirable. The game play is also great with new weapons and features not seen in the previous game.", "hours": 47.4, "username": "Jaykoni", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "A vast improvement in gameplay from the first game, which rode on the wings of its original concept, but fell flat in gameplay and story pacing.  Superb graphics and a very compelling story with good pacing, and a likeable, relatable hero.  One of the top two games I've played this year.", "hours": 50.7, "username": "MX OneFive", "products": 986, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "Compared to the 1st Assassins Creed its not perfect but i do highly recomend it although the PC version needs some serious updating cause of mega lag due to its required internet connection, but overall its good!", "hours": 281.8, "username": "The Pasha [\u262a\u26051453rd\u262a\u2605]", "products": 298, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "Great gameplay, excellent story, replay value is good. Needs a beefy rig to play, however.", "hours": 63.7, "username": "Count Brolaf", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "33230", "page": 554, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is the beast. But Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood will be a lot better of course when it finallys comes out in Steam.", "hours": 350.9, "username": "Gunsmoke", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
